Elmer Davis ( January 13 , 1890 -- May 18 , 1958 ) was a news reporter , author , the Director of the United States Office of War Information during World War II and a Peabody Award recipient .
Bernhard Walterbach ( 30 October 1918 -- 26 July 1997 ) was a highly decorated Leutnant of the Reserves in the Wehrmacht during World War II , and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .

Erich Zepper ( 27 November 1915 -- 28 July 2005 ) was a Untersturmführer ( 2nd Lieutenant ) in the Waffen SS during World War II who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany during World War II .

Mahrukh Tarapor is an Indian museum professional and art consultant , known for her scholarship in museum art , especially Islamic art . She was honoured by the Government of India , in 2013 , by bestowing on her the Padma Shri , the fourth highest civilian award , for her contributions to the field of art .
Hans - Detloff von Cossel ( 1 July 1916 -- 22 July 1943 ) was a Major in the Wehrmacht during World War II . He was a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
Diethelm von Eichel - Streiber ( 1914 - -1996 ) was a Luftwaffe flying ace of World War II . He claimed a total of 96 victories and was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .

Fritz Haber ( German : ( ˈhaːbɐ ) ; 9 December 1868 -- 29 January 1934 ) was a German chemist who received the Nobel Prize in Chemistry in 1918 for his invention of the Haber - Bosch process , the method used in industry to synthesize ammonia from nitrogen and hydrogen gases .
Ernst Tiburzy ( 26 December 1911 -- 14 November 2004 ) was a German Volkssturm - Bataillonsführer who received the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross for his performance fighting alone and the destruction of five or nine T-34s with Panzerfausts during the defense of Königsberg on February 10 , 1945 .

King 's Crossing was a completely different show , but employed several actors ( including Doran Clark , Linda Hamilton , Marilyn Jones , and Daniel Zippi ) who had also appeared in the earlier drama .
The Son of Robin Hood is a 1958 adventure DeLuxe color CinemaScope film directed by George Sherman , starring David Hedison and June Laverick .
Polish Wedding is a 1998 American comedy - drama film written and directed by Theresa Connelly and is also ( a then - unknown ) Kristen Bell 's film debut in her uncredited role .
Suvarna Simhaasanam is a 1997 Indian Malayalam film directed by P. G. Vishwambharan and starring Suresh Gopi , Mukesh and Ranjitha in the lead roles .
Midnight Run is a 1988 American action - comedy film directed by Martin Brest and starring Robert De Niro and Charles Grodin .
Three Men and a Girl is a lost 1919 American romantic comedy film directed by Marshall Neilan and starring Marguerite Clark .
Timber Falls is a 2007 horror - thriller film with elements of a slasher film directed by Tony Giglio , it stars Josh Randall and Brianna Brown .
Empty Days ( French : Rien à faire ) is a 1999 French drama film written and directed by Marion Vernoux and starring Valeria Bruni Tedeschi .
Six Million and One ( Hebrew : שישה מיליון ואחד ) is a 2011 Israeli documentary film , a Fisher Features Ltd. release , written directed and produced by David Fisher .
Andha Kanoon ( Hindi : अंधा क़ानून ; English : Blind Law ) is a 1983 Bollywood drama film directed by T. Rama Rao , starring Rajinikanth , Hema Malini , Reena Roy .
The Probation Wife is a 1919 American silent comedy drama film directed by Sidney Franklin and starring Norma Talmadge .
13 Dead Men is a 2003 film starring rapper Mystikal and Lorenzo Lamas .
The Corbett - Fitzsimmons Fight is an 1897 documentary film directed by Enoch J. Rector depicting a boxing match between James J. Corbett and Bob Fitzsimmons in Carson City , Nevada on St. Patrick 's Day the same year .
The Vice of Humanity ( German : Laster der Menschheit ) is a 1927 German silent drama film directed by Rudolf Meinert and starring Asta Nielsen , Werner Krauss and Alfred Abel .
Dorf and the First Games of Mount Olympus is a 1988 comedy film starring Tim Conway and Vincent Schiavelli .
Gimme the Power is a 2012 Mexican documentary film by Olallo Rubio about the band Molotov .
The Two Mrs. Carrolls is a 1947 mystery film starring Humphrey Bogart , Barbara Stanwyck , and Alexis Smith , directed by Peter Godfrey , and produced by Mark Hellinger from a screenplay by Thomas Job , based on the 1935 play by Martin Vale .

The Mad Game is a 1933 American Pre - Code crime drama film about an imprisoned bootlegger ( Spencer Tracy ) recruited from incarceration to help capture his own gang after they kidnap the daughter ( Claire Trevor ) of the judge who jailed him .

Oberleutnant Franz Peter ( 8 October 1896 -- 1968 ) was an Austrian flying ace credited with six aerial victories in World War I. After World War I , Peter decided to join the Polish Air Force , encouraged by Stefan Stec , with whom he had served during the war .

Savage Mostyn ( c.1713 -- 16 September 1757 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy who saw service during the War of the Austrian Succession and the Seven Years ' War .
The 31st Indian Armoured Division was an armoured division of the Indian Army during World War II , formed in 1940 , as 1st Indian Armoured Division ; it consisted of units of the British Army and the British Indian Army .

Danville Leadbetter ( August 26 , 1811 -- September 26 , 1866 ) was a career U.S. Army officer and later he served as a Confederate general during the American Civil War .
Colonel Tomb , also `` Nguyen Toon '' ( Nguyễn Tuân ) or `` Colonel Toon '' was a mythical North Vietnamese fighter pilot and flying ace who allegedly shot down 13 American aircraft during the Vietnam War .

Gordon Byrom Rogers ( August 22 , 1901 -- July 3 , 1967 ) was a United States Army Lieutenant General who served in several command positions during World War II and the Korean War , including the United States Military Advisory Group to the Republic of Korea and the 3rd Armored Division .
Alberto Salinas Carranza ( November 15 , 1892 -- October 31 , 1970 ) was a Mexican aviator who participated in the Mexican Revolution .

Alfredo Guzzoni ( 12 April 1877 -- 15 April 1965 ) was an Italian military officer who served in both World War I and World War II .
Thomas James Maling ( 15 July 1778 -- 22 January 1849 ) was a Royal Navy officer , a captain during Napoleonic Wars and later promoted to Rear - Admiral .
Lieutenant General George C. Axtell ( November 29 , 1920 -- August 20 , 2011 ) was a retired United States Marine Corps general officer and a World War II ace and Navy Cross recipient .
Kay Summersby ( 23 November 1908 -- 20 January 1975 ) was a member of the British Mechanised Transport Corps during World War II , who served as chauffeur to Supreme Commander Allied Expeditionary Force Dwight D. Eisenhower , later as his secretary .
Vize - Wachtmeister Elo Sambo ( 1885 - 1933 ) was a Cameroonian who served in the Imperial German Army in World War I , notable for being one of very few Africans to do so .

Lambda Persei ( λ Per , λ Persei ) is a star in the constellation Perseus .

Imtiaz Gilani is a Pakistani civil engineer and a vice chancellor of the University of Engineering and Technology ( Peshawar ) , Pakistan from 2004 till now ( September 2013 ) .
Arjun Modhwadia is an active politician from Gujarat , India .
Sue Wells ( 29 September 1965 ) is a media personality and former city councillor in Christchurch , New Zealand .

Gustav Lorentzen ( 28 September 1947 -- 21 April 2010 ) , also known by his stage name Ludvigsen , was a Norwegian singer - songwriter , best known from being half of the successful duo Knutsen & Ludvigsen , alongside Øystein `` Knutsen '' Dolmen .

Landon Carter ( August 1710 -- December 22 , 1778 ) was a planter from Virginia , best known for his account of colonial life leading up the American War of Independence , The Diary of Colonel Landon Carter .

Jovan Marinović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јован Мариновић ; 1821 -- August 30 , 1893 ) was a Serbian politician and diplomat , that introduced several enlightened reforms in Serbian political system .

Christian Goller ( born 1943 ) is a German painter and trained art restorer who is under investigation by German authorities regarding a number of paintings attributed to Lucas Cranach the Elder .

Bradley ( born c. 1945 ) was a lieutenant general in the United States Air Force who served as Commander of the United States Air Force Reserve Command , Headquarters U.S. Air Force , Washington D.C. , and commander , Headquarters Air Force Reserve , a separate operating agency located at Robins Air Force Base , Georgia .

Count Faustino Duranti ( 1695 - -1766 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of illumination and miniature portraits .
Solomon Blay ( 20 January 1816 -- 20 August 1897 ) was an English convict transported to the Australian penal colony of Van Diemen 's Land ( present - day Tasmania ) .
Georges Paulmier ( 24 December 1882 in Frepillon -- 30 December 1956 in Chateaudin ) was a French professional road bicycle racer , who won two stages in the early Tour de Frances .
Professor Ricardo Galeazzi ( 1866 -- 1952 ) was an Italian orthopaedic surgeon remembered for describing the Galeazzi fracture .
Helen Suzman , DBE ( 7 November 1917 -- 1 January 2009 ) was a liberal South African anti - apartheid activist and politician .
Pedlar Palmer , born Thomas Palmer , ( 1876 - 1949 ) was a British boxer who held the world bantamweight championship from 1895 - 1899 .
James Annand ( 1843 -- 6 February 1906 ) was a Scottish journalist , newspaper editor and Liberal Party politician .
Maulsby Willett Blackman ( 1876 - -1943 ) was an American entomologist .
Alphons Czibulka , Alfons Czibulka , or Czibulka Alfonz ( 14 May 1842 -- 27 October 1894 ) was an Austro - Hungarian military bandmaster , composer , pianist , and conductor .
Musa Haji Ismail Galal ( Somali : Muuse Xaaji Ismaaciil Galaal , Arabic : موسى الحاج اسماعيل جلال‎ ) ( 1917 - -1980 ) was a Somali writer , scholar , linguist , historian and polymath .
Reverend Charles Bigg , DD ( 1840 - -1908 ) was a Church of England clergyman , theologian and church historian .
Peer Guldbrandsen ( 22 October 1912 -- 13 March 1996 ) was a Danish screenwriter , actor , film director and producer .
Terry Winter Owens ( 1941 -- 31 July 2007 ) was an American composer and music educator .
Sir John Philipps , 6th Baronet PC ( c. 1701 -- 22 June 1764 ) was a Welsh Jacobite politician .
Francis Marlow ( 8 October 1867 Tamworth , Staffordshire - 7 August 1952 Hove , Sussex ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket principally for Sussex
Karsten Friis Johansen ( 5 December 1930 -- 29 July 2010 ) was a Danish philosopher and classical philologist .
Marie Cazin ( née Guillet ; 1845 , Paimboeuf -- 18 March 1924 , Boulogne ) was a French painter , sculptor , and decorative artist .
Malcolm Judge ( 1918 -- 17 January 1989 ) was a British cartoonist , best known for his contributions to DC Thomson 's range of comics .
Edward Elwall , born 9 November 1676 , died 29 November 1744 , was a mercer and grocer , born at Sedgley near Wolverhampton .
John Hartnup Jr. ( 1841 -- 21 April 1892 ) was the second director of the Liverpool Observatory ( which has since moved to become the Bidston Observatory ) located at the West Waterloo Dock on the River Mersey in Liverpool , England .
Carlos Santana Becerra ( 1908-March 11 , 1971 ) served for over 13 years as an Associate Justice of the Puerto Rico Supreme Court .
Siegfried Dehn ( 24 February 1799 -- 12 April 1858 ) was a German music theorist , editor , teacher and librarian .
K. B. Tilak ( 14 January 1926 -- 23 September 2010 ) was an Indian independence activist , film director and producer .
Prospero Fagnani ( born in Italy , place and date of birth uncertain ; died 1678 ) was an Italian canon lawyer .
Lakhajirajsinhji II Bavajirajsinhji ( 17 December 1885 -- 2 February 1930 ) , the 12th Thakore Saheb of Rajkot , was an Indian nobleman , who was ruler of the princely state of Rajkot from April 1890 until his death .
Raymond Clare Archibald ( 7 October 1875 - -26 July 1955 ) was a prominent Canadian - American mathematician .
Jacob Cornelisz van Oostsanen ( before 1470 -- 1533 ) was a Northern Netherlandish designer of woodcuts and painter .
Abelardo Aguilú , Jr. ( ca . 1870 - ca . 1940 ) was Mayor of Ponce , Puerto Rico from 1924 to 1925 .
Lieutenant - Colonel Vivian Bullwinkel , Mrs. Statham , AO , MBE , ARRC , ED , FNM ( 18 December 1915 -- 3 July 2000 ) was an Australian Army nurse during the Second World War .
James Ferrie ( born 1857 ; died 1929 ) was a Scottish checkers or English draughts player of Irish descent .
Ágoston Valentiny ( 6 October 1888 -- 21 August 1958 ) was a Hungarian politician and jurist , who served as Minister of Justice in the Interim National Government .
Richard Bushrode , also Bushrod ( 1576 - 1 July 1628 ) was an English haberdasher and merchant adventurer and a politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1624 and 1626 .
Samuel Sanders ( 27 June 1937 -- 9 July 1999 ) was a distinguished American classical pianist known for sensitive collaborations with noted soloists .
Helen Allingham ( née Helen Mary Elizabeth Paterson ) ( 26 September 1848 -- 28 September 1926 ) was an English watercolour painter and illustrator of the Victorian era .
John Poulett , 1st Baron Poulett , ( 1585 -- 20 March 1649 ) of Hinton St George , Somerset , was an English sailor and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1610 and 1621 and was later raised to the peerage .
Feng Chian or Feng Zhi'an ( Chinese : 冯治安 ; Wade -- Giles : Feng Chih - an ; 1896 - -1954 ) was a Chinese Nationalist Lieutenant - General during the Second Sino - Japanese War , from Hebei .
Empress Dowager Chinu ( 叱奴太后 , personal name unknown ) ( died 574 ) , formally Empress Xuan ( 宣皇后 , literally `` the responsible empress '' ) , was an empress dowager of the Chinese / Xianbei dynasty Northern Zhou .
Leonhard Haskel ( 7 April 1872 -- 30 December 1923 ) was a German stage and film actor and drama teacher .
Eristavi Zaal , Duke of Aragvi ( died 1660 ) was a powerful Georgian lord who controlled much of Kakheti in the seventeenth century .
Johann Berthold von Höffer ( born in Ljubljana on 24 July 1667 - died 1718 ) was a nobleman from Ljubljana , and an amateur Slovenian composer .
Pavle Merkù ( pronounced ( ˈpaːu̯lɛ mɛɾˈku ) ) ( 12 July 1927 -- 20 October 2014 ) was an Italian - Slovene composer , ethnomusicologist , Slovene specialist , and etymologist .
Jesus Fuertes ( 14 April 1938 -- 18 June 2006 ) was a Cubist painter , who was initiated into the world of art by Salvador Dalí , and was described as a `` true genius '' by Pablo Picasso .
Thomas Draxe ( died 1618 ) was an English divine , a theological and classical author .
Narayan Maharaj ( 20 May 1885 -- 3 September 1945 ) was a Hindu Indian spiritual master considered by his followers to be a sadguru .
Hermann Vermeil ( 1889 - -1959 ) was a German mathematician who produced the first published proof that the scalar curvature is the only absolute invariant among those of prescribed type suitable for Einstein 's theory .
Duomi Khan ( 多彌可汗 ) ( died 646 ) , personal name Bazhuo ( 拔灼 ) , full regal name Jialijulixueshaduomi Khan ( 頡利俱利薛沙多彌可汗 ) , was a khan of the Xueyantuo .
Alec Taylor , Jr. ( 1862 - -1943 ) , known as the Wizard of Manton , was a British Thoroughbred racehorse trainer who followed in the footsteps of his highly successful father , Alec Taylor , Sr ..
Archduke Wenceslaus of Austria ( 9 March 1561 -- 22 September 1578 ) , was a German prince and member of the House of Habsburg and since 1577 Grand Prior of the Order of Malta in Castile .
Heinz August Kämpfer ( 31 March 1901 -- 14 April 1943 ) , Meister ( Master ) in the German Gendarmerie ( Rural Police ) , was an early member of the Nazi Party ( NSDAP ) and holder of the Golden Party Badge and the Gau Thüringen Commemorative Badge .
Johan Storjohann ( 15 August 1832 -- 23 April 1914 ) was a Norwegian priest , educator and non - fiction writer .
Ernst Ziegler ( born Ernst Aldoff , 16 April 1894 -- 11 April 1974 ) , was a German actor .
Edward Lippincott Tilton ( 19 October 1861 -- January 1933 ) was an American architect , with a practice in New York City , where he was born .
Nicola Agnozzi ( 5 November 1911 -- 17 February 2008 ) was an Italian Prelate of Roman Catholic Church .
Augustus Hotham ( date of birth unknown , -- 24 December 1896 ) was an Australian cricketer .
Edward Griffiths ( 7 March 1929 - 18 October 1995 ) was a British Labour politician and director of the British Steel Association .
Stanisław Radziwon ( b. Dolistowo 29 August 1907 then Russian Empire -- d. Edinburgh , Scotland 10 July 1973 ) was a Polish administrator , soldier and an active member of the Polish émigré community in Scotland .
Sir Thomas Norris ( Norreys ) ( 1556 - -1599 ) was an English soldier , made Lord President of Munster in Ireland .
Fernando García de Hita ( or de Fita ; floruit 1097 - -1125 ) was a Castilian nobleman , traditionally considered the founder of the noble House of Castro .
Friedrich Rehberg ( 22 October 1758 - 20 August 1835 ) was a German portrait and historical painter .
Sir Busick Harwood ( 1745 ? -- 10 November 1814 ) was an English physician who became Professor of Anatomy at Cambridge .
Shlomo Sztencl ( Hebrew : שלמה שטנצל‎ , pronounced Shtentzel ) ( 1884 - -1919 ) was a Polish Orthodox Jewish rabbi .
Dabney Cosby ( c. 1793 -- August 1862 ) was an American architect and builder active primarily in Virginia and North Carolina .
Walid Hassan ( born c. 1959 - d. 20 November 2006 ) was a Shia Muslim Iraqi comedian .
Edward Bocking ( died 1534 ) was a controversial monk during the reign of King Henry VIII . He attended Oxford where he received a B.D. in 1513 and a D.D. in 1518 .
John Bourchier , 1st Earl of Bath ( 20 July 1470 -- 30 April 1539 ) was created Earl of Bath in 1536 .
John Ross Macduff ( 23 May 1818 - 30 April 1895 ) was a Scottish divine and a prolific author of religious essays .
Wincenty Konstanty Kalinowski , also known as Kastuś Kalinoŭski ( Belarusian : Касту́сь Каліно́ўскі ) , Konstanty Kalinowski ( Polish ) and Konstantinas Kalinauskas ( Lithuanian ) ( 21 January or 2 February 1838 -- 22 March 1864 ) , was a 19th - century writer , journalist , lawyer and revolutionary .
Jerzy Semkow ( 12 October 1928 -- 23 December 2014 ) was a Polish - born French conductor .
Rosa Albach - Retty ( 26 December 1874 -- 26 August 1980 ) was an Austrian movie and stage actress .
John Shakespeare was buried on 8 September 1601 .
Sir John St John , 1st Baronet ( 5 November 1585 - -1648 ) of Lydiard Tregoze in the English county of Wiltshire , was a Member of Parliament and prominent Royalist during the English Civil War .
Mahasi Sayadaw U Sobhana ( Burmese : မဟာစည်ဆရာတော် ဦးသောဘန , pronounced : ( məhàsì sʰəjàdɔ̀ ʔú θɔ́bəna̰ ) ; 29 July 1904 -- 14 August 1982 ) was a Burmese Theravada Buddhist monk and meditation master who had a significant impact on the teaching of Vipassana ( Insight ) meditation in the West and throughout Asia .
Edward Mack ( 1826 - -1882 ) , also known as E. Mack , was a German American composer .
Granado Pigot ( c.1650 - 1724 ) , of Bassingbourn , Cambridgeshire , was an English politician .
Donald Francis Roy ( 1909 - -1980 ) was a sociologist on the faculty of Duke University from 1950 to 1979 .
Morag Hood ( 12 December 1942 -- 5 October 2002 ) was a Scottish actress described by many commentators as `` a celebrated beauty , '' who featured in numerous British programmes , stage productions , and audio presentations from the 1960s up to the late 1990s .
Ann Rowan ( died 10 August 2014 ) was an Irish actress .
Ernestine Cannon ( 1904 - 1969 ) , also known as Ernestine Virden - Cannon , was an American ceramicist and designer of dinner ware whose business , Ceramica D'Arte , was based in Italy .
Rev. Thomas Huet ( died 19 August 1591 ) was a Welsh clergyman and translator of the Bible .
Despite his previous accomplishments , the true measure of Bernardo Rossellino 's architectural place in history lies in the extraordinary project he undertook for Pope Pius II Piccolomini at Pienza between 1459 and 1464 .
Aziz Mahmud Hudayi ( 1541 - -1628 ) , ( b. Şereflikoçhisar , d. Üsküdar ) , is amongst the most famous sufi ermiş ( Muslim saint ) of the Ottoman Empire .
Gustaf Edvard Helenelund ( 6 June 1885 , Solf - 13 March 1976 ) was a Swedish - speaking Finnish farmer and politician .
Safiya Zaghloul ( 1876 - -1946 ) was an Egyptian political activist .
George Milner Stephen ( 18 December 1812 -- 16 January 1894 ) , often written G. Milner Stephen , was a South Australian and Victorian politician and faith healer .
Volney White ( 20 May 1907 - 23 December 1966 ) was an American animator and director active in the late 1930s and early 1940s .
Carlos Alfredo D'Amico ( 23 March 1839 , Buenos Aires -- 18 August 1917 ) was an Argentine lawyer , politician and writer .
Joseph Leo Loftus ( born 24 January 1906 in Ferryhill and died 23 October 1992 in Durham Central ) was an English footballer who played as an inside left .
Cornelius Ludewich Bartels ( unknown -- 18 April 1804 ) was a military and colonial officer of German origin employed by the Dutch West India Company .
Jørgen Juve ( 22 November 1906 -- 12 April 1983 ) was a Norwegian football player , jurist , journalist and non - fiction writer .
Andrew Willatsen ( 8 October 1876 - 25 July 1974 ) was an architect chiefly remembered for bringing the influence of Frank Lloyd Wright and the Prairie School to the Pacific Northwest .
Michel Luc ( 7 February 1927 -- 18 January 2010 ) was a French zoologist ( nematologist ) and one of the founding father of the field of plant - nematology .
Tamura Takaaki ( 1517 ? -- 1574 ) was a Japanese samurai of the Sengoku period , who served the Date clan .
Byron Duckenfield died , aged 93 , on 19 November 2010 in Bretby , Derbyshire .
John Delbridge ( 1564 - -1639 ) was an English merchant from Devon who was elected six times as Member of Parliament for his home town , the borough of Barnstaple , in the years 1614 , 1621 , 1624 , 1625 , 1626 and 1628 .
Francis Herbert Dufty , II ( 1846 - 1910 ) , who was also known as Frank Dufty , was an English - born Australian photographer , known for his photographs of Fiji .
Adam de Brome ( /də ˈbruːm/ ; died 16 June 1332 ) was an almoner to King Edward II and founder of Oriel College in Oxford , England .
Khwaja Qamar ul Din Sialvi ( 1906 - -1981 ) known as Shaykh - ul - Islam was a Pakistani Islamic scholar , religious leader and politician .
Sir Victor Gollancz ( 9 April 1893 -- 8 February 1967 ) was a British publisher and humanitarian .
Stephan Lucien Joseph van Waardenburg ( 21 February 1900 -- 4 April 1975 ) was the first Dutch - appointed governor of Dutch New Guinea .
Henri Maillardet ( 1745 - -1830 , born Jean Henri Nicholas Maillardet ) , was a Swiss mechanician of the 18th century who worked in London producing clocks and other mechanisms .
Elena Paunero Ruiz ( born 21 September 1906 -- 9 March 2009 ) was a Spanish botanist who specialised in agricultural botany .
Sir Richard Warde ( died 1578 ) was an English politician and royal official .
Albert Seitz ( 24 June 1872 in Besançon -- 23 September 1937 ) was a French composer and viola player .
Jörg Syrlin the Younger ( c.1455 - -1521 ) was a German sculptor .
Sir Edward Mackay Edgar , 1st Baronet ( 27 February 1876 -- 7 October 1934 ) was a Canadian - British banker .
Princess Frederica Caroline of Saxe - Coburg - Saalfeld , Duchess in Saxony ( 24 June 1735 -- 18 February 1791 ) was a princess of Saxe - Coburg - Saalfeld by birth and through marriage the last Margravine of Brandenburg - Ansbach and Bayreuth .
Peter Faucett ( 1813 -- 22 May 1894 ) was an Australian barrister , jurist and politician .
Hachaliah Bailey ( pronounced heck - a - LIE - uh ) ( Jul 31 , 1775 -- Sep 2 , 1845 ) is the eponym of Bailey 's Crossroads , Virginia and a relative to several famous individuals involved in early American circuses .
Harris Newmark ( July 5 , 1834 -- 1916 ) was a Prussian - American businessman , philanthropist , and historian .
Tawfik Toubi ( Arabic : توفيق طوبي‎ , Hebrew : תופיק טובי‎ , 11 May 1922 -- 12 March 2011 ) was an Israeli Arab communist politician .
Émonn Ó Braonain , subject of an Irish poem , died 30 November 1632 .
Sir Edward Darcy , Darcey or Darsey ( 1543/1544 -- 28 October 1612 ) of Stainforth , East Riding of Yorkshire , was an English politician and courtier .
Jabra Nicola ( Arabic : جبرا نقولا‎ , Hebrew : ג'ברא ניקולא ; February 16 , 1912 - December 25 , 1974 ) was an Arab Israeli and Palestinian Trotskyist leader , the author of numerous articles and pamphlets who also translated some of the classics of Marxism into Arabic .
John Gawen ( died 1418 ) , of Norrington , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
Arthur Ernest Hagg ( 1888 to 21 January 1985 ) was a British aircraft and boat designer .

Emmy Hennings ( born Emma Maria Cordsen , 17 January 1885 -- 10 August 1948 ) was a performer and poet .
Lewis P. Firey ( 11 April 1825 -- 5 March 1885 ) was a Southern Unionist who served in the Maryland State Convention , and the Maryland State Senate during the American Civil War .
Isaac Joslin Cox , Ph.D. ( 1873 - -1956 ) was an American professor of history .
Vladimir Vyshpolsky ( Russian : Владимир Владимирович Вышпольский ; 28 December 1915 -- 18 February 1987 ) was a Soviet Olympic fencer .
James Fawckner Nicholls ( 1818 - -1883 ) was an English antiquarian and librarian .
Maura Laverty ( née Kelly ; 1907 -- 26 July 1966 ) was an Irish author , journalist and broadcaster known for her work on Irish soap opera Tolka Row .
Juanita Molina de Fromen ( 1893 - 1934 ) was a Nicaraguan educator and feminist .
Karobo Moses Motsisi ( 1932 - -1977 ) , better known as Casey Motsisi or Casey `` Kid '' Motsisi , was a South African short - story writer and journalist .
Eben Norton Horsford ( 27 July 1818 -- 1 January 1893 ) was an American scientist who is best known for his reformulation of baking powder , his interest in Viking settlements in America , and the monuments he built to Leif Erikson .
Hamlet Watling ( b. Kelsale , Suffolk , 1818 , d. Ipswich , 2 April 1908 ) was a Suffolk - born antiquary whose professional career was as a schoolmaster .
Photinos Panas ( 30 January 1832 - 5 January 1903 ) was an ophthalmologist born on the Greek island of Cefalonia .
Zhang Xingcheng ( 587 -- October 10 , 653 ) , courtesy name Deli , posthumously known as Duke Ding of Beiping , was a Chinese official who served as a chancellor during the reigns of the emperors Taizong and Gaozong in the Tang dynasty .
Sir Thomas Chicheley ( 25 March 1614 -- 1 February 1699 ) was a politician in England in the seventeenth century who fell from favour in the reign of James II . His name is sometimes spelt as Chichele .
Mangkunegara II was the king in Mangkunegaran who succeeded to the throne of his grandfather , Mangkunegara I. His reign lasted for approximately 40 years ( 1796 - -1835 ) .
Ken Whitfield ( 1930 -- 1995 ) was a footballer who played as a centre half in the Football League for Wolverhampton Wanderers , Manchester City , Brighton & Hove Albion and Queens Park Rangers .
Francis Bramston or Brampston ( died 1683 ) was an English judge and Baron of the Exchequer .
Robert Mewburn ( 1827 - -1891 ) was a convict transported to Western Australia , who later became one of the colony 's ex - convict school teachers .
Ernest Townsend ( 1 January 1880 -- 22 January 1944 ) was a portrait artist from Derby in England .
Sir Joseph Francis Olliffe , MA , MD , FRCP ( 1808 -- 14 March 1869 ) was an Irish - born British physician .
Herbert Dyer ( 1898 -- 1974 ) was a famous coppersmith who worked in Mousehole , near Penzance , during the 1920s , influenced by the Newlyn School of craftsmen near Penzance , Cornwall .
Edgar Wreford ( 29 December 1923 -- 20 January 2006 ) was a British stage and television actor .
Gaudenz Canova ( 31 December 1887 , Domat / Ems -- 21 January 1962 ) was a Swiss socialist from Graubünden ( Grisons ) .
Abel Hendy Jones Greenidge ( 22 December 1865 -- 11 March 1906 ) was a writer on ancient history and law .
Brigadier - General Sir Robert Barker , 1st Baronet , FRS ( 1732 -- 14 September 1789 ) was a British soldier .
Francis Smith , 2nd Viscount Carrington ( c. 1621 -- 7 April 1701 ) , was an English peer .
José Alberto dos Reis ( 1875 - 1955 ) was a Portuguese jurist and the leading Portuguese authority on legal procedure in the 20th century .
Revo ( né Revo Jõgisalu ; 9 July 1976 -- 30 August 2011 ) was an Estonian rapper .
Kathrine Sorley Walker ( 5 March 1920 -- 14 April 2015 ) was a British writer , editor and critic with a particular focus on ballet .
Jan Albert Hendrik Hugenholz ( 12 March 1825 -- 24 February 1874 ) was a Dutch colonial official , who served as Governor ad interim of the Dutch Gold Coast in 1871 .
Hélène Durand ( 9 August 1883 Watermael - Boitsfort - 4 August 1934 Ukkel ) was a Belgian botanical illustrator .
William Bagshaw or Bagshall ( 1628 - -1702 ) was an English presbyterian and nonconformist minister , known as the `` Apostle of the Peak '' .
C. S. Ranga Iyer ( 1895 - -1963 ) was an Indian journalist , politician , Indian independence activist and social reformer .
Koca Sinan Pasha ( Albanian : Sinan Pasha Topojani ; 1506 -- 3 April 1596 ) was an Ottoman grand vizier , Ottoman military figure , and statesman .
Margaret Tisdall ( 8 January 1906 -- 30 April 1979 ) , better known by her stage name Peggy Dell , was an Irish singer and pianist who became a popular music hall entertainer .

Major Johann Hinkel ( 1890- 28 March 1943 ) was the German representative in Sark from 1942 .
David Mitrany ( 1888 - -1975 ) was a Romanian - born , naturalized British scholar , historian and political theorist .
Sadie Corré ( born 31 May 1918 -- 26 August 2009 ) was an English actress , tap dancer , comic performer and leading pantomime cat .

Hovenden Hely ( 1823 -- 8 October 1872 ) was an Australian explorer and politician .
Hugh Hume - Campbell , 3rd Earl of Marchmont PC FRS ( 15 February 1708 -- 10 January 1794 ) , styled Lord Polwarth between 1724 and 1740 , was a Scottish politician .
Lev Nikolaevich Gassovsky ( 1894 -- 1989 ) was a Russian professor ( 1935 ) , Candidate of Science ( 1938 ) , and Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences ( 1940 ) .
William Scrope ( 1772 - -1852 ) was an English sportsman and amateur artist , known as a writer on sports .
Mary Ellen Chase ( 24 February 1887 -- 28 July 1973 ) was an American educator , teacher , scholar , and author .
Tadé was the name used by Tadeusz Fuss - Kaden ( 15 September 1914 -- 16 November 1985 ) to sign his paintings as Tadé or Fuss or Kaden .
Mohammed al - Makki al - Nasiri ( 1906 - -1994 ) was a religious scholar and nationalist politician from Morocco , active in the 1930s and 1940s .
Wendy Law Suart ( 26 August 1926 -- 16 July 2012 ) was an Australian traveller and writer .
Giovanni Francesco Bagnoli ( 1678 - -1713 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , who painted still - life paintings .
Flora Garry ( 30 September 1900 - 16 June 2000 ) was a Scottish poet who mostly wrote in the Scots dialect of Aberdeenshire .
William Ambrose Shedd ( 1865 - -1918 ) was a US Presbyterian missionary who served in Persia and tried to protect the Assyrian people from the genocide .
Edward Sullivan Murphy PC(NI ) KC ( 3 February 1880 -- 3 December 1945 ) was an Irish barrister , judge and politician .
Sir Thomas Rich , 1st Baronet ( c.1601 -- 15 October 1667 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in House of Commons in 1660 .
Fred R. Moore ( 16 June 1857 -- 1 March 1943 ) was an editor and publisher who became closely associated with Booker T. Washington until 1915 when Washington died .
Campbell Copelin ( died 1988 ) was an English actor , who moved to Australia in the 1920s and worked extensively in film , theatre , radio and television .
Edward John White ( 8 December 1831 -- 2 August 1913 ) was an English - born meteorologist and astronomer , president of the Royal Society of Victoria in 1902 .
Than Tun ( Burmese : သန်းထွန်း , pronounced : ( θáɴ tʰʊ́ɴ ) ; 6 April 1923 -- 30 November 2005 ) was an influential Burmese historian as well as an outspoken critic of the military junta of Burma .
Lorenz Hengler ( 3 February 1806 -- 1858 ) was a Catholic priest who is often credited as the inventor of the horizontal pendulum .
Edward Hugo Oehler known as Hugo Oehler ( 1903 - 1983 ) was an American communist .
Alfred Strombergs ( Latvian : Alfrēds Štrombergs ; 19 February 1922 , Liepāja , Latvia - 22 February 2006 , Toronto ) was a Canadian conductor , music educator , and pianist of Latvian birth .
Joseph Sibbel ( b. Dulmen , 7 June 1850 ; d. in New York , 10 July 1907 ) was a German - born sculptor .
Paris Nesbit , QC ( 8 August 1852 -- 31 March 1927 ) , born Edward Pariss Nesbit , was an Australian lawyer .
Eamonn O'Neill ( 1882 -- 3 November 1954 ) was an Irish businessman , a Cumann na nGaedheal and later Fine Gael politician .
Robert Thomas Cross ( born 15 May 1850 in Worstead , d. 1923 ) was a British astrologer .
Murchadh mac Maenach ( died 891 ) was King of Maigh Seóla .
James Unaipon ( born James Ngunaitponi ) ( c. 1835 - 1907 ) was an Australian Indigenous preacher of the Warrawaldie ( also spelt Waruwaldi ) Lakalinyeri of the Ngarrindjeri .
Olav Braarud ( 2 February 1885 -- 4 April 1969 ) was a Norwegian director and engineer .
Sir Henry Pickering , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1656 -- 7 May 1705 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1685 to 1689 , and later settled in Barbados , where he played a prominent part in the island 's government .
Niccolò Acciaioli or Acciaiuoli ( 1310 -- 8 November 1365 ) was an Italian noble , a member of the Florentine banking family of the Acciaioli .
Vincent Dillon was an Irish Dominican martyr , who died 1651 .
Sui Gu ( died 199 ) , courtesy name Baitu ( 白兔 ) , was a vassal serving under the warlord Zhang Yang in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Henry Martyn Taylor , FRS , FRAS ( 6 June 1842 , Bristol -- 16 October 1927 , Cambridge ) , was an English mathematician and barrister .
John Boyle , 3rd Earl of Glasgow ( 4 November 1714 -- 7 March 1775 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Sir Edward George Warris Hulton ( 29 November 1906 -- 8 October 1988 ) was a British magazine publisher and writer .
Captain Bernard Acworth DSO ( 3 February 1885 -- 16 February 1963 ) was an English submariner , writer , evangelical Christian and creationist .
William of Durham ( died 1249 ) is said to have founded University College , Oxford , England .
Jenet Sarsfield , Baroness Dunsany ( c. 1528 - -1598 ) was an Anglo - Irish noblewoman , memorable for having married six husbands .
Major Robert Henry Cain VC TD ( 2 January 1909 -- 2 May 1974 ) was a Manx recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Margaretta Scott ( 13 February 1912 -- 15 April 2005 ) was an English stage , screen and television actress whose career spanned over seventy years .
Archibald Blair ( born 1752 -- died 1815 ) was a naval surveyor and Lieutenant in the Bombay Marine .
John Stewart Bell FRS ( 28 June 1928 -- 1 October 1990 ) was a Northern Irish physicist , and the originator of Bell 's theorem , an important theorem in quantum physics regarding hidden variable theories .
Sir John Jamison ( 1776 -- 29 June 1844 ) was an Australian physician , pastoralist , banker , politician , constitutional reformer and public figure .
Sir William Wedderburn , 4th Baronet , JP DL ( 25 March 1838 -- 25 January 1918 ) was a Scottish civil servant in India and a politician .
Miodrag Rajičić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Миодраг Рајичић ; February 14 , 1898 - -November 23 , 1977 ) was a Yugoslav Serbian historian .
Aagot Didriksen ( 3 July 1874 -- 19 March 1968 ) was a Norwegian theatre actress and film actress of the 1930s .
Frederick Grinnell ( 1836 - -1905 ) was a pioneer in fire safety and was the creator of the first practical automatic fire sprinkler .
F. L. Anthing ( 1820 - -1883 ) was one of the Dutch evangelists evangelizing in Java in the 19th century .
Ana María Romero de Campero ( 29 June 1941 -- 26 October 2010 ) was a Bolivian journalist , writer , activist and influential public figure in her country .
Izi Dorot ( 1916 - -1980 ) , born Isidore Roth , was an Israeli military person , and director of the Shabak between 1952 and 1953 .
James Laidlaw Maxwell , Junior ( Chinese : 馬雅各二世 ; 1876 -- 12 August 1951 ) was a pioneering modern English Presbyterian medical missionary to Formosa ( Taiwan ) and China .
Richard John Russell ( 12 April 1872 -- 5 February 1943 ) was a British dental surgeon and Liberal later Liberal National politician .
José António Freire Sobral ( Sobral de Monte Agraço , São Quintino , 10 June 1840 -- Lisbon , 19 April 1905 ) , was a rich farmer and a large exporter of coffee , cocoa and woods who made his fortune in São Tomé Island in Portuguese São Tomé and Príncipe .
Thomas Bigelow Craig ( 1849 - -1924 ) was an American landscape painter from Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Xue Rengao ( 薛仁杲 ) ( died 618 ) , also known as Xue Renguo ( 薛仁果 ) , was an emperor of the short - lived state of Qin , established by his father Xue Ju ( Emperor Wu ) at the end of the Chinese dynasty Sui Dynasty .
Sir Dugald Baird ( 1899 -- 1986 ) was a Scottish medical doctor .
Prince Abyssinia Akweke Nwafor Orizu ( 1915 - -1999 ) .

Charles Curwen Walker ( 1856 - -1940 ) was a Christadelphian writer and editor of The Christadelphian Magazine from 1898 to 1937 .

Allen Batsford ( 9 April 1932 -- 28 December 2009 ) was a former football manager .

Thomas Potts James ( 1803 - -1882 ) was an American botanist and bryologist .

Ralph Stein ( 1909 - -1994 ) was a writer , cartoonist and illustrator .
The Hon . George Wentworth - FitzWilliam ( 3 May 1817 - 4 March 1874 ) , was a British politician .
Robert Fidgeon ( 15 October 1941 -- 2 September 2007 ) was a television writer and critic for the Melbourne based newspaper , the Herald Sun . He wrote a regular column in the section , The Guide .
Vittore Trincavelli ( also Vettore or Victor Trincavelli ; 1496 - -1568 ) was an eminent Italian physician , but is most famous as the editor of some of the first editions of the Greek classics .
Edouard Lippé ( May 24 , 1884 in Pennsylvania -- 1956 ) also frequently spelt Eduardo Lippe .
Ernest Greenhill , 1st Baron Greenhill ( 23 April 1887 -- 18 February 1967 ) , was a Scottish politician .
Henry Morgan Dockrell ( 1880 -- 26 October 1955 ) was an Irish Cumann na nGaedheal and Fine Gael politician who was elected to both Dáil Éireann and Seanad Éireann .
Samuel Prout ( /praʊt/ ; 17 September 1783 -- 10 February 1852 ) was one of the masters of British watercolour architectural painting .
Thomas Charles Bigge ( 1739 - -1794 ) was an English landowner and banker , High Sheriff of Northumberland for 1771 .
Prof . George J. Fritschel or Georg Johann Fritschel DD ( 1867 - -1941 ) was a German - Iowan Lutheran theologian who taught in Dubuque , Iowa .
Franz Reinzer ( 1661 - -1708 ) was an Austrian Jesuit professor of rhetoric , philosophy , and theology at Linz , Graz , Vienna , and Krems .
Tamás Bujkó ( 1 July 1959 -- 21 March 2008〈London 〉 ) was a Hungarian judo competitor who competed at World Championship and Olympic levels .
Hank Simms ( 1923 - 2013 ) was a voice actor and announcer , best known for narrating the opening credits of Quinn Martin TV shows , including The F.B.I. , Mannix , Barnaby Jones and The Streets of San Francisco .
Li Gengtao ( Chinese : 李耕涛 ) ( 1912 - 1974 ) was a People 's Republic of China politician .

Nathaniel B. Nichols ( 1914 - -1997 ) was an American control engineer who made significant contributions to the field of control theory .
Malkoč - beg ( died in 1565 ) was an Ottoman military officer , the first governor of the Vilayet Croats .

Muhammad Aytimur ( died August or September 1346 ) was the leader of the Sarbadars of Sabzewar from 1343 until his death .
Christy Brown ( 5 June 1932 -- 7 September 1981 ) was an Irish writer and painter who had cerebral palsy and was able to write or type only with the toes of one foot .
Patrick Charles Mitchell Fitzgerald ( 21 June 1896 -- 10 September 1984 ) , known as Paddy Fitzgerald , was a brewer from Rockhampton in Queensland , Australia .
Zain ul Abadeen Gillani ( 1885 - 1960 ) also Hazrat Syed Zain ul Abideen Gilani was a member of the Pakistan Movement .
Major - General Thomas Tait Pitman CB CMG JP ( born 22 December 1868 , died 8 March 1941 ) was a British cavalry officer , who was a general officer during the First World War

Richmond Mumford Pearson ( 1805 - 1878 ) was an American jurist who served as Chief Justice of the North Carolina Supreme Court from 1858 to 1878 .
Sir Derek Milman , 9th Baronet died on 12 May 1999 .
Semen Pavlovych Bublyk ( Ukrainian : Бублик Семен Павлович , 25 April 1909 - 1990 ) was a Soviet Ukrainian professor and scientist in the field of agricultural sciences of the Ukrainian Cossack origin .
John Rotheram ( 1725 - -1789 ) was an English cleric , known as a theological writer .
Danny Bennett ( born in Dublin , died 3 August 2008 ) is a former Irish football player .

Edoardo Navone ( Rome , 1844 - 1912 ) was an Italian painter of rural scenes , in a Realist style .

Sanghapala ( 506 - -518 CE ) was a famous Mon - Khmer monk who travelled to Southern and Northern Dynasties China .

Joachim Daniel Andreas Müller ( 7 September 1812 -- 18 September 1857 ) was a Swedish gardener and writer .

Marietta Brambilla ( 6 June 1807 -- 6 November 1875 ) was an Italian contralto who sang leading roles in the opera houses of Europe from 1827 until her retirement from the stage in 1848 .

Jan Borluut ( ca . 1250 - murdered , Ghent , before 1306 ) was a patrician from Ghent .

Rubi Noor was suffering from lung cancer and died at Kolkata on 10 July 2008 .
Arthur Sutton Valpy ( 28 March 1849 - 15 June 1909 ) was a canon of Winchester Cathedral .

Edward Maturin was born in Dublin , Ireland , on 18 June 1812 and died in New York city on 25 May 1881 .
Brian Anslay ( died 1536 ) was an administrator in the employ of Henry VII and Henry VIII , and is notable for translating Christine de Pizan 's The Book of the City of Ladies .

Thomas Lewis , Jr. ( January 26 , 1760 -- 1847 ) was an American politician from Rockingham County , Virginia .

Sten Bergman ( 20 October 1895 -- 19 February 1975 ) was a Swedish zoologist , who visited Korea , Kamchatka , Papua New Guinea , and many other places .
Friedrich Wilhelm von Bergholz ( 1699 - -1765 ) was a courtier from Holstein .
Ednyfed Fychan ( c. 1170 -- 1246 ) , full name Ednyfed Fychan ap Cynwrig , was a Welsh warrior who became seneschal to the Kingdom of Gwynedd in Northern Wales , serving Llywelyn the Great and his son Dafydd ap Llywelyn .
Jacobus Barnaart ( 6 October 1726 in Haarlem - 2 November 1780 in Haarlem ) was a Dutch merchant and one of the five first directors of the Teylers Stichting .
Isaac Van Duzen Reeve ( 29 July 1813 Butternuts , Otsego County , New York - 31 December 1890 New York City ) was a soldier in the United States Army during the 19th century .
Jamyang Khyentse Wangpo ( Tibetan : འཇམ་དབྱངས་མཁྱེན་བརྩེའི་དབང་པོ , 1820 - -1892 ) , also known by his tertön title , Pema Ösel Dongak Lingpa , was a renowned teacher , scholar and tertön of 19th century Tibet .
Anicet Wilfrid Pandou , commonly known as Willy Matsanga ( c. 1969 -- 9 October 2014 ) , was a Congolese politician .

Balgitzin ( died 704 ) , in the account of Theophanes the Confessor , was the Khazar tudun of Phanagoria during the sojourn of Justinian II in that town .

Katherine Ursula Towle ( March 26 , 1900 -- September 1957 ) better known by her pen name Ursula Parrott , was an American writer of romantic fiction stories and novels .

Gerry Fiennes ( full name : Gerard Francis Gisborne Twisleton - Wykeham - Fiennes OBE , MA ) ( 7 June 1906 -- 25 May 1985 ) was a British railway manager who rose through the ranks of the London and North Eastern Railway and later British Rail following graduation from Oxford University .
Dori of Yejju ( died 1831 ) was a Ras of Begemder and Inderase ( regent ) of the Emperor of Ethiopia .
Francis Price Blackwood ( 25 May 1809 - -22 March 1854 ) was a British naval officer who while posted at several different locations during his time in the Royal Navy , spent much of his time posted in colonial Australia and was an instrumental pioneer of regions near Australia 's east coast and nearby islands .
Konstanty Maria Sopoćko ( 1903 - 1992 ) was a Polish artist , specializing in woodcuting .

Postumus assumed his fifth consulship on 1 January 269 , but the army in Germania Superior raised a usurper in early 269 .
George Patrick Huntley ( 13 July 1868 -- 21 September 1927 ) , always billed as G P Huntley , was an Irish actor , known for comic performances in the theatre and the music halls .

Dervan or Derwan ( Latin : Dervanus ) was an early prince of the Sorbs ( fl . 631 - -636 ) .

Samuel Anderson Robb ( 1851 - -1928 ) was an American sculptor , best known for his carved wooden figures for tobacco shops and circus wagons .

Francis Kirwan ( 1589 - -1661 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic Bishop of Killala .
Sir Peter Maule ( died 1254 ) was the eldest son of Richard Maule of Fowlis .
Nils Georg Åberg ( 20 January 1893 -- 18 August 1946 ) was a Swedish athlete who won a silver and a bronze medal in the triple jump and long jump , respectively , at the 1912 Olympics .
James Duff Brown ( 1862 - -1914 ) was a British librarian , information theorist , music biographer and educationalist .
Merikare died in c. 2040 BCE , few months before the fall of Herakleopolis .
Roberto Salido Beltrán ( 1912 - -1988 ) was a noted Mexican military aviator .
Stanley Milburn ( 27 October 1926 -- 30 July 2010 ) was an English former football full back .
Sir John Batty Tuke ( 9 January 1835 -- 13 October 1913 ) was one of the most influential psychiatrists in Scotland in the late nineteenth century , and a Conservative Member of Parliament ( MP ) from 1900 to 1910 .
Theophilus Dorrington ( 1654 - -1715 ) was a Church of England clergyman .
Chormaqan ( also Chormagan or Chormaqan Noyan ) ( died c. 1241 ) was one of the most famous generals of the Mongol Empire under Genghis Khan and Ögedei Khan .
Antonis Diamantidis ( Greek : Αντώνης Διαμαντίδης)(1892 , Istanbul-1945 , Athens ) was born in 1892 in the Arnavutköy suburb of Istanbul .

Robert Wilson Andrews ( 1837 - -1922 ) was a Hawaii - born artist and engineer .
William Ranwell ( 26 July 1797 - 5 October 1861 ) was a notable English landscape artist during the early 19th century .
Hatidža Hadžiosmanović ( 19 August 1938 -- 23 December 2015 ) was a President of the Constitutional Court of Bosnia and Herzegovina .
Adolfo Bellocq ( 1899 - -1972 ) was an influential Argentine artist known for his lithographs .

Just Betzer ( 11 June 1944 -- 6 November 2003 ) , was a Danish Oscar winning film producer , born in Åbyhøj , Denmark .
Gustaaf Hulstaert ( 1900 - -1990 ) was a Belgian entomologist mainly interested in Lepidoptera .
Samaresh Basu ( 11 December 1924 -- 12 March 1988 ) was a Bengali writer born on 11 December 1924 ( 1331 in the Bengali calendar ) and spent his early childhood in Dhaka , Bikrampur in present day Bangladesh .
Sigmund Zois Freiherr von Edelstein , usually referred as Sigmund Zois ( Slovene : Žiga Zois , archaic Cojs or Cojz ; pronunciation ) ( 23 November 1747 -- 10 November 1819 ) was a Carniolan nobleman , natural scientist and patron of the arts .
Myles William Patrick O'Reilly ( Born in Balbriggan , Ireland in 1825 ; died in Dublin , Ireland in 1880 ) was a Catholic soldier and publicist .

Roger François Lotte ( b. 1922 - d. 1989 ) was French archetier and bow maker , son of François Lotte and Marguerite Ouchard .
Sir Thomas Burnett , 1st Baronet of Leys ( died 27 June 1653 ) was a feudal baron and leading Covenanter who had represented Kincardineshire in the Scottish Parliament in 1621 .

Wilf Paish MBE ( Wilfred Henry Charles Paish , 29 July 1932 -- 29 January 2010 ) was a British athletics coach .
Jeanette Dyrkjær ( 26 November 1963 -- 29 July 2011 ) was a Danish nude model and adult actress .
Antonio Zoppi ( 1860 - 1926 ) was an Italian painter , mostly of genre and costume scenes , as well as landscapes ..
Thomas Cranley DD ( aka Craule ; c.1337 - -1417 ) was a leading statesman , judge and cleric in early fifteenth - century Ireland , who held the offices of Chancellor of Oxford University , Archbishop of Dublin and Lord Chancellor of Ireland .
Józef Zaremba ( c.1731 - 1774 ) was a Polish noble ( of the Zaremba coat of arms ) and general .
Frederick Charles Davies ( 12 April 1884 -- 23 July 1932 ) was a world - class Welsh athlete who was better known to the sporting world as Tenby Davies , and who became the half - mile world professional champion in 1909 after an enthralling race against Irishman Beauchamp Day .
Sheikh Tahir Jalaluddin ( born 8 December 1869 in Ampek Angkek , Agam , West Sumatra -- died 1956 ) was a famous Muslim ulama in Southeast Asia .
Louis Gayant ( died 1673 ) was a French surgeon and anatomist .
Colonel Sir Thales Pease , KCB ( 1835 - 26 February 1919 ) was a British Army and Navy ordnance officer .
Beverley Sitgreaves ( 1863 - -1943 ) was an American stage actress , journalist and philanthropist whose theatre career spanned some 50 years .
Otto Langmann ( 1898 - 1956 ) was a German pastor and diplomat .
Sayyid Murtada Sharif ' Askari ( Persian : سید مرتضی شریف عسکری‎ ; 4 May 1914 -- 16 September 2007 ) , known as Allamah ' Askari , was a Shiite scholar and a neo - religious thinker .
Luís Antônio de Carvalho Ferraz ( 21 February 1940 -- 11 August 1982 ) was a Brazilian Navy officer , engineer , hydrographer , oceanographer , and Brazilian pioneer in Antarctica .
Maredudd ab Owain ( died c. 999 ) was a 10th - century king in Wales of the High Middle Ages .
Bettie Cilliers - Barnard ( 18 November 1914 -- 15 September 2010 ) was a South African abstract artist , generally known for her large canvases of birds in flight .
Brigadier Harold Burfield Taylor MC and bar ( 10 August 1890 -- 15 March 1966 ) was an analytical chemist ( B.Sc . , D.Sc . )
Giles Hussey ( 1710 - -1788 ) was a painter from Dorset , England .
Harry Hosier ( c. 1750 - -May 1806 ) , better known during his life as `` Black Harry '' , was a black Methodist preacher during the Second Great Awakening in the early United States .
William of Salisbury , 2nd Earl of Salisbury ( died 1196 ) was an Anglo - Norman peer .
Bourn Russell ( 1 December 1794 -- 4 July 1880 ) was an Australian politician and businessman .
Sir William Jenner , 1st Baronet , QHP , FRCP , FRS ( 30 January 1815 -- 11 December 1898 ) was a significant English physician primarily known for having discovered the distinction between typhus and typhoid .
William John Biffen , Baron Biffen , PC , DL ( 3 November 1930 -- 14 August 2007 ) was a Conservative member of the House of Lords , who previously spent 36 years in the House of Commons .
Song Wenfei ( 30 May 1985 -- 3 March 2013 ) , also known as `` Song Wenting '' or `` Vionn Song '' , was a Chinese actress .
Antonio Amico was a Roman Catholic Canon of Palermo , and ecclesiastical historian of Syracuse and Messina , ( died 1641 ) .
John Schenck ( sometimes written Schanck ) ( 1750 - -1823 ) was a captain in the New Jersey Militia during the American Revolutionary War .
Elisabeth of Culemborg ( 30 March 1475 , the former slot of Hoogstraten - 9 December 1555 , Culemborg ) , nicknamed ' Lady Elizabeth ( ' Vrouwe Elisabeth ' ) was the last lord or lady of the fiefdom of Culemborg ( promoted to a county by Charles V , Holy Roman Emperor shortly before her death ) .
Maurice Leyland ( 20 July 1900 -- 1 January 1967 ) was an English cricketer who played 41 Test matches between 1928 and 1938 .
Shyamal Sinha , also known as Shyamlal Sinha , ( 10 July 1930 -- 7 June 1963 ) was an Indian first - class cricketer and cricket coach .
Mathias Rukavina von Boynograd ( Croatian : Matija Rukavina Bojnogradski ) , also Mathias Rukawina , Mathias Ruccavina , Mate Rukavina , ( 1737 - 3 May 1817 ) was a Croatian general in the Habsburg Monarchy imperial army service .
John Boda ( 2 August 1922 , in Boyceville , Wisconsin -- 14 April 2002 , in Ocala , Florida ) was a composer and music professor who taught music theory , composition and piano at Florida State University in Tallahassee , Florida between 1947 and 2001 .
Mohammed Akensus ( also Akensous ) or Abu Abdallah Mohammed ben Ahmad Akensus al - Marrakushi ( 1797 , ( Sous ) - 1877 ) was a well - known Moroccan historian and a minister under moulay Sulaiman and moulay Abderrahmane .
Swami Pranavananda ( Bengali : স্বামী প্রণবানন্দ ) also known as Yugacharya Srimat Swami Pranavananda Ji Maharaj , ( 29 January 1896 -- 8 February 1941 ) was the founder of the organization known as the Bharat Sevashram Sangha .
Visarion Pavlović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Висарион Павловић ; 1670-Novi Sad , 18 October 1756 ) was a scholar , educator and the Serbian Orthodox bishop of the Eparchy of Bačka ( 1731 - -1756 ) .
Yelü Xiuge ( 耶律休哥 ) ( died 998 ) was an important Khitan general and politician in ancient China 's Liao Dynasty .
Melaghlin Ua Madadhan ( died 1188 ) was King of Síol Anmchadha .
Colum Corless ( 12 May 1922 -- 1 February 2015 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a right corner - back for the Galway senior team .
John Teele Pratt ( December 25 , 1873 -- June 17 , 1927 ) was an American corporate attorney , philanthropist , music impresario , and financier .
Giovanni Battista Vernici ( died 1617 ) was an Italian painter .
His Honour Alistair Watson Bell ( 31 March 1930 -- 2 August 2012 ) , was a British Circuit judge and Liberal Party politician .
John Gretton , 1st Baron Gretton ( 1 September 1867 - -2 June 1947 ) , CBE ( 1919 ) , VD , TD , PC ( 1926 ) , JP , DL Leics , Derbys , ( 1 September 1867 -- 2 June 1947 ) , was a British businessman and Conservative politician .
Sancho Ramírez ( c. 1042 -- 4 June 1094 ) was King of Aragon ( 1063 - -1094 , not formally until 1076 ) and King of Navarre ( from 1076 , as Sancho V ) .
Tobias Cohn or Tobias Kohn ( in Hebrew , Toviyyah ben Moshe ha - Kohen ; in Polish , Tobiasz Kohn ) ( also referred to as Toviyah Kats ) ( 1652 - 1729 ) was a Polish - Jewish physician of the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries .
Anfin Øen ( 2 August 1868 -- 14 February 1928 ) was a Norwegian bailiff and politician for the Liberal and Agrarian parties .
Frank Morton McMurry ( 1862 - -1936 ) was an American educator and a brother of Charles Alexander McMurry .
Francesco de Layolle ( also spelled dell'Aiolle , dell'Aiuola , dell'Ajolle , dell'Aiolli ) , ( March 4 , 1492 -- c. 1540 ) was an Italian composer and organist of the Renaissance .
Emmanouil Miaoulis ( Greek : Εμμανουήλ Μιαούλης , 1812 - 1871 ) was a Greek naval officer .
Reginald Ben Davis ( 1907 - -1998 ) was a British wildlife artist who contributed many painted pages to Look and Learn and Treasure magazines .
Henning Arnisaeus ( Arniseus ) ( 1570 - -1636 ) was a German physician and moral philosopher .
Charles Carroll II ( 1702 -- 1782 ) known as Charles Carroll of Annapolis to distinguish him from his similarly named relatives , was a wealthy Maryland planter and lawyer .
Richard Armstedt ( 10 November 1851 -- 14 April 1931 ) was a German philologist , educator , and historian .
Joseph Cupitt ( 25 September 1867 -- 6 May 1932 ) was an English cricketer who played first class cricket for Derbyshire in 1905 .
Sister M. Madeleva Wolff , C.S.C. , ( May 24 , 1887 -- July 25 , 1964 ) , the `` lady abbess of nun poets '' , was the third President of Saint Mary 's College in Notre Dame , Indiana .
Tulasa Thapa ( 1970 - -1995 ) was a Nepali girl who was kidnapped from her home village of Thankot near Kathmandu in 1982 at the age of 12 , smuggled into Mumbai via the border town of Birganj in Parsa District , and sold into prostitution .
Sir Robert Henry Woods ( 1865 -- 8 September 1938 ) was an Irish Independent Unionist Member of Parliament ( MP ) in the United Kingdom Parliament .
Jiang Zhuyun ( Chinese : 江竹筠 ; 20 August 1920－14 November 1949 ) was a Chinese revolutionary martyr .
Octavius Vaughan Morgan ( 1837 -- 26 February 1896 ) was a Welsh - born Liberal Party politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1892 .
Li Chang ( 12 December 1914 -- 3 September 2010 ) was an official of the People 's Republic of China .
Paraluman died of cardiac arrest on 27 April 2009 at her home in Parañaque City .
Helen M. Knowlton ( 1832 - 1918 ) was an American artist , art instructor and author .
Richard Prideaux ( 1606 -- 1667 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1640 .
Clifton Wheeler ( 1883 -- 1953 ) was an American Impressionist artist from Hadley , IN .
Hector Og Maclean , or Eachann Óg Maclean in Scottish Gaelic , or Hector Maclean the Younger ( c. 1540 - 1573 ) was the 13th Chief of Clan MacLean .
Sofie Aubert Lindbæk ( 19 May 1875 -- 29 October 1953 ) was a Norwegian author , teacher and film critic .
Abdullah Saleh Al Mulla ( died 1955 ) was Secretary of State in Kuwait under the Emirs Sheikh Ahmad Al - Jaber Al - Sabah and Sheikh Abdullah III Al - Salim Al - Sabah .
Peter Jepson - Young , M.D. ( 1957 - -1992 ) , better known as simply Dr. Peter , was a medical doctor in Vancouver , British Columbia , Canada who promoted AIDS and HIV awareness and education in the early 1990s through his regular segment on CBC Television news broadcasts called The Dr. Peter Diaries .
Hamble James Leacock ( ` 1795 - 1856 ) was an African missionary .
Ulisse Cambi ( 22 September 1807 -- 7 April 1895 ) was an Italian sculptor active in Tuscany during the 19th century .
Philippe - Louis van de Werve , Baron of Schilde ( 1784 -- 1834 ) formed part of a very old , important and noble family of Antwerp .
Shin Sawbu ( Burmese : ရှင်စောပု , pronounced : ( shɪ̀ɴ sɔ́ pṵ ) ; Mon : သေဝ်စါဝ်ပေါအ် ; 1394 - -1471 ) was the 15th monarch of the Hanthawaddy Kingdom in Burma from 1454 to 1471 .
Alexandru Callimachi ( 1737 -- 12 December 1821 ) was Prince of Moldavia during the period of 6 May 1795 through 18 March 1799 .
Arthur Furguson ( 1883 - -1938 ) was ( or may have been ) a Scottish con artist who allegedly became known for `` selling '' English national monuments and other government property to visiting American tourists during the 1920s .
Dom Didier de La Cour de La Vallée ( 1550 -- 1623 ) was a Benedictine monk , responsible for the foundation of the reforming Congregation of St. Vanne in 1604 .
Sir James Pemberton ( 1550 -- 8 September 1613 ) was an English goldsmith who was Lord Mayor of London in 1611 .
William Morton Meredith ( 1835 - -1917 ) was an official in the United States Department of the Treasury who was Director of the Bureau of Engraving and Printing from 1889 to 1893 and from 1900 to 1906 .
Silseong of Silla ( died 417 ) ( r. 402 - -417 ) , whose name is also given as Silju or Silgeum , was the 18th ruler of the Korean kingdom of Silla .
Edmond I de Bermingham ( died 1612 ) was an Anglo - Irish lord .
Siegfried Schoenbohm ( born 1938 in South Dakota , USA - died spring 2006 ) was an opera stage director .
Miles Clark ( 1960 - -1993 ) was a sailor , journalist and writer from Northern Ireland .
Louis Beethoven Prout ( 1864 - -1943 ) was an English entomologist and musicologist .
Robert of Winchester ( died 1180 ) was abbot of Glastonbury .
Cornelis van Tienhoven ( ca . 1601 Utrecht- November 1656 ? , Manhattan ? ) was secretary of the New Netherlands from 1638 to 1656 and as such one of the most influential people in New Amsterdam .
Heinz Heinrich Nordhoff ( 6 January 1899 -- 12 April 1968 ) was a German engineer famous for his leadership of the Volkswagen company as it was rebuilt after World War II .
Jakub Bart - Ćišinski ( 20 August 1856 in Kuckau -- 16 October 1909 in Panschwitz ) , also known as Łužičan , Jakub Bart Kukowski , was Sorbian poet , writer and playwright , translator of Czech , Polish , Italian and German literature .
Radha Mohan Lal , also known as Bhai Sahib ( October 1900 - 21 July 1966 , Kanpur , India ) , was a Naqshbandi Sufi master .
William Reid Owen ( 25 November 1864 -- 22 March 1949 ) was the 20th mayor of Vancouver , British Columbia in 1924 .
Deric Bolton ( 1908 - 1993 ) was a Scottish research chemist and poet born in Paisley .
Charles L. Carson ( b. Nov. 3 , 1847 - d. Dec. 18 , 1891 ) , was an architect born in Baltimore , the oldest son of Daniel Carson , a builder , and one of the founders of the Baltimore chapter of AIA .
Kurt Küttner ( 1907 -- 1964 ) was an SS - Oberscharführer ( Staff Sergeant ) who served at Treblinka extermination camp , arrested and charged with war crimes at the Treblinka trials twenty years after the war ended .
Sir John Hubert Plunkett Murray , usually known as Sir Hubert Murray ( 29 December 1861 -- 27 February 1940 ) , was a judge and Lieutenant - Governor of Papua from 1908 until his death at Samarai .
Elizabeth Egerton ( née Cavendish ) , countess of Bridgewater ( 1626 -- 14 July 1663 ) , was an English writer from the Egerton family .
William Pemble ( Pember ) ( 1591 or 1592 - -1623 ) was an English theologian and author .
Manfred Reiss ( 1922 - -1987 ) was born in Leipzig , Germany , the son of Menahem Reiss & Golda Reiss , who were Jews of Polish descent .
Francis Wichmans ( name in religion Augustine ) ( born at Antwerp , 1596 ; died 1661 ) was a Belgian Norbertine abbot .
Kotayya Pratyagatma ( born Kolli Kotayya Pratyagatma ) , also known as K. P. Atma ( b : 31 October 1925 - d : 8 June 2001 ) was an Indian film journalist , director and producer known for his works in Bollywood and Telugu cinema .
Thomas Cromwell , 3rd Earl of Ardglass ( 29 November 1653 -- 11 April 1682 ) , was an English nobleman , the only son of Wingfield Cromwell , 2nd Earl of Ardglass of Ilam , Staffordshire and Mary Russell .
Anders Hald ( 3 July 1913 -- 11 November 2007 ) was a Danish statistician who made contributions to the history of statistics .
Reinis Zālītis ( 19 September 1943 - 15 October 2005 ) was a Latvian football defender , famous for playing for Daugava Rīga .
John Rede or Reade ( before 1509 - -1557 ) was an English politician and member of the court staff .
Caroline McNairn ( 16 May 1955 - -29 September 2010 ) was a Scottish figurative painter .
Zain Khan Koka ( died 1601 ) was a leading official in the Mugal Empire under Akbar , including serving for a time as governor of Kabul .
Adolph I , Count of Nassau - Wiesbaden - Idstein ( 1307 -- 17 January 1370 ) was a son of Count Gerlach I and Agnes of Hesse .
Saint Fulgentius of Cartagena ( Spanish : San Fulgencio de Cartagena ) , born in Cartagena in the 6th century and died in 630 , was Bishop of Ecija ( Astigi ) , in Hispania ( the Iberian Peninsula , comprising modern Spain and Portugal ) .
Ludwig von Löfftz ( 21 June 1845 -- 3 December 1910 ) was a German genre and landscape painter .
Samuel Heinrich Schwabe ( 25 October 1789 -- 11 April 1875 ) a German astronomer remembered for his work on sunspots .
William Grosvenor , 3rd Duke of Westminster ( 23 December 1894 -- 22 February 1963 ) was the son of Lord Henry Grosvenor and a grandson of Hugh Grosvenor , 1st Duke of Westminster .
Rabbi Sholom Mordechai Schwadron ( 1835 - -1911 ) ( Hebrew : שלום בן משה הכהן שוודרן ) was known by his acronym Maharsham .
George Pilcher ( 1801 - -1855 ) was an English aural surgeon and medical reformer .
Matilda Anne Mackarness ( née Planché ; 23 November 1826 -- 6 May 1881 ) was an English novelist of the 19th century , primarily writing children 's literature .
Richard Chichester Mason ( 7 May 1793 - -22 July 1869 ) was a prominent physician practicing in Alexandria , Virginia .
Graham Higman FRS ( 19 January 1917 -- 8 April 2008 ) was a leading British mathematician .
Niño Ricardo ( 11 July 1904 -- 14 April 1972 ) , born as Manuel Serrapí , was a Flamenco composer , considered by some sources as the most accomplished flamenco player of his day .
Johannes de Villiers Graaff ( also known as Jan de Van Graaff or Jannie Graaff ) ( 19 February 1928 -- 6 January 2015 ) was a neoclassical South African welfare economist .
Thomas Beattie Roberton ( 1879 - 1936 ) was a Scottish - born Canadian journalist .
Meredith Gwynne Evans , FRS ( 2 December 1904 -- 25 December 1952 ) was a British physical chemist , who made important theoretical contributions in the study of chemical reaction rates and reaction mechanisms .
Sven Ingvar Svennilson ( 14 March 1908 -- 1972 ) was a Swedish economist that became known for his theories in planned economics .
Baynard Rush Hall ( 1793 - 1863 ) was an American academic and Christian minister .
Sir Thomas Fitz - Christopher Plunket ( c.1407 - 1471 ) was a leading Irish lawyer and judge of the fifteenth century who held office as Lord Chief Justice of Ireland .
Sir Henry Spelman ( born Congham , Norfolk c.1562 and died 1641 ) was an English antiquary , noted for his detailed collections of medieval records , in particular of church councils .
Jack van Geloven ( 4 January 1934 -- 21 August 2003 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played three matches for Yorkshire in 1955 , and then joined Leicestershire on special registration for the 1956 season .
Huang Zicheng ( Chinese : 黃子澄 ) ( 1350 - 1402 ) was a Ming dynasty imperial scholar and overseer of rituals .
Ben Taub ( 1889 - -1982 ) was a philanthropist and medical benefactor in Houston , Texas .
Ramnath Biswas ( Bengali : রামনাথ বিশ্বাস ) ( 13 January 1894 - 1 November 1955 ) was an Indian revolutionary , soldier , globetrotter and travelogue writer .
Zhuang Xueben ( Chinese : 庄学本 ; 1909 - -1984 ) was one of China 's first ethnographic photographers .
Sir Capel Luckyn , 2nd Baronet ( 8 May 1622 -- 23 January 1680 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1647 and 1679 .
Maharani Bharani Thirunal Lakshmi Bayi CI ( 1848 - -1901 ) was the Senior Rani of Travancore from 1857 till her death in 1901 .
Leopold Lojka ( also spelt Leopold Loyka ) ( 17 September 1886 -- 18 July 1926 ) was the chauffeur of the car carrying Austro - Hungarian Archduke Franz Ferdinand at the point of Ferdinand 's assassination in Sarajevo in 1914 .
Flavius Gaudentius ( or simply Gaudentius ) ( died 425 AD ) was the father of the Roman magister militum Flavius Aetius and married to an Italian noblewoman .
Humphrey Brooke ( 1617 - -1693 ) was an English physician and political radical .
Saint William of Perth ( died c. 1201 ) , also known as Saint William of Rochester was a Scottish saint who was martyred in England .
Tony Thornton ( November 8 , 1959 -- September 10 , 2009 , in Camden , New Jersey ) was an American professional boxer who died of a motorcycle accident on 10 September 2009 .
Kemper Harreld ( January 31 , 1885 - -1971 ) , born William Kemper Harreld in Muncie , Indiana , was a renowned African - American concert violinist .
Isaac Gulliver ( 1745 - 1822 ) was an English smuggler based on the South Coast .
Richard Elford ( 1677?--1714 ) was an English singer , the leading figure in his field in Queen Anne 's London .
Charles Ancliffe ( 1880 - -1952 ) was an Irish born composer of light music , chiefly remembered for his marches and waltzes .
Giovan Francesco Rustici , or Giovanni Francesco Rustici , ( 1475 - -1554 ) was an Italian Renaissance painter and sculptor .
Jean - Pierre Wimille ( 26 February 1908 -- 28 January 1949 ) was a Grand Prix motor racing driver and a member of the French Resistance during World War II .
David Hildyard ( May 1916 -- 19 February 2008 ) was an English sound engineer .
Marie Nizet ( 19 January 1859 - -15 March 1922 ) , married name Marie Mercier , was a Belgian writer .
Isaac Baker Brown ( 1811 -- 3 February 1873 ) was a prominent 19th - century English gynaecologist and obstetrical surgeon .
János Grünn ( 3 June 1864 , Banská Bystrica - 5 March 1932 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Finance in 1919 .
Thomas Bradbury ( 1677 - -1759 ) , was an English congregational minister .
Oliver Dennett Grover ( 1861 Earlville , Illinois - 1927 Chicago ) , was an American landscape and mural painter , the son of lawyer Alonzo Jackson Grover .
Richard Du Cane , M.P. ( 13 October 1681 -- 3 October 1744 ) was the Member of Parliament for Colchester ( Essex ) from 1715 to 1722 .
Neil Christian , born Christopher Tidmarsh ( 14 February 1943 -- 4 January 2010 ) had a solo hit single in 1966 , when `` That 's Nice '' ( written by Miki Dallon ) , reached Number 16 in the UK Singles Chart .
Yu Zhishan ( Chinese : 于 芷山 ; pinyin : Yú Zhǐshān ; Hepburn : U Shizan ; 1882 -- May 1951 ) , was a military officer under the Beiyang Government and the Fengtian clique , subsequently becoming a cabinet minister in the Empire of Manchukuo .
Jože Pučnik ( 9 March 1932 -- 11 January 2003 ) was a Slovenian public intellectual , sociologist and politician .
Kieran Nugent ( 1958 - 4 May 2000 ) was a volunteer in the Provisional Irish Republican Army and best known for being the first IRA ' blanket man ' in the H - Blocks .
Jitka Snížková born Skrhova ( 1924 - -1989 ) was a Czech composer , music educator and musicologist .
JoAnn Wilson ( 21 August 1939 -- 21 January 1983 ) was the wife of Canadian politician Colin Thatcher who was convicted of her murder after the end of their marriage .
Sir Charles Frederic Belcher OBE ( 1876 - -1970 ) was an Australian lawyer , author , British colonial jurist and amateur ornithologist .
Rhys ap Gruffydd or ap Gruffudd ( often anglicised to `` Griffith '' ) ( 1132 -- 28 April 1197 ) was the ruler of the kingdom of Deheubarth in south Wales from 1155 to 1197 .
Teresa Maria Manetti ( 3 March 1846 -- 23 April 1910 ) , born Teresa Adelaide Cesina Manetti , was an Italian Roman Catholic nun and was the founder of the Carmelite Sisters of Saint Teresa .
Krzysztof Zborowski ( died 1593 ) was a Polish Royal Deputy Cup - bearer of the Crown ( Polish : podczaszy koronny ; 1574 - -1576 ) , supporter of the Habsburgs .
Emanuele d'Astorga ( 11 December 1681 -- 21 August 1736 , by some reports ) was an Italian composer known mainly for his Stabat Mater .
Albert Hamilton Stokesbury ( 26 June 1897 -- 3 March 1968 ) was an Australian rules footballer .
Tutta Rolf ( born Solveig Jenny Berntzen ; 7 October 1907 -- 26 October 1994 ) was a Norwegian - Swedish film and theatre actress and singer .
Immanuel Nobel the Younger ( /noʊˈbɛl/ ; Swedish : ( nʊˈbɛl ) ; 24 March 1801 -- 3 September 1872 ) was a Swedish engineer , architect , inventor and industrialist .
Alonzo John Gallishaw ( St. John 's , Newfoundland and Labrador , 1891 - 1968 ) was a Canadian author and teacher .
Kamal Chunchie was born in 1886 and died 1953 .
Alex MacIntyre ( 1954 - 1982 ) was a British mountaineer in the 1970s .
Hans Hansen Lilienskiold ( c.1650 -- 1703 ) was a Norwegian civil servant and non - fiction writer .
Guy Bara ( 11 July 1923 -- 18 June 2003 ) is the pseudonym of Guy Willems a Belgian comic strip writer , artist and cartoonist .
Frans Michael Franzén ( 9 February 1772 -- 14 August 1847 ) was a Swedish and Finnish poet .
Thomas Moore - Lane ( 22 January 1797 -- 26 September 1844 ) was born in Co. Wexford , Ireland and was son of Robert Moore - Lane of Lansboro , and Emily Gordon .
Elijah Montalto ( 1567 -- 1616 ) was a Marrano physician and polemicist from Paris , who became the personal physician of Maria de Medici .
William Carnaby ( 1595 - -1645 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1640 .
Margaret Fane ( born Beatrice Florence Osborn , January 10 , 1887 -- 1962 ) was an Australian novelist and poet .
Viktor Sharygin ( Russian : Виктор Шарыгин ; 9 October 1949 -- 1991 ) was a Russian swimmer who won a bronze medal at the 1974 European Aquatics Championships .
Count Otto Franc von Lichtenstein ( 1846 - -1903 ) was a cattle baron , sheriff and judge in the Big Horn Basin region of the U.S. State of Wyoming .
Isabella Macdonald ( née Clark ; 1811 -- 28 December 1857 ) was the first wife of John A. Macdonald , one of the fathers of the Canadian federation .
Kayahan Açar , stage name Kayahan , ( 29 March 1949 -- 3 April 2015 ) was a Turkish pop music singer - songwriter .
Infanta Maria of Guimarães ( 12 August 1538 -- 7 September 1577 ) was a Portuguese infanta , daughter of Infante Duarte , Duke of Guimarães ( son of King Manuel I of Portugal ) , and Isabel of Braganza .
Sir Matthew Digby Wyatt ( 28 July 1820 -- 21 May 1877 ) was a British architect and art historian who became Secretary of the Great Exhibition , Surveyor of the East India Company and the first Slade Professor of Fine Art at the University of Cambridge .
Yvonne Georgi ( 29 October 29 , 1903 -- 25 January 1975 ) was a German dancer , choreographer and ballet mistress .
Claude Bertin ( died 1705 ) was a French sculptor , who was part of the highly trained team that supplied sculptures for Versailles .
Joseph Colt Bloodgood ( 1 November 1867 - 22 October 1935 ) was a prominent surgeon in the United States based in Johns Hopkins Hospital in Baltimore , Maryland .
Edward Vivian Timms ( 1895 - -1960 ) , better known as E. V. Timms , was an Australian novelist and screenwriter .
John Monson , 11th Baron Monson ( 3 May 1932 -- 12 February 2011 ) was a British hereditary peer and crossbench member of the House of Lords .
Frank Stauffacher ( 1917 - 24 July 1955 , San Francisco , California ) was an experimental filmmaker best known for directing the cinema series `` Art in Cinema '' at the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art from 1946 to 1954 .
William Crawford Honeyman ( 1845 - -1919 ) was a Scottish musician and author .
Frederick Fermor - Hesketh , 2nd Baron Hesketh DL ( 8 April 1916 - 10 June 1955 ) , was a British peer and soldier .
John Faithfull Fleet C.I.E ( 1847 -- 21 February 1917 ) was an English civil servant with the Indian Civil Services and became known as a historian , epigraphist and linguist .
Dong Xi ( died 217 ) , courtesy name Yuanshi , was a military general serving under the warlords Sun Ce and Sun Quan in the late Eastern Han dynasty .
Friedrich Gärtner ( 1824 - 1905 ) was a German architectural painter .
Austin Burton Edwards ( 15 August 1909 -- 8 October 1960 ) was an Australian geologist , winner of the Clarke Medal in 1960 .
Sjumandjaja ( Perfected Spelling : Syumanjaya ; 5 August 1934 -- 19 July 1985 ) was an Indonesian director , screenwriter , and actor .
Leslie Holligan ( 3 August 1978 -- 15 September 2007 ) was a Guyanese footballer who last played for Caledonia AIA .
Bonham Norton ( 1565 - -1635 ) , was an English printer working in London and politician .
Sigfrid Mattsson , born 19 September 1917 , dead 27 August 2009 , was a Swedish cross - country skier .
Bryan Desmond Hughes MC ( c. 1887 -- 6 August 1918 ) was an Australian soldier and international rugby union player .
Bertie Messitt ( 28 September 1930 -- 18 February 2012 ) was an Irish long - distance runner .
Sir Patrick Muir Renison GCMG ( 24 March 1911 -- 10 November 1965 ) was a British colonial administrator .
Sir Arthur Gore , 1st Baronet ( c. 1640 -- 20 December 1697 ) was an Irish soldier and politician .
On 25 February 1986 , shortly after the death of her companion Albert Yersin , Henriette Grindat took her own life in Lausanne .
Lewis Grandison Alexander ( July 4 , 1900 - 1945 ) was an American poet , actor , playwright , and costume designer who lived in Washington , D.C. and had strong ties to the Harlem Renaissance period in New York .
George Dixon Snell ( 1836 - -1911 ) was the mayor of Spanish Fork , Utah Territory from 1873 until 1881 as well as two earlier periods .
George Young Blair ( 1826 Drumrauch near Dundee -- Drumrauch Hall 22 September 1894 ) was a Scottish marine engineer , who specialised in the building of triple expansion engines at his factory Blair & Co. , Ltd. in Stockton - on - Tees .
Gary Rippingale ( 10 July 1974 -- 31 October 1992 ) was an English professional ice hockey defenceman who played for the Nottingham Panthers .
Jerome Urban ( 1914 - 1991 ) was an American surgical oncologist who promoted superradical mastectomies until 1963 , when the lack of difference in ten - year survival rates convinced him that it worked no better than the less - mutilating radical mastectomy .
Mowaffak Allaf ( Arabic : موفق علاف‎ ) ( 1927 - -1996 ) was a Syrian diplomat , and a former ambassador to the United Nations .
Philippe Jean ( or Philip Jean ) ( 1755 -- 1802 ) was a painter .
Matthew Bryan otherwise Brian ( died 10 March 1699 ) was an English clergyman , non - juror and Jacobite preacher .
Collier Twentyman Smithers ( 1867 -- 7 December 1943 ) was a portrait , figure and rustic painter .
Sir James Lamont , 1st Baronet ( 26 April 1828 -- 29 July 1913 ) was a Scottish explorer , particularly known for his travels in the Arctic ; he also travelled to Africa and the West Indies .
William Glennie ( 7 April 1761 -- 7 January 1828 ) was a teacher to Lord Byron and father to a number of Australian pioneers .
Henry Grissell ( 4 July 1817 -- 31 January 1883 ) , sometimes known as `` Iron Henry '' , was an English foundry - man who was responsible for the ironwork in a number of prestigious buildings in England , Russia , Austria , and Egypt .
Hermann Poppelbaum Dr. Phil . ( 1891 - -1979 ) was an anthropologist , psychologist , philosopher , anthroposophist , teacher and author .
St. James of the Marches , O.F.M. , ( ca . 1391 -- 28 November 1476 ) ( Italian : Giacomo della Marca ) was an Italian Friar Minor , preacher and writer .
Jacob Marcaria ( died 1562 ) is best known as operator of the Jewish printing press in Trento in the period from 1558 to 1562 .
Emerik Derenčin ( Hungarian : Imre Derencsényi , Croatian : Mirko Derenčin ) was a Hungarian - Croatian nobleman remembered as the commander of the Croatian troops in the 1493 Battle of Krbava field .
John William Hodkinson ( 29 December 1942 -- 9 June 2013 ) , also known as J.W. Hodkinson or J.W. Hodgkinson , was a British rock vocalist .
Warren Ives Bradley ( 27 March 1847 - 15 June 1868 ) was an American children 's author who wrote as Glance Gaylord .
Jill Sinclair ( 5 April 1952 -- 22 March 2014 ) was an English businesswoman and former record company director , and a founder of ZTT Records , one of the most influential women in pop music .
Samuel Lysons FRS ( 1763 -- June 1819 ) was a notable English engraver and antiquary of the late 18th and early 19th century , who -- with his older brother , Daniel -- published the four - volume The Environs of London ( published 1792 to 1796 ) .
Empress Dowager Wang Baoming ( 王寶明 ) ( 455 - -512 ) , formally Empress An ( 安皇后 , literally `` the peaceful empress '' ) , semi - formally Empress Dowager Xuande ( 宣德太后 ) , was an empress dowager of the Chinese dynasty Southern Qi .
