Tamara Drasin ( c. 1905 -- 22 February 1943 ) , often credited as simply Tamara , was a singer and actress who introduced the song `` Smoke Gets in Your Eyes '' in the 1933 Broadway musical Roberta .
Ivan Ivanovich Zarubin ( Russian : Иван Иванович Зарубин ) ( September 27 , 1887 -- February 3 , 1964 ) was a Soviet specialist of Iranian languages , particularly Pamir languages .
Dr. Alla Selawry ( 23 August 1913 in Moscow , Russia - 27 July 1992 in Stuttgart , Germany ) , was a scientist , Anthroposophist , doctor , homeopath , and theologian writer .
Sir John Conyers ( died 1490 ) , one of twenty - five children of Sir Christopher Conyers ( died 1460 ) , was a pre - eminent member of the gentry of Yorkshire , northern England , during the fifteenth century Wars of the Roses .
Norman Bingley ( 17 September 1863 -- 16 January 1940 ) was an English sailor and Olympic Champion for Great Britain .
Jadwiga Tarło - Mniszech ( b. between 1560 and 1570 - 1629 ) was a Polish noble lady in the Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth .
Charles Seymour , 6th Duke of Somerset ( 13 August 1662 -- 2 December 1748 ) , known by the epithet `` The Proud Duke '' , was a British peer .
Heinrich XXIV , Count Reuss of Ebersdorf ( Ebersdorf , 22 January 1724 -- Ebersdorf , 13 May 1779 ) , was ruler of the German county Reuss - Ebersdorf from 1747 till his death .
Francesco Antonio Boi ( 1767 - 15 May 1850 ) was a Sardinian physician and professor of anatomy .
Sándor Sztranyavszky ( 9 December 1882 -- 30 April 1942 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Speaker of the House of Representatives of Hungary between 1935 and 1938 and as Minister of Agriculture in 1938 .
Manuel Delgado Villegas ( Spanish pronunciation : ( manw'el delˈɣaðo βiˈʎeɣas ) ; 25 January 1943 -- 2 February 1998 ) , also known as El Arropiero , was a Spanish serial killer active between 1964 and 1971 .
Joëlle Aubron ( 26 June 1959 -- 1 March 2006 ) was a militant in the French group Action directe .
Mackenzie Taylor ( 8 September 1978 -- 18 November 2010 ) was a British comic , writer and director .
Addison Webster Moore ( 30 July 1866 -- 25 August 1930 ) was a U.S. pragmatist philosopher .
Owen Roe McGovern ( December 1917 -- 2 May 2011 ) was a former Gaelic footballer for Cavan , winning 2 All - Ireland Senior Football Championship medals in 1947 and ' 48 .
Paul Hoeffler ( 1 November 1937 -- 30 July 2005 ) was an American photographer based in Toronto , Canada .
Charles Eugene Beatty ( 1909 - -1998 ) was and American track and field athlete and educator .
Aodh Ó Máille ( alias Hugh O'Malley ) , Gaelic - Irish Lord and Chief of the Name , died 1415 .
George Sutherland Smith ( 1830 -- 18 August 1903 ) was a Scotsman who migrated to Australia , a builder and paddle - steamer captain who turned to winemaking , with considerable success , founding the All Saints winery in the Rutherglen region of Victoria .
John Wastell ( 1460 -- 1515 ) was an English gothic architect responsible for Manchester Cathedral , parts of King 's College Chapel , Cambridge , the crossing tower ( Bell Harry Tower ) of Canterbury Cathedral , and the fan vaulted section of Peterborough Cathedral .
William Cadogan , 1st Earl Cadogan KT PC ( 1675 -- 17 July 1726 ) was a noted military officer in the army of John Churchill , 1st Duke of Marlborough during the War of the Spanish Succession .
Alfred Senier ( 24 January 1853 - 29 June 1918 ) was a chemist and a Professor of Chemistry , Queen 's College , Galway from 1891 until his death .
Rabia Sultan ( Ottoman Turkish : رابعه سلطان‎ ; before 1680 - 14 January 1712 ) was a consort to Sultan Ahmed II of the Ottoman Empire .
George Burton Drake ( 1870 - -1942 ) was a Congregational minister , born August 8 , 1870 in Eagle , New York to John ( 1833 - -1901 ) and Emily ( Helmer ) Drake ( 1848 - -1904 ) .
Hughie McPherson ( 21 August 1918 -- 25 July 2013 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray and Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Joseph Parsons ( 1876 - -1951 ) was a long - serving principal of Perth Modern School and an influential West Australian educator .
Henry Willoughby , 16th Baron Willoughby of Parham ( 1696 -- 29 January 1775 ) was an English peer of the House of Lords .
Francis Peck ( 1692 - -1743 ) was an English antiquary , best known for his Desiderata Curiosa ( 1732 - 1735 ) .
Stane Derganc ( 23 April 1893 -- 9 August 1981 ) a.k.a . Chainman ( Slovene : Verigar ) was a Yugoslavian gymnast .
Burkhard VII . Münch ( died 29 August 1444 ) was a knight and life peer , a renowned late member of the Landskron branch of the Münch family .
Thomas Ferrier Hamilton ( 31 March 1820 -- 7 August 1905 ) was an Australian politician , pastoralist , and sportsman .
Merrill Leroy Ellis ( 9 December 1916 Cleburne , Texas -- 12 July 1981 Denton , Texas ) was an American composer , performer , and experimental music researcher .
Wang Lang ( died 228 ) , courtesy name Jingxing , was a politician and minor warlord who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Marian Hannah Winter ( 1910 -- 15 December 1981 ) was an American dance historian .
John Furber Dexter ( 1848 , Kensington , London - 1927 , Wandsworth , London ) was an English collector of Charles Dickens 's works .
John Clark Marshman ( 1794 - -1877 ) was an English journalist and historian .
Johan Oscar Michelsen ( 4 December 1844 -- 12 August 1936 ) was a Norwegian missionary to the New Hebrides ( now Vanuatu ) .
Christian Friedrich Wilhelm Heinrich Syberg , generally known as Fritz Syberg , ( 28 July 1862 , Fåborg -- 20 December 1939 , Kerteminde ) was a Danish painter and illustrator , one of the reactionary Fynboerne or `` Funen Painters '' group living and working on the island of Funen .
Mohan Gokhale ( 1954 -- 29 April 1999 ) was an Indian film , television and theater actor who has worked in art films such as Sparsh , Bhavni Bhavai and Mirch Masala .
Freeman Wills Crofts FRSA ( 1 June 1879 -- 11 April 1957 ) was an Anglo - Irish mystery author during the Golden Age of Detective Fiction .
George Robert Aberigh - Mackay ( 25 July 1848 -- 12 January 1881 ) , Anglo - Indian writer , son of a Bengal chaplain , was educated at Magdalen College School , Oxford and Cambridge University .
George Bird Evans ( 28 December 1906 -- 5 May 1998 ) was an author , an artist , a dog breeder , and a sportsman .
Thomas Maxfield ( real name Macclesfield ) ( c.1590 -- 1 July 1616 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest .
William Francis Ganong , M.A. , Ph.D. , LL.D. , F.R.S.C. , ( 19 February 1864 - 7 September 1941 ) was a Canadian botanist , historian and cartographer .
Sir Robert Peel , 3rd Baronet GCB , PC ( 4 May 1822 -- 9 May 1895 ) was a British Peelite and later Liberal politician .
Noel Mewton - Wood ( 20 November 1922 -- 5 December 1953 ) was an Australian - born concert pianist who achieved international fame on the basis of many distinguished concerto recordings during his short life .
Alfred Otto Herz ( 14 October 1856 Hoyerswerda , Silesia -12 July 1905 ) was a German entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera and Coleoptera .
Matthew Clerk ( 1659 -- 25 January 1735 ) , was an Irish Presbyterian minister .
Anders Hansen Grønneberg ( 1779 -- 30 October 1819 ) was a Norwegian Naval officer and farmer who served as a representative at the Norwegian Constituent Assembly in 1814 .
Lionel Edward Pyke ( 1854 - -1899 ) an English - Jewish barrister , born at Chatham England on 21 April 1854 and died in Brighton England on 26 March 1899 .
Philip Carteret Webb ( 14 August 1702 -- 22 June 1770 ) was an English barrister , involved with the 18th - century antiquarian movement .
Lelia J. Robinson died at the age of 41 , in 1891 , leaving behind a remarkable impact on our legal history .
Sir David Wilson , 1st Baronet ( 4 April 1855 -- 8 March 1930 ) was a Scottish landowner and agriculturalist .
Domenico Bettini ( 1644 - 1705 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , mainly depicting still - life subjects .
Stanislaus Okurut ( ? -- 5 April 2014 ) was a Ugandan politician .
Jonathan Marsh ( 1621 - -1672 ) was a founding settler of the New Haven Colony , and of Norwalk , Connecticut .
John Willis Clark ( 1833 -- 1910 ) , sometimes J. W. Clark , was an English academic and antiquarian .
Imre Markója ( 1931 -- 27 March 2008 ) was a Hungarian politician and jurist , who served as Minister of Justice between 1978 and 1988 .
Praepositinus ( Gilbert Prevostin of Cremona , Prevostinus Cremonensis ) ( c. 1135 -- 1210 ) was an Italian scholastic philosopher and theologian .
William Widdrington , 1st Baron Widdrington ( 11 July 1610 -- 3 September 1651 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1642 and was created a peer in 1643 .
Michael George Farr ( 30 June 1941 -- 18 April 1996 ) , professionally known as Mike Leander , was an English arranger , songwriter and record producer .
Michelle Brunner ( 31 December 1953 -- 24 June 2011 ) was a British bridge player , writer and teacher .
John Barton Hack ( 2 July 1805 -- 4 October 1884 ) was an early settler in South Australia ; a prominent farmer , businessman and public figure .
Norrie Woodhall ( 18 December 1905 -- 25 October 2011 ) was an English stage actress and the last surviving member of the Hardy Players , a theatrical group based around the work of poet Thomas Hardy , whom Woodhall knew personally after an encounter in 1924 .
George William Stow ( 2 February 1822 , Nuneaton , Warwickshire , England -- 17 March 1882 , Heilbron , Orange Free State ) was a South African geologist and ethnologist , a poet , historian , artist , cartographer and writer .
Ruth Clark ( Woodcraft name : Minobi , meaning Glad Heart ) ( 29 November 1899 -- 2 October 1964 ) was the author of the first woodcraft book for girls and co - founder of the Kibbo Kift .
Ashton Oxenden ( 20 September 1808 -- 22 February 1892 ) was Bishop of Montreal .
Graham Dixon - Lewis , MA , DPhil , FRS ( 1 July 1922 -- 5 August 2010 ) was a British combustion engineer .
Abba Poemen ( Greek : Ὁ Ἅγιος Ποιμήν ; ποιμήν means `` shepherd '' ) ( c. 340 - -450 ) was an Egyptian monk and early Desert Father who is the most quoted Abba ( Father ) in the Apophthegmata Patrum ( Sayings of the Desert Fathers ) .
Orunamamu ( 4 April 1921 -- 4 September 2014 ) was an American / Canadian professional storyteller , raconteur and griot .
Baruch Rahmilevich Mendelson ( 22 March 1910 -- 13 April 1994 ) , commonly known as Bert Ramelson , was an industrial organiser and politician for the Communist Party of Great Britain .
Hamilton Prieleaux Bee Maule , commonly known as Tex Maule ( May 19 , 1915 in Ojus , Florida -- May 16 , 1981 ) was the lead American football writer for Sports Illustrated in the 1950s , 1960s , and 1970s .
August Mikael Soininen ( 3 November 1860 , Kuhmoniemi - 12 March 1924 ; surname until 1906 Johnsson ) was a Finnish professor of Education theory ( at the University of Helsinki ) and politician .
Harald Skavlan ( 19 June 1854 -- 11 July 1908 ) was a Norwegian railroad engineer .
Christina McCall ( 29 January 1935 -- 2005 ) was a Canadian political writer .
Harald Barlie ( 4 January 1937 -- 12 October 1995 ) was a Norwegian Greco - Roman wrestler .
Sir Robin Mountfield , KCB ( 16 October 1939 -- 9 November 2011 ) was a British civil servant , who retired in 1999 from his most senior post as Permanent Secretary at the Cabinet Office .
Countess Joanna of Pfirt ( 1300 -- 15 November 1351 ) was Duchess consort of Austria and a member of the House of Habsburg by marriage .
George Beesley ( Bisley ) ( born at The Hill in Goosnargh parish , Lancashire , England , of a Catholic family ; died 2 July 1591 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest .
Robert Bealknap ( or Belknap ) JP ( died 19 January 1401 ) was a British justice .
Joseph Ivor Linton ( also referred to as Ivor Joseph Linton ) ( b. July 2 , 1900 -- d. March 1 , 1982 ) was an Israeli diplomat .
Eric M. Rogers ( 15 August 1902 -- 1 July 1990 ) was a British author and physics educator .
Alodie - Virginie Paradis ( 12 May 1840 -- 3 May 1912 ) was a Canadian Roman Catholic nun who established the Little Sisters of the Holy Family congregation in 1880 .
Gustaf Wathier Hamilton ( 1783 - 1835 ) was a Swedish count , jurist and official .
Kristo Luarasi ( 1876 - 1934 ) was an Albanian nationalist figure and publisher .
Pierre Sterlé ( 1905 - -1978 ) was a French jeweller , known as the ' couturier of jewellery ' .
Ahlerich ( 1971 - -1992 ) was a Westphalian gelding .
Tbeli Abuserisdze ( Georgian : ტბელი აბუსერისძე ) ( c. 1190 -- 1240 ) was a medieval Georgian scholar and religious writer .
Gang Jo ( 강조 , 康兆 , died 31 December 1010 ) was a Goryeo general who served under King Mokjong of Goryeo and King Hyeonjong of Goryeo .
José Joaquín Vicuña Larraín ( 1786 - -1857 ) was a Chilean politician whose selection as vice president by Congress precipitated the Chilean Civil War of 1829 .
Alain Voss ( 1946 -- 13 May 2011 ) , also known as Al Voss , was a Brazilian - French comics artist .
Pierre Auguste Brahain Ducange ( Tours , ? -- Paris , 1833 ) was a French journalist , minor diplomat , secret agent , swindler , and author .
Richard Farnworth ( died 1666 ) was an English Quaker writer of tracts .
Father Cyril Bernard Papali OCD or `` Fr . Cyril Bernard of the Mother of God OCD '' ( 1902 - -1981 ) was a Carmelite monk of the Manjummel Province .
William Battine ( 25 January 1765 -- 5 September 1836 ) , was the English holder of many legal offices , and poet .
Jan Bochenek ( 20 September 1931 -- 2 November 2011 ) was a Polish weightlifter .
Douglas Kolk ( born 1963 , Newark , New Jersey , died August 2014 ) was a United States artist based in Boston , Massachusetts .
Fereydun Ebrahimi ( Azerbaijani : Firudin İbrahimi , Persian : فريدون ابراهيمي‎‎ ; 1919 in Astara -- 1947 in Tabriz ) was an Iranian Azerbaijani Jurist and politician .
Wilhelm Ernst Oswald Kohts ( 31 January 1844 in Berent , West Prussia -- 1912 ) was a German physician and pediatrician .
Helmer Swenholt ( 28 June 1886 - 8 May 1952 ) was born in Wittenberg , Shawano County , Wisconsin ( near Shawano , Wisconsin ) .
Manuel Cardoso ( baptized 11 December 1566 -- 24 November 1650 ) was a Portuguese composer and organist .
Jacob Levitzki , also known as Yaakov Levitsky ( Hebrew : יעקב לויצקי‎ ) ( 17 August 1904 - 25 February 1956 ) was an Israeli mathematician .
George Allsop ( 4 January 1864 -- 27 March 1927 ) played first - class cricket for Transvaal between 1890 - -91 and 1897 - -98 , and also stood as an umpire in one cricket Test match in 1895 - 96 .
Robert Some ( Soame ) ( 1542 - -1609 ) was an English churchman and academic .
Eugenia Popescu - Județ ( also spelled Popescu - Judetz , 1925 - -2011 ) was a Romanian dancer , dance teacher , choreographer and folklorist .
Charles William Dyson Perrins ( 25 May 1864 -- 29 January 1958 ) was an English businessman , bibliophile and philanthropist .
Jimmy Russell ( 29 August 1879 -- 6 August 1925 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rao Muhammad Afzal Khan ( born in 1925 in Kalanaur , India - 12 May 1988 ) was a politician in Pakistan .
Louis Christian Oliver Zachariasen known as Louis Zachariasen ( 21 January 1890 in Kirkja , Fugloy -- 30 August 1960 ) was a Faroese writer and politician ( Sjálvstýrisflokkurin ) .
George Karreman ( 4 November 1920 -- 27 February 1997 ) was a Dutch - born US physicist , mathematical biophysicist and mathematical / theoretical biologist .
Cináed mac Mugróin ( died 829 ) was a king of the Uí Failge , a Laigin people of County Offaly , Ireland .
Roberts Plūme ( 16 May 1897 -- 25 August 1956 ) was a Latvian cyclist and cross - country skier .
Bernardo Celentano ( 23 February 1835 -- 28 July 1863 ) was an Italian painter of the 19th century , who painted historical themes in the style of Realism .
Sir Louis Cools - Lartigue , O.B.E. ( 18 January 1905 - 21 August 1993 ) was a Dominican politician .
Martin Drew ( 11 February 1944 -- 29 July 2010 ) was an English jazz drummer , who played with Ronnie Scott between 1975 and 1995 , and with Oscar Peterson between 1974 and 2007 .
Roger Quenolle ( 19 July 1925 -- 13 July 2004 ) was a French football striker who played for RC Paris , Rouen , Strasbourg , Red Star , Stade Saint - Germain .
Henry Kent Hughes ( c. 1814 -- 30 August 1880 ) , usually referred to as `` H. Kent Hughes '' , was a pastoralist and politician who sat in the South Australian House of Assembly from 1868 to 1875 representing the seats of Victoria and later , Port Adelaide .
Gerald Willoughby - Meade ( 25 September 1875 - 24 June 1958 ) was a British author who wrote on the subject of the supernatural in Chinese folklore .
Kirk von Ackermann was an American contractor who disappeared in Iraq in 2003 .
François Lamathe Bédos de Celles de Salelles , known as Dom Bédos de Celles , ( 24 January 1709 -- 25 November 1779 ) was a Benedictine monk best known for being a master pipe organ builder .
Don Lindner ( c. 1936 -- 31 December 2008 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with North Adelaide in the SANFL .
Syed Ahmed Quadri died of natural causes after a short illness on Wednesday , 16 May 1990 at Hyderabad , and was buried at the ancestral graveyard at Tekmal
Stanisława Angel - Engelówna ( 23 April 1908 -- 7 August 1958 ) was a Polish stage and film actress .
Eufrosin Poteca ( born Radu Poteca ; 1786 -- 10 December 1858 ) was a Romanian philosopher , theologian , and translator , professor at the Saint Sava Academy of Bucharest .
Gerrit van Uylenburgh ( c. 1625 -- 1679 ) , or Gerrit Uylenburgh , was a Dutch Golden Age painter and art - dealer .
Frank Bird Linderman ( September 25 , 1869 -- May 12 , 1938 ) was a Montana writer , politician , Native American ally and ethnographer .
Georg Johann Pfeffer ( 1854 - -1931 ) was a German zoologist , primarily a malacologist , a scientist who studies mollusks .
Wu Changshuo ( September 12 , 1844 - November 29 , 1927 ) , born Wu Junqing , was a prominent painter , calligrapher and seal artist of the late Qing Period .
Heinrich Andres ( 5 May 1883 , Bengel -- 11 August 1970 , Bonn ) was a German educator and botanist known for his investigations of Rhineland flora .
Edi Federer ( 20 February 1955 -- 30 May 2012 ) was an Austrian ski jumper .
Rabbi Shemaryahu Gurary , also known by his Hebrew initials as Rashag , ( 1898 - 1989 ) was an Orthodox rabbi belonging to the Chabad - Lubavitch Hasidic movement .
Ona Šimaitė ( 6 January 1894 -- 17 January 1970 ) of Lithuania , a librarian at Vilnius University , used her position to aid and rescue Jews in the Vilna Ghetto .
Abu Abdullah Muhammad al - Arabi al - Darqawi ( 1760 - -1823 ) was a Moroccan Sufi leader of the Shadhili tariqa and the author of letters concerning the dhikr he preached and instructions for daily life .
Léon Chenault ( 1853 - -1930 ) was a French nurseryman and botanist best known for his nurseries at Orleans , where he raised a vast range of plants , notably roses , from seeds and cuttings obtained from foreign sources such as Kew and the Arnold Arboretum .
Paragu ( Burmese : ပါရဂူ ; pronounced : ( pàɹəɡù ) ; 10 November 1921 -- 9 April 2011 ) was a Burmese writer .
Angelo Cuniberti , I.M.C. ( 6 February 1921 -- 26 June 2012 ) was an Italian Prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Dr Arthur Charlett ( 1655 -- 4 November 1722 ) was an Oxford academic and administrator .
Mita Klima ( 1892/1893 -- April / May 1945 at Berlin ; married name Mita Kribben ) was an Austrian tennis player .
Charles Seymour Robinson , D.D. , LL.D. , ( March 31 , 1829 -- February 1 , 1899 ) , was a pastor , and an editor and compiler of hymns .
Robert Bland ( 1730 - -1816 ) was an English physician and man - midwife ( obstetrician ) .
Prince Yên Sinh Trần Liễu ( 1211 - -1251 ) was the elder brother of the Trần Thái Tông , the first emperor of Trần Dynasty .
William John Bankes ( 11 December 1786 -- 15 April 1855 ) , the second , but first surviving son of Henry Bankes , was a notable explorer , Egyptologist and adventurer .
Harry Geoffrey Beasley ( 18 December 1881 -- 24 February 1939 ) was a British anthropologist and museum curator who developed an important ethnographic collection during the early 20th century that is now held in various British museums .
Johann Friedrich Gleditsch ( 15 August 1653 -- 26 March 1716 ) was a major book publisher in the late 17th and early 18th centuries .
John Cecil , 5th Earl of Exeter ( c. 1648 -- 29 August 1700 ) , known as Lord Burghley until 1678 , was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
Matthew Edmond McCoy ( 2 June 1868 - December 1929 ) served as Magistrate of the British Overseas Territory of Pitcairn Island in 1909 .
José María Caro Martínez ( Spanish pronunciation : ( xoˈse maˈɾia ˈkaɾo maɾˈtineθ ) ( ) ; 1830 -- 11 November 1916 ) was a Chilean politician and civil servant .
Ivor Wood ( 4 May 1932 -- 13 October 2004 ) was a prolific Anglo French stop motion director , producer , animator and writer known for his work on children 's television series .
Auguste Joseph Peiffer ( 1832 - -1886 ) was a French sculptor , mainly working in bronze on allegorical and mythological subjects .
Ellen Neel ( 1916 - -1966 ) was a Kwakwaka'wakw artist woodcarver and is the first woman known to have professionally carved totem poles .
Søren Tjønneland ( 1868 - -1954 ) was a Norwegian mason , trade unionist and politician for the Labour Party and Social Democratic Labour parties .
William Drake Westervelt ( December 26 , 1849 -- March 9 , 1939 ) was the author of several books and magazines on Hawaiian history and legends .
Panas Myrny ( real name is Panas Yakovych Rudchenko , 13 May 1849 - 28 January 1920 ) was a famous Ukrainian prose writer and playwright .
Ian Breakwell ( 26 May 1943 in Long Eaton , Derbyshire -- 14 October 2005 in London ) was a world - renowned British fine artist .
George Clifton ( 1823 - -1913 ) was an English collector of seaweed specimens , active in Australia .
Peter Severin Steenstrup ( 29 November 1807 -- 17 February 1863 ) was a Norwegian naval officer and businessperson .
Franz Michael Vierthaler ( 25 September 1758 -- 3 October 1827 ) was a distinguished Austrian pedagogue .
Sir Robert Francis Dunnell , 1st Baronet KCB ( 26 July 1868 - -16 July 1960 ) was an English solicitor , civil servant and railway executive .
Skendrowell Syiemlieh ( died 2008 ) was a Khasi folk and Gospel singer .
William Savile , 2nd Marquess of Halifax ( 1665 -- 31 August 1700 ) was the son of George Savile , 1st Viscount Halifax and Dorothy Savile , Viscountess Halifax ( née Spencer ) .
Sir Philip Stephens , 1st Baronet ( 11 October 1723 -- 20 November 1809 ) was First Secretary of the Admiralty in the late 18th century and later a Lord Commissioner of the British Admiralty between 1795 and 1806 .
Yi Chong ( 이정 ; 1541 - -1622 ? ) was a Korean painter , one of the most popular of his time .
João Soares de Albergaria ( c. 1415 - 1499 ) , also referred to as João Soares ( or João Soares Velho ) , was the second Portuguese Dontary - Captain of the islands of Santa Maria and São Miguel , succeeding his maternal uncle Gonçalo Velho Cabral in the title .
Admiral Sir Richard Hughes , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1729 -- 5 January 1812 ) was a British naval commander .
Joe Cardarelli ( 1944 - -1994 ) was a poet , painter , graduate of the Johns Hopkins Writing Seminars , and teacher of writing at the Maryland Institute College of Art for 27 years .
Conradin of Bornada ( or Conradin of Brescia ) ( died 1 November 1429 ) was an Italian Dominican preacher .
Iller Pattacini ( Barco di Bibbiano , 7 October 1933 -- Barco , 3 September 2006 ) , was an Italian composer of light music , arranger , band leader , and conductor .
John LaPorta ( 13 April 1920 -- 12 May 2004 ) was a Philadelphia - born jazz clarinetist and saxophonist .
Henry Breres ( died 1619 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1586 and 1611 .
Marjan Keršič aka Belač ( Slovene : Marjan Keršič - Belač ) ( 18 May 1920 -- 3 June 2003 ) was a Slovenian sculptor and mountaineer .
Constance Mary Whitehouse , CBE ( née Hutcheson , 13 June 1910 -- 23 November 2001 ) was an English social activist known for her strong opposition to social liberalism and the mainstream British media , both of which she accused of encouraging a more permissive society .
Adolf Büchler ( also Adolph ) ( October 18 , 1867 , at Priekopa , Hungary ( now Slovakia ) -- 1939 ) was an Austro - Hungarian rabbi , historian and theologian .
Alistair Cameron Crombie ( 4 November 1915 -- 9 February 1996 ) was an Australian historian of science who began his career as a zoologist .
James Wentworth Buller ( 1 October 1798 -- 13 March 1865 ) of Downes , Crediton , Devon , was a British Whig Member of Parliament for Exeter , in Devon , from 1830 to 1835 , and for North Devon from 1857 to 1865 .
Frederick Nicholas Charrington ( 4 February 1850 -- 2 January 1936 ) was an English social reformer who renounced succession to a fortune of over £ 1 million in order to devote his life to temperance work .
Martin Kneser ( 21 January 1928 -- 16 February 2004 ) was a German mathematician .
Jorge González Camarena ( 24 March 1908 -- 24 May 1980 ) was a prominent painter , muralist and sculptor .
Joseph Albert Rosario , M.S.F.S ( 30 May 1915 -- 31 July 2011 ) was an Indian prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Esther Abrahams ( c.1767 or 1771 -- 26 August 1846 ) was a Londoner sent to Australia as a convict on the First Fleet .
Mara McAfee ( 1929 - 1984 ) was an American Pop artist and illustrator best known for her satirical depictions of historical figures , contemporary subjects , and high art traditions .
Gerard Johnson the elder ( d. 1611 ) is the Anglicised form of Gheerart Janssen , a Dutch sculptor who operated a monument workshop in Elizabethan and Jacobean England and the father of Gerard Johnson the younger , who is thought to have created Shakespeare 's funerary monument .
Henry Nicol ( 1845 - -1880 ) was a philologist specialized in French phonology .
Rama Varma XIII ( died July 1851 ) was an Indian monarch who ruled the Kingdom of Cochin from 1844 to 1851 .
Jean - Baptiste Pallegoix , M.E.P. ( 24 October 1805 -- 18 June 1862 ) was vicar apostolic of Eastern Siam .
Emilia Aylmer Blake , also known as Emilia Aylmer Gowing , ( 1846 - -1905 ) was a British dramatist , novelist and poet .
Charles Corbin ( 1882 - -1970 ) was a French diplomat who served as ambassador to Britain before and during the early part of the Second World War , from 1933 to 27 June 1940 .
Zephyrin Engelhardt , O.F.M. , ( born Charles Anthony Engelhardt ; 1851 - -1934 ) was a German - born Roman Catholic priest and clerical historian of the Franciscan Order .
Daniel Eberlin ( 4 December 1647 -- ca . 1715 ) was a German Baroque composer and Kapellmeister .
Gordon Rattray Taylor ( 11 January 1911 -- 7 December 1981 ) was a popular British author and journalist .
Hermann Gmeiner ( 23 June 1919 -- 26 April 1986 ) was an Austrian philanthropist and the founder of SOS Children 's Villages .
Ernst Diesen ( 6 April 1913 -- 14 November 1970 ) was a Norwegian revue and film actor and theatre director .
Germaine Yvonne Arnaud ( 20 December 1890 -- 20 September 1958 ) was a French pianist , singer and actress .
Leetile Benjamin Mophatlane ( 12 May 1973 -- 11 June 2014 ) was a South African business magnate , and former Chief Executive Officer of Business Connexion Group He died on 11 June 2014 after suffering cardiac arrest while in a meeting in Rosebank in Johannesburg .
Herbert of Wetterau ( c. 930 -- 992 ) was the son of Odo of Wetterau and a daughter ( presumably named Cunigunde ) of Herbert I , Count of Vermandois and Bertha de Morvis .
Belchior Febos , also called Phoebus ( died 1632 ) was one of the leading Portuguese jurists of his time .
The Rev. Dr Thomas Henry Stokoe DD ( 1833 -- 8 December 1903 ) , known as T. H. Stokoe and as Dr Stokoe , was an English clergyman , schoolmaster , author and headmaster .
A. S. Subbaraj ( 28 October 1914 to 22 February 1963 ) was an Indian politician and former Member of the Legislative Assembly of Tamil Nadu .
Péter Petrovics ( Hungarian : Petrovics Péter ; Serbian : Петар Петровић/Petar Petrović ; c. 1486 -- October 1557 ) was a Hungarian noble of Serb ethnicity from Banat , who was active in the 16th - century Transylvania .
Alexander Goss ( 5 July 1814 -- 3 October 1872 ) was a Roman Catholic Bishop ; his highest posting was as the Bishop of Liverpool .
Ram Brahma Sanyal ( 1858 - 13 October 1908 ) was the first superintendent of the Alipore Zoological Gardens in Kolkata ( then Calcutta ) .
William Landsborough ( 21 February 1825 -- 16 March 1886 ) was an explorer of Australia .
John Nathaniel Couch ( 12 October 1896 in Prince Edward County , Virginia -- 16 December 1986 ) was an American mycologist .
Quraish Pur , born Zulqarnain Qureshi ( 1932 -- 5 August 2013 ) was a scholar , Urdu writer / novelist , columnist and media expert from Pakistan .
Valentine Blanchard ( 1831 -- 14 November 1901 ) was a prominent English photographer who was widely recognized for his artistic and technical contributions in the early days of photography in the 1860s .
Maria Peale ( 1787 - -1866 ) was an American painter , primarily of still - lifes .
William Grindal ( died 1548 ) , was an English scholar .
Oreste Carpi ( 3 November 1921 -- 11 March 2008 ) was an Italian deaf painter , engraver and ceramist .
Rachel Pinney ( 11 July 1909 -- 19 October 1995 ) was a British doctor who pioneered therapeutic approaches to children 's development in the 1960s which she termed Creative Listening , and Children 's Hours .
Vera Elkan ( 1908 - -2008 ) was a South African photographer who is remembered for her images of the International Brigades in the Spanish Civil War .
Bauddha Rishi Mahapragya ( Devanagari : बौद्ध ऋषि महाप्रज्ञा ) ( born Nani Kaji Shrestha ) ( 21 May 1901 -- 1979 ) was one of the most influential figures in the revival of Theravada Buddhism in Nepal in the 1920s .
Stephen L. Ross ( c. 1815 - January 4 , 1891 ) was an American farmer from Jacks Creek , Tennessee , who served two terms in the Tennessee State Senate and ( very briefly ) in the Tennessee House of Representatives .
Hans Jürgen Kiebach ( 28 August 1930 -- 19 May 1995 ) was a German production designer , art director and set decorator .
Aleksander Rajchman ( 13 November 1890 -- July or August 1940 ) was a Polish mathematician who introduced Rajchman measures .
Sophie of Landsberg ( Polish : Sophie z Landsberg , German : Sophie von Landsberg ) ( ca . 1259 -- 24 August 1318 ) was a German princess member of the House of Wettin and by marriage Duchess of Glogów .
Mary Devenport O'Neill ( 3 August 1879 -- 1967 ) was an Irish poet and dramatist and a friend and colleague of W. B. Yeats , George Russell , and Austin Clarke .
Laxman Mahadeo Chitale , ( 1892 - 1960 ) was an Indian architect , author and one of the first Indian associates of the Royal Institute of British Architects .
Samuel Isaac ( 1812 -- 22 November 1886 ) was a merchant and a projector of the Mersey Railway Tunnel .
Jeannie Thib ( 1955 - -2013 ) was a Canadian artist , sculptor and printmaker .
John Rex ( 1925 -- 18 December 2011 ) was a South African - born British sociologist .
Samuel Schoenbaum ( 6 March 1927 -- 27 March 1996 ) was a leading 20th century Shakespearean biographer and scholar .
Jean René Baroux ( 1922 in Casablanca , Morocco -- 1992 in Nanaimo , British Columbia ) was a veteran of the World War II and a writer very much engaged in the evolution of the French language .
Joanne Jordan ( 1920 -- 29 July 2009 ) was an American actress and television spokesmodel .
Sarduri II ( ruled 764 - 735 BCE ) was a King of Urartu .
Tadeusz Sobolewicz ( Polish pronunciation : ( taˈdɛuʂ sɔbɔˈlɛvit͡ʂ ) ; 25 March 1925 -- 28 October 2015 ) was a Polish actor and author , and a survivor of six Nazi concentration camps , a Gestapo prison , and a nine - day death march .
Văn Phụng ( Hanoi , 1930 - -1999 ) was a Vietnamese songwriter .
Charles Alton Ellis ( 1876 - -1949 ) was a professor , structural engineer and mathematician who was chiefly responsible for the structural design of the Golden Gate Bridge .
Baba Qamar U Zaman Faridi Chishti , more commonly known as Sarkar Baba Qamar U Zaman ( 1940 - -2011 ) was a Muslim Saint from the Chishti Order .
Alfred Karamuço ( January 27 , 1943 in Korçë -- 14 February 2012 in Tirana ) was an Albanian politician , attorney and constitutional judge .
John Hore ( 1690 - -1762 ) was an English navigation engineer notable for engineering the River Kennet navigation in 1718 .
Chauncy Hare Townshend , born Chauncy Hare Townsend ( 10 April 1798 , Godalming , Surrey -- 25 February 1868 ) , was a 19th - century English poet , clergyman , mesmerist , collector , dilettante and hypochondriac .
Sir Jonathan Trelawny , 2nd Baronet ( ca . 1623 -- 5 March 1681 ) , of Trelawne , Cornwall , was an English Member of Parliament .
Charles Alexander Shain ( 6 February 1922 -- 11 February 1960 ) was an Australian pioneer in the field of radio astronomy .
John Jenner Weir , FLS , FZS ( 9 August 1822 -- 23 March 1894 ) was an English amateur entomologist , ornithologist and British civil servant .
David Erskine , 2nd Lord Cardross ( 1616 - -1671 ) was a Scottish Royalist .
Thaman Gurung VC ( 2 October 1924 -- 10 November 1944 ) was a Nepalese Gurkha recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Carl Ludwig Franck ( 25 September 1904 -- 20 February 1985 ) was a German - British architect who practiced in the United Kingdom from the 1930s to the 1960s .
William Baillie , Lord Provand ( died 26 May 1593 ) , was a Scottish judge .
Joseph Albert Riley ( 1869 -- 6 January 1940 ) , invariably referred to as `` J. A. Riley '' , was a prominent South Australian businessman , and longtime organising secretary of several South Australian institutions .
Pádraig Ó Finneadha ( 23 January 1913 -- 18 November 1986 ) , Irish scholar and doctor .
Aldo Giuffrè ( 10 April 1924 -- 26 June 2010 ) was an Italian film actor and comedian who appeared in over 90 films between 1948 and 2001 .
Zaya Pandita or Namkhaijamts ( 1599 - -1662 ) was a Buddhist missionary priest and scholar of Oirat origin who is the most prominent Oirat Buddhist scholar .
Dennis Armitage ( 28 May 1928 -- 5 November 2005 ) was a British pianist , saxophonist and painter , living in Switzerland .
Guillaume de la Sudrie ( la Sudré ) ( died 18 April 1373 ) was a French Dominican and Cardinal , born Laguenne , Corrèze .
Len Ablett ( 10 May 1916 -- 19 December 2006 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond in the VFL during the early 1940s .
Patrick von Kalckreuth ( 1892 - -1970 ) was a leading German maritime painter .
Air Vice - Marshal Meredith Thomas CSI , CBE , DFC , AFC RAF ( 6 July 1892 -- 20 May 1984 ) was a senior commander in the Royal Air Force during World War II . He began his career as a flying ace during World War I , credited with five aerial victories .
Michael Podro CBE , FBA ( 13 March 1931 -- 28 March 2008 ) was a British art historian .
James Maitland , 8th Earl of Lauderdale KT PC ( 26 January 1759 -- 10 September 1839 ) was Keeper of the Great Seal of Scotland and a representative peer for Scotland in the House of Lords .
George Getgood ( 15 November 1892 -- 22 July 1970 ) , also known as George Goodman , was a Scottish professional footballer who played as a half - back for various clubs in the 1920s .
Henry Melville ( 1799 - 1873 ) was an Australian author and journalist best remembered for writing the play The Bushrangers .
Thomas Graeme Nelson Haldane , known as Graeme Haldane ( 14 December 1897 -- 24 June 1981 ) , was a Scottish engineer .
Sir Thomas McClure , 1st Baronet , DL ( 4 March 1806 -- 21 January 1893 ) was an MP for Belfast from 1868 - -1874 .
Silvester Diggles ( 24 January 1817 -- 21 March 1880 ) was an Australian artist and musician of British origin , as well as being a noted amateur ornithologist and entomologist .
Robert Goossens ( 1927 -- 7 January 2016 ) was a French jeweller .
John IV , Duke of Mecklenburg ( before 1370 -- 16 October 1422 ) was sole ruler of the Duchy of Mecklenburg from 1384 to 1395 and co - regent from 1395 to 1422 .
Sandor Harmati ( 9 July 1892 -- 4 April 1936 ) was a Hungarian - American violinist , conductor and composer , best known for his song `` Bluebird of Happiness '' written in 1934 for Jan Peerce .
Sir Richard Beaumont , 1st Baronet JP ( 2 August 1574 -- 28 October 1631 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1625 .
Muhammed Hamdi Yazır also known as Elmalılı Hamdi Yazır and Elmalılı ( 1878 , Antalya - 27 May 1942 , İstanbul ) was a Turkish theologian , logician , Qur'an translator , Qur'anic exegesis scholar , Islamic legal academic , philosopher and encyclopedist .
Mordechai ben Hillel HaKohen ( c. 1250 - -1298 ) , also known as The Mordechai , was a 13th - century German rabbi and posek .
Piero de Bonzi ( also Pierre ; April 15 , 1631 - 11 July 1703 ) was an Italian - French Roman Catholic cardinal .
Dr. V. K. Narayana Menon ( Thrissur Vadakke Kurupath Narayana Menon ) ( 1911 - 1997 ) was a scholar of classical Indian dance and Indian classical music .
General Mateo Noriel Luga ( 1872 - -1935 ) was an Ibanag revolutionary , named one of the 100 prominent natives of Cebu .
John Freeston ( 1512 -- 1594 ) is known by the locals of Altofts and Normanton , West Yorkshire .
Enid Justin ( 1893 - -1990 ) , a native of Montague County , Texas , founded the Nocona Boot Company in the small community of Nocona .
Warder Cresson ( Philadelphia , Pennsylvania , July 13 , 1798 - Jerusalem November 6 , 1860 ) was the first U.S. Consul to Jerusalem .
Francis Slacke , CSI ( 6 June 1853 -- 8 August 1940 ) was a senior officer in the Indian Civil Service and later became Lieutenant - Governor of Bengal .
Siegfried Knemeyer ( 5 April 1909 -- 11 April 1979 ) was a German aeronautical engineer and aviator .
Hafiz Ghulam Ahmad Faroghi ( 1861 - -1919 ) was a scholar of repute of Arabic and Persian language at Bhopal state .
Oliver Herford ( 1863 - -1935 ) was an American writer , artist and illustrator who has been called `` The American Oscar Wilde '' .
Grace Thorpe ( born 10 December 1921 ; died 1 April 2008 ) was a World War II veteran with the Women 's Army Corps , receiving a Bronze Star Medal due to what she did in the New Guinea campaign .
Stephan Szántó ( István Arator ) ( 1541 in Diocese of Raab , Hungary -- 1612 in Olmütz ) was a Hungarian Jesuit .
Thomas Rowe Edmonds ( 1803 - -1889 ) was an English actuary and political economist .
Elam Ives , Jr. ( 1802 - -1864 ) was a New England - based music teacher whose work with William Channing Woodbridge helped introduce the ideas of Johann Heinrich Pestalozzi into music education in the United States .
John C. Corlette was born John Hubert Christian Corlette on 21 June 1911 , and died 9 December 1977 .
Yaakov Herzog ( Hebrew : יעקב הרצוג‎ , 11 December 1921 -- 9 March 1972 ) ( 50 ) was an Israeli diplomat .
Alban Köhler ( 1 March 1874 - 26 February 1947 ) was a German radiologist .
Solomon Skuza ( 1956 - -1995 ) , also known as Jah Solo was a Zimbabwean musician , one of the most popular to come out of Plumtree .
Thomas William Lancaster , M.A. ( 1787 - -1869 ) was an English churchman and academic , vicar of Banbury and fellow of Queen 's College , Oxford .
Gundemaro Pinióliz ( died c. 1012 ) , was a noble from the Kingdom of León , the ancestor of one of the most important Asturian lineages of the Middle Ages , and most likely the great - grandfather of Jimena Díaz , wife of Rodrigo Díaz de Vivar , el Cid .
Kilian of Cologne , Irish Abbot , died 19 January 1003 Kilian was a native of Ireland .
Count Stanisław Dunin - Wąsowicz ( 1785 in Volhynia -- 1864 in Paris ) was a Polish general of the November Uprising , Captain of the 1st Polish Lancers and Napoleon 's bodyguard and aide - de - camp during his 1812 Russian Campaign .
Lionel Hale ( 26 October 1909 -- 1 January 1977 ) was an English critic , broadcaster and playwright .
Halil Hamid Pasha , also Halil Hamit Paşa ( 1736 - -1785 ) was the grand vizier of the Ottoman Empire from 31 December 1782 to 30 April 1785 .
Reuben Bosworth ( ca.1797 -- 26 July 1883 ) was a watch and clockmaker in Nottingham .
Brne Karnarutić , 1515 - 1573 ) was a Croatian Renaissance poet .
Graeme Fellowes ( 29 January 1934 -- 24 January 2013 ) was a former professional Australian rules footballer who played for Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the late 1950s and early 1960s .
Calvin J. Spann ( November 28 , 1924 -- September 6 , 2015 ) was an original Tuskegee Airman and fighter pilot with the 100th Fighter Squadron of the 332nd Fighter Group .
William II , Lord of Egmond or Willem II , heer van Egmond ( c. 1230 -- 30 March 1304 ) was a ruling Lord of Egmond .
Messenger Monsey ( baptised 30 October 1694 , died 26 December 1788 ) was an English physician and humourist who became physician to the Royal Hospital , Chelsea , a home for injured and elderly soldiers .
Sylvanus Charles Thorp Hanley ( 1819 - -1899 ) was a British conchologist and malacologist who published the first book on shells using the then new technique of photographs .
Eric Sollee ( 8 September 1926 - 30 June 2008 ) was an American fencer and fencing coach .
Graham Michael Lesch ( 1936 - 2007 ) was a South African activist , who fought for human rights from all angles .
Una Lucy Fielding ( 20 May 1888 -- 11 August 1969 ) was an Australian neuroanatomist .
Henry Attfield ( 1756 -- c. 1829 ) was an English cricketer who made his first known appearance in the 1773 season .
Laura Elenes ( 1933 - -2005 ) was a Mexican painter , sculptor and printmaker .
Rhys Nanmor ( fl . 1480 - -1513 ) was a Welsh language poet who lived in Nanmor , near Beddgelert in North Wales .
Stanley Ridges ( 17 July 1890 -- 22 April 1951 ) was a British - born actor who made his mark in films by playing a wide assortment of character parts .
Stanisław Szostak ( 14 January 1898 -- 11 February 1961 ) was a colonel of the Polish Armoured Corps .
Malik Ghulam Farid ( 1897 - -1977 ) , was a notable Ahmadiyya scholar .
Launcelot Brown ( 13 January 1748 - 28 February 1802 ) was an English politician .
Tracy McCleary ( died 2003 ) , was the leader of the Royal Men of Rhythm and a prominent part of the Baltimore jazz scene .
Honoré Chavée ( 1815 - -1877 ) was a Belgian Indo - Europeanist and Semitologist who started natural linguistics in France .
F. Alton Everest ( 1909 - -2005 ) was an American acoustical engineer , a cofounder of the American Scientific Affiliation , and its first president .
The Rt Rev Rennie MacInnes ( 23 July 1870 -- 24 December 1931 ) was a Bishop in the Anglican Church in the first third of the twentieth century .
John Ward or Birdy ( c. 1553 -- 1622 ) , also known as Jack Ward , was a notorious English pirate around the turn of the 17th century who later became a Barbary Corsair operating out of Tunis during the early 17th century .
Mutsuro Nakazono ( December 20 , 1918 -- 1994 ) ( first name also spelled `` Mitsuro '' or `` Masahiro '' ) was a Japanese acupuncturist , an Oriental medicine practitioner and a 7th dan Aikikai aikido master with a strong judo background .
César Gemayel ( b. Ain al Touffaha near Bikfaya , Lebanon in 1898 died in Beirut , Lebanon in 1958 ) was a famous Lebanese painter .
Adam Murimuth ( c. 1274 -- 1347 ) was an English ecclesiastic and chronicler .
Sir John Cloberry ( c. 1625 -- January 1688 ) was an English soldier and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1660 and 1685 .
Chester Edward Ide ( June 13 , 1878 - -March 18 , 1944 ) was an American composer and music teacher , primarily known for his operettas , some major instrumental works , and his participatory teaching methods .
René Goormaghtigh ( 13 October 1893 , Ostende -- 10 February 1960 , Ixelles ) was a Belgian engineer , after whom the Goormaghtigh Conjecture is named .
Alexandru Custov ( 8 May 1954 -- 20 March 2008 ) was a Romanian footballer .
William Rudolph ( died 27 May 1975 ) was an American film technician , who received an Academy Award for Technical Achievement .
Joseph Oscar Irwin ( 17 December 1898 -- 27 July 1982 ) British statistician who advanced the use of statistical methods in biological assay and other fields of laboratory medicine .
Martin Dunsford ( 1744 - -1807 ) was an English merchant and Dissenter , known as an antiquarian and radical politician .
Ronald Phillip Tanaka ( 1944 - -2007 ) was a Japanese - American poet and editor .
Merkelis Giedraitis ( Polish : Melchior Giedroyć ; ca . 1536 -- 6 April 1609 in Alsėdžiai ) was Bishop of Samogitia from 1576 to 1609 .
Philip H. Rhinelander ( January 1 , 1908 -- March 24 , 1987 ) , was a philosopher , Stanford professor emeritus , and former dean of the Stanford University School of Humanities and Sciences .
Salvatore Ferragamo ( 5 June 1898 -- 7 August 1960 ) was an Italian shoe designer .
Febo Conti ( 25 December 1926 -- 16 December 2012 ) was an Italian TV and radio presenter and actor .
William John Law ( 1786 - -1869 ) was a British judge of the 19th century .
James Colyer ( ca . 1560 - 14 July 1597 ) was an English politician .
Anona Winn MBE ( born Anona Edna Wilkins , 5 January 1904 -- 2 February 1994 ) was an Australian - born actress , broadcaster and singer , who spent most of her career in the UK .
Marie Pilátová ( 14 May 1921 -- 20 January 2015 ) was a Czech actress known for her role in the comedy trilogy Slunce , seno , jahody , Slunce , seno a pár facek and Slunce , seno , erotika ; directed by Zdeněk Troška .
Attilio Pavesi ( 1 October 1910 -- 2 August 2011 ) was an Italian cyclist and Olympic champion .
Abraham Pasha , originally Abraham Eramyan , ( Istanbul , 1833 - Istanbul , 1918 ) was an Ottoman civil servant and diplomat of Armenian origin .
Maria Katarina Öhrn , later Maria Katarina Berlin , ( 1756 -- 8 November 1783 in Stockholm ) was a Swedish stage actress and singer .
Joseph Kinghorn ( 1766 - -1832 ) was an English particular Baptist minister in Norwich .
Edwin Ferdinand Lee ( 10 July 1884 -- 14 September 1948 ) was a Missionary Bishop of the Methodist Episcopal Church and The Methodist Church , elected in 1928 .
Nikephoros Melissenos ( Greek : Νικηφόρος Μελισσηνός , ca . 1045 -- 17 November 1104 ) , Latinized as Nicephorus Melissenus , was a Byzantine general and aristocrat .
Artur Axmann ( 18 February 1913 -- 24 October 1996 ) was the German Nazi national leader ( Reichsjugendführer ) of the Hitler Youth ( Hitlerjugend ) from 1940 to the war 's end in 1945 .
Florence Nagle ( 26 October 1894 -- 30 October 1988 ) was a trainer and breeder of racehorses , a breeder of pedigree dogs , and an active feminist .
Elspeth Champcommunal ( 1888 -- 10 November 1976 ) was a British fashion designer and the first editor of Vogue in Britain .
Adolfo Carlo Barone ( 1861 -- 1936 ) , also known as Carlo Adolfo Barone , was an Italian painter .
Henrik Otto von Fieandt ( 1762 - -1823 ) was a Swedish Colonel who fought in the 1788 - -90 war with Russia .
Alan Senitt ( 26 December 1978 -- 9 July 2006 ) was a British political activist whose murder in Washington , DC garnered media attention .
Simeon Fox ( or Foxe ) , M.D. ( 1568 - -1642 ) was an English physician , who became President of the College of Physicians .
Géza Vermes ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈɡeːzɒ ˈvɛrmɛʃ ) ; 22 June 1924 -- 8 May 2013 ) was a British scholar of Jewish Hungarian origin -- one who also served as a Catholic priest in his youth -- and writer on religious history , particularly Jewish and Christian .
Frederick T. Kemper ( 1816 - 1881 ) was the founder of the school that later became Kemper Military School in Boonville , Missouri .
Jerome Corbet died in 1598 and was buried in the family chapel at Moreton Corbet parish church on 30 July .
Sir Benjamin Dawson , 1st Baronet ( 26 September 1878 -- 25 September 1966 ) was a British textile manufacturer .
Edward Buckton Lamb ( 1806 - -1869 ) was a British architect who exhibited at the Royal Academy from 1824 .
Helen Hitchings ( born 17 June 1920 , died 4 July 2002 ) was a New Zealand art dealer , best known for the short - lived but influential eponymous dealer gallery she opened in Wellington in 1949 .
Yiannis Moralis ( Greek : Γιάννης Μόραλης ; also transliterated Yannis Moralis or Giannis Moralis ; 23 April 1916 -- 20 December 2009 ) was an important Greek visual artist and part of the so - called `` Generation of the ' 30s '' .
Ma Su ( 190 - -228 ) , courtesy name Youchang , was a military general and strategist of the state of Shu Han in the Three Kingdoms period .
Gordon Beningfield ( 31 October 1936 , London -- 4 May 1998 ) was a wildlife artist and broadcaster .
Nikolaos Vorvolakos ( Greek : Νικόλαος Βορβολάκος , 1931 -- 17 April 2014 ) was a Hellenic Army officer who served as head of the Cypriot National Guard from February 1993 to April 1998 .
Inger Louise Valle ( 28 November 1921 -- 21 May 2006 ) was a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party , particularly noted for her efforts to reform the Norwegian penal system .
Marquess Su of Zhao ( Traditional Chinese : 趙肅侯 ) ( died 326 BCE , reigned 349 BCE -- 326 BCE ) reigned in the State of Zhao during the early Warring States period of Chinese history .
Stephan Jakob Neher ( b. Ebnat , 24 July 1829 ; d. Nordhausen , 7 October 1902 ) was a Church historian .
William Maitland Woods ( 4 January 1864 -- 6 February 1927 ) was an Anglican clergyman and a military chaplain in Queensland , Australia .
William D. Reynolds ( 1867 - -1951 ) was an American Southern Presbyterian ( PCUS ) missionary and Bible translator in Korea .
Charles Cornwallis , 2nd Marquess Cornwallis ( 19 October 1774 -- 9 August 1823 ) , styled Viscount Brome until 1805 , was a British Tory politician .
Bill Elston ( 4 December 1897 -- 26 September 1968 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Anna Blackburne ( 1726 -- 30 December 1793 ) was an English naturalist .
Dragan Maksimović ( 7 February 1949 - 4 February 2001 ) , nicknamed Maks , was a Serbian actor .
Colin Wark ( 1896 - -1939 ) was a British composer of film scores .
Dr. Badri Nath Prasad ( 1899 - 1966 ) was an Indian parliamentarian .
Sattar Beheshti ( Persian : ستار بهشتی‎‎ ) was an Iranian blogger who died in early November 2012 several days after being arrested by the Iranian Cyber Police unit for criticizing the government of the Islamic Republic on Facebook , and after making a signed complaint of being tortured while in custody .
Kim Mills ( 1931 -- 28 August 2006 ) was a British television director .
Hendrik van der Borcht II ( 8 March 1614 , Frankenthal - 29 June 1676 ) was a German Baroque painter .
Saint Romaric ( died 653 ) was a Frankish nobleman who lived in Austrasia from the late 6th century until the middle of the 7th century .
Charlie Case ( August 27 , 1858 --1916 ) was a blackface comedian in America who wrote and sang vaudeville parodies of the 19th century ballad style .
Josias Howe ( c.1611 -- 28 August 1701 ) was an English divine .
Gojčin Crnojević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Гојчин Црнојевић , 1398 - -d . after 1451 ) was a Lord of Zeta , initially as a vassal of the Serbian Despotate until he revolted against Despot Stefan Lazarević .
Hugh Enes Blackmore ( 1 October 1863 -- 21 May 1945 ) was a British opera and concert singer and actor .
George Bertram Cockburn OBE ( 8 January 1872 -- 25 February 1931 ) was a research chemist who became an aviation pioneer .
Maxwell Irvine ( 28 February 1939 - 24 March 2012 ) was a British theoretical physicist and university administrator , who served as Vice - Chancellor of the Universities of Aberdeen and Birmingham .
John II , Duke of Opava - Ratibor ( also known as John II of Troppau or John the Iron ; Czech : Jan II . Opavský or Hanuš Ferreus ; after 1365 -- 1424 ) was Duke of Opava - Racibórz ( Ratibor ) , Krnov and Bruntál .
Léon Moreaux ( 10 March 1852 -- 11 November 1921 ) was a French sports shooter and Olympian who competed in pistol and rifle shooting in the late 19th century and early 20th century .
Narayan Rao Pawar ( 1925 -- 12 December 2010 ) was an Indian independence activist and member of Arya Samaj .
Denis O'Gorman ( 28 August 1914 -- 1 May 2005 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a left corner - back and as a goalkeeper for the Tipperary senior team .
Liam Reidy ( 1924 - -2012 ) was an Irish sportsperson .
Inji Aflatoun ( 1924 - -1989 ) was an Egyptian painter and activist in the women 's movement .
John Nisbet , Lord Dirleton ( c. 1609 - -1687 ) was a Scottish judge .
Patrick Calhoun ( March 21 , 1856 -- June 16 , 1943 ) was the grandson of John C. Calhoun and Floride Calhoun , and the great - grandson of his namesake Patrick Calhoun .
Julius Christian Mergenthaler ( 8 November 1884 - † 11 September 1980 ) , was a Nazi German politician , member of the Reichstag and Württemberg Landtag , Ministerpräsident of Württemberg and Culture Minister .
Klaus Tschira ( 7 December 1940 -- 31 March 2015 ) was a German entrepreneur .
Bernard Delaire ( 28 March 1899 -- 1 October 2007 ) was a French naval veteran of the First World War and one of the last six identified French veterans .
Arthur Elphinstone , 6th Lord Balmerino ( 1688 -- 18 August 1746 ) was a Scottish nobleman and an officer in the Jacobite army .
Mary de Vere ( died circa 24 June 1624 ) , whose married names were Bertie and Hart , was a noblewoman of the sixteenth century .
Count Alessandro Contini - Bonacossi ( 18 March 1878 - 22 October 1955 ) was an Italian politician , art collector , dealer and philatelist .
Eric Aldwinckle ( 22 January 1909 -- 13 January 1980 ) was a Canadian war artist , designer and illustrator .
Gul Rahman ( died 20 November 2002 ) was a suspected Afghan militant and torture victim .
John Martin Munro Kerr ( 5 December 1868 -- 7 October 1960 ) was Regius Professor of Midwifery at the University of Glasgow from 1927 to 1934 .
Giovanni de Macque ( Giovanni de Maque , Jean de Macque ) ( 1548/1550 -- September 1614 ) was a Netherlandish composer of the late Renaissance and early Baroque , who spent almost his entire life in Italy .
Merten de Keyser ( born Martin Lempereur ; died 1536 ) was a 16th - century French printer and publisher working mainly in Antwerp , who printed the first complete French and the first complete English Bible translations as well as a number of works by English Protestant authors .
Adelchi Bianchi ( 1918 - 1968 ) was an Italian director , screenwriter , producer and cinematographer .
Hood Hanway Christian ( 23 July 1784 -- 31 August 1849 ) was a British naval officer who reached the rank of Rear - Admiral .
The Reverend D'Ewes Coke ( 1747 - 12 April 1811 ) was rector of Pinxton and South Normanton in Derbyshire , a colliery owner and philanthropist .
Birger Eklund ( 22 October 1929 -- 6 December 2015 ) ) was a Swedish footballer .
Henry Jerome de Salis , DD , FRS , FSA , ( 20 August 1740 - 2 May 1810 ) was an English churchman .
Manasses II , Count of Rethel ( died 1032 ) was a son of Manasses of Omont and his wife , Castricia .
William Wadsworth Evans ( October 5 , 1886-November 1972 ) is an American Republican Party politician who served in the New Jersey General Assembly from 1919 to 1924 .
Tom Vernon ( 23 April 1939 -- 11 September 2013 ) was a British broadcaster and writer , best known as the titular `` Fat Man '' of a number of popular travelogues .
John Daborne ( c1500 - Sept 1548 ) was a merchant and alderman of Guildford Surrey .
Massimiliano Massimo ( ? - 1911 ) was an Italian Jesuit .
Jorge Cepernic ( 23 February 1915 -- 18 July 2010 ) was an Argentine politician and Governor of Santa Cruz Province between 1973 and 1974 .
Charlotte Townshend , Viscountess Townshend ( died 3 September 1770 ) , suo jure 15th Baroness Ferrers of Chartley and 7th Baroness Compton , known as Lady Charlotte Compton until 1749 and as Lady Ferrers of Chartley from 1749 to 1764 , was a British peer .
John Barham Day ( 1793 - -1860 ) was a British Jockey and Trainer .
Robert Baldwin Hayward ( 1829 - -1903 ) was an English educator and mathematician .
Moisés Bensabat Amzalak ( 4 October 1892 - 6 June 1978 ) was a Portuguese scholar and economist .
Alejandro Christophersen ( 1866 --1946 ) was an Argentine architect and artist of Norwegian descent who designed many important buildings in the city of Buenos Aires , including the renowned Anchorena Palace .
Ou Zhen ( 歐震 , 1899 - -1969 ) , or Ou Chen , was a KMT army general from Qujiang , Guangdong .
Reuben Colburn ( 1740 - -1818 ) was a shipbuilder in Pittston , Maine who made great contributions to the American side in the Revolutionary War .
Robert Rich , 2nd Earl of Warwick ( 5 June 1587 -- 19 April 1658 ) was an English colonial administrator , admiral , and Puritan .
Jerg Ratgeb ( also Jörg ) ( c.1480 - -1526 ) was a German painter and contemporary of Dürer .
George Parker Winship , A. M. ( 29 July 1871 - 22 June 1952 ) was an American librarian and author , born at Bridgewater , Mass. He was educated at Harvard where he graduated in 1893 .
Sardar Bahadur Arjan Singh Chahal ( 1839 - -1908 ) was a Sikh Chahal Jat of Chahal village in Amritsar in what is now the Indian state of Punjab .
Marie Dainton ( 8 June c. 1881 -- 1 February 1938 ) was an actress of the Victorian and Edwardian eras who appeared regularly in both music halls and in the legitimate theatre .
Andrew Newport JP ( 30 November 1622 -- 11 September 1699 ) , styled The Honourable from 1642 , was an English Tory politician , courtier and royalist .
Melvin Sabshin , M.D. ( 1925 - 2011 ) was an American psychiatrist , the Medical Director of the American Psychiatric Association from 1974 to 1997 , and a leader in psychiatry placing it firmly within the discipline of medicine .
Sir John Plunket ( c.1497 - -1582 ) was an Irish politician and judge who held the office of Lord Chief Justice of Ireland .
Aaron ha - Levi Oettingen was a Galician rabbi ; born about the beginning of the eighteenth century ; died in Lemberg about 1769 .
Selbach mac Ferchair ( died 730 ) was king of the Cenél Loairn and of Dál Riata .
Sir Francis Sacheverel Darwin ( 17 June 1786 -- 6 November 1859 ) was a physician and traveller who was knighted by King George IV .
Urban Runner ( originally subtitled Lost In Town ) is a French produced computer game developed by Coktel Vision and published by Sierra On - line .
Skyfox is a 1984 action computer game developed by Ray Tobey and published by Electronic Arts .
Ski or Die is a 1990 winter sports game by Electronic Arts for the Amiga , NES , MS - DOS and Commodore 64 .

Wizardry 8 is the eighth and final title in the Wizardry series of role - playing video games by Sir - Tech Canada .
Pocket Legends is an iOS and Android mobile 3D MMO developed by Spacetime Studios .
Crush , Crumble and Chomp ! is a 1981 computer game from Epyx .
Honeycomb Beat is a puzzle game developed by Hudson Soft for the Nintendo DS . It features touch screen gameplay and more than 200 unique puzzles .
HB Arcade Cards is a video game by HB Studios consisting of a collection of six card games ( rummy , hearts , euchre , canasta , cribbage , and solitaire ) for WiiWare .
Fieldrunners 2 is a tower defense video game , the sequel to Fieldrunners , developed by Subatomic Studios .
Bejeweled Twist is a puzzle game of the Bejeweled series created and published by PopCap Games , released on October 17 , 2008 .
Prior to the ArcGIS suite , Esri had focused its software development on the command line Arc / INFO workstation program and several Graphical User Interface - based products such as the ArcView GIS 3.x desktop program .
Toyota Celica GT Rally ( sometimes abbreviated as GT Rally ) is a racing computer game developed and published by Gremlin Graphics Software Ltd. ( later Gremlin Interactive ) released for the Commodore Amiga , Amstrad CPC and the ZX Spectrum .
Tournament of Legends ( formerly known as Gladiator A.D. ) is a fighting video game developed by High Voltage Software for the Wii console .
Homeworld 2 is a real - time strategy computer game sequel to Homeworld , developed by Relic Entertainment and released in 2003 by now defunct publisher Sierra Entertainment .
LightWave 3D is a 3D computer graphics software developed by NewTek .
Bugzilla is used , among others , by the Mozilla Foundation , WebKit , Linux kernel , FreeBSD , GNOME , KDE , Apache , Red Hat , MediaWiki , Eclipse and LibreOffice .
Star Trek Online is a massively multiplayer online role - playing game ( MMORPG ) developed by Cryptic Studios based on the Star Trek series created by Gene Roddenberry .
F.E.A.R. First Encounter Assault Recon is a survival horror first - person shooter developed by Monolith Productions and published by Sierra Entertainment .
Collapse ! is a series of award - winning tile - matching puzzle video games by GameHouse , a software company in Seattle , Washington .
The Apple A7 is a 64-bit system on a chip ( SoC ) designed by Apple Inc. It first appeared in the iPhone 5S , which was introduced on September 10 , 2013 .
The Elder Scrolls Online is a massively multiplayer online role - playing video game developed by ZeniMax Online Studios .
M1 Tank Platoon is a tactical simulation of tank warfare , released by MicroProse for the Commodore Amiga , Atari ST and DOS in 1989 .
Peek - A - Boo Poker is a video game made by Hacker International and distributed by Panesian in 1991 as one of three pornographic video games the company made for the Nintendo Entertainment System , the other two being Bubble Bath Babes and Hot Slots .
PixelJunk Shooter 2 is a video game developed by Q - Games for the PlayStation 3 .
Mozilla Firefox ( or simply Firefox ) is a free and open - source web browser developed by the Mozilla Foundation and its subsidiary , the Mozilla Corporation .
Crayon Physics Deluxe is a computer video puzzle game designed by Petri Purho and released on January 7 , 2009 .
Mini - Putt is a simulation of miniature golf developed by Artech Digital Entertainment and released by Accolade for various home computers and consoles since 1987 .
In January / February 2005 a member of the game 's community , Stuart `` Stucuk '' Carey , asked Altar Interactive ( Now known as Altar Games ) for permission to maintain Original War with fan - made patches .
On September 15 , 2014 , Microsoft announced a deal to buy Mojang and the ownership of the Minecraft intellectual property for US$ 2.5 billion ; the acquisition was completed on November 6 , 2014 .
Mist of Chaos ( ミスト オブ カオス , misuto obu kaosu ) is a strategy role - playing game co - developed by Idea Factory and Neverland Co. for the PlayStation 3 video game console .
The Bugs Bunny Crazy Castle 2 , known in Japan as Mickey Mouse II ( ミッキーマウスII ) and known in Europe either as Hugo or simply Mickey Mouse , is a video game developed by Kemco for the Game Boy .
Lords of the Rising Sun is a 1989 video game by Cinemaware , game design and art by Doug Barnett , released for the Amiga among other systems .
Zarlor Mercenary is an action game for the Atari Lynx handheld console , released by Epyx .
NASCAR Legends is a NASCAR racing simulator developed by Papyrus Design Group for Windows - based personal computers and released by Sierra Entertainment in late 1999 .
Project Gotham Racing 2 ( PGR2 for short ) is a racing game for the Xbox , developed by Bizarre Creations and published by Microsoft .
Grow Home is an adventure platform video game developed by Ubisoft Reflections and published by Ubisoft .
Al sur de Granada ( English title : South from Granada ) is a 2003 film written and directed by Fernando Colomo , based on the book by Gerald Brenan .
Karulina Kare ( Kannada : ಕರುಳಿನ ಕರೆ ) is a 1970 Kannada romantic drama film directed and written by Puttanna Kanagal .
The Breton National Party ( French Parti National Breton , or PNB ) was a nationalist party in Brittany that existed from 1931 to 1944 .
The Principality of Valona ( 1346 - -1417 ) was a medieval principality in Albania , roughly encompassing the territories of the modern counties of Vlorë ( Valona ) , Fier , and Berat .
Professionally , Jean - Marc Jézéquel worked as a computer scientist at the University of Rennes , France .
Simeon Djankov also holds a 1997 doctorate from the University of Michigan , on the topic `` Three Essays on the Economics of Transition . ''
Candace Smith attended the University of Dayton on a full academic scholarship and graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in Psychology and a minor in Communications .
Mushirul Hasan did his M. A. from the Aligarh Muslim University in 1969 .
Bradon McDonald is a graduate of the Juilliard School ( 1997 ) and a recipient of the Princess Grace Award and a National ARTS Foundation award .
Mike Bryan played for Stanford University in 1997 and 1998 , where he helped the Cardinal win back - to - back NCAA team championships .
In 1966 , on the news of his father 's death , the then 21-year - old Azim Premji returned home from Stanford University , where he was studying engineering , to take charge of Wipro .
Jack R. Anderson was appointed Director of Bands at the University of Pittsburgh in 1995 after serving as assistant director at Pitt for 9 years .
Yosef Hayim Yerushalmi ( May 20 , 1932 -- December 8 , 2009 ) was the Salo Wittmayer Baron Professor of Jewish History , Culture and Society at Columbia University , a position he held from 1980 to 2008 .

Domenico Fisichella ( born 15 September 1935 ) is an Italian academic and politician , who served as culture minister in the first cabinet of Silvio Berlusconi from 1994 to 1995 .

Quizquiz later commanded Atahualpa 's troops in the battles of Vilcaconga , Cuzco ( both 1533 ) and Maraycalla ( 1534 ) , ultimately being bested by the Spanish forces in both accounts .
Iginio Straffi ( born 30 May 1965 ) is an Italian animation director , most famous for being the founder and CEO of Rainbow S.r.l . , as well as the creator of its most famous product , the Winx Club series .
Jaroslav Průšek ( simplified Chinese : 普实克 ; traditional Chinese : 普實克 ; pinyin : pǔshíkè , 1906 - -1980 ) was a Czech sinologist .
Francisco Mariano Nipho ( 1719 Alcañiz -- 1803 Madrid ) was a Spanish writer and journalist .
Vicenç Vilarrubla Solsona ( born January 31 , 1981 in la Seu d'Urgell ) is a Catalan Spanish cross - country skier from Bellestar ( Alt Urgell ) who has competed in the World Cup since 2001 .
William Wigram ( 1780 -- 8 January 1858 ) was an English Member of Parliament for Irish constituencies .
Gian Vincenzo Pinelli ( 1535 -- 31 August 1601 ) was an Italian humanist , born in Naples and known as a savant and a mentor of Galileo .
Frank Arthur Swinnerton ( 12 August 1884 -- 6 November 1982 ) was an English novelist , critic , biographer and essayist .
Ludwig Christoph Heinrich Hölty ( 21 December 1748 -- 1 September 1776 ) was a German poet , known especially for his ballads .
John Danyel or John Daniel ( Baptized 6 November 1564 -- c. 1626 ) was an English lute player and songwriter .
Alfonso Ungría is a Spanish screenwriter and film director .
Gilles Châtelet ( 2 February 1944 -- 11 June 1999 ) was a French philosopher and mathematician .
Mikša Pelegrinović ( or Michiele Pelegrinovich ) ( c. 1500 -- 26 December 1562 ) was a Croatian poet from Dalmatia .
Estefanía Muñiz Villa ( León , 8 January 1974 ) is a Spanish film director , scriptwriter and critic .
Johannes Schaaf ( born 7 April 1933 in Stuttgart ) is a German film , theatre and opera director and actor .
James Round JP ( 6 April 1842 -- 25 December 1916 ) was an English first - class cricketer and Conservative politician .
Catherine Storr ( born Catherine Cole ; 21 July 1913 -- 8 January 2001 , ) was an English children 's writer , best known for her novel Marianne Dreams and for a series of books about a wolf ineptly pursuing a young girl , beginning with Clever Polly and the Stupid Wolf .
Hugo Becker ( born Jean Otto Eric Hugo Becker , 13 February 1863 , died 30 July 1941 ) was a prominent German cellist , cello teacher , and composer .
Daniel Boone was of English and Welsh ancestry .
Sir Walter Baldwin Spencer KCMG ( 23 June 1860 -- 14 July 1929 ) was an English - Australian biologist and anthropologist .
Teodor Bujnicki ( 1907 - 1944 ) was a Polish poet , writing for `` Żagary '' magazine .
Alex Soler - Roig ( Catalan pronunciation : ( ˈaɫəks suˈɫe ˈrɔtʃ ) ; born 29 October 1931 ) is a former racing driver from Barcelona , Spain .
Sir Walter Raleigh ( /ˈrɔːli/ , /ˈræli/ , or /ˈrɑːli/ ; circa 1554 -- 29 October 1618 ) was an English landed gentleman , writer , poet , soldier , politician , courtier , spy , and explorer .
Dagny Juel - Przybyszewska ( 8 June 1867 -- 5 June 1901 ) was a Norwegian writer , famous for her liaisons with various prominent artists , and for the dramatic circumstances of her death .
Thorvald Steen ( born 9 January 1954 ) is a Norwegian writer and government scholar .
Hermann Allmers ( 11 February 1821 , Rechtenfleth -- 9 March 1902 ) was a German poet .
Jan Woleński ( also known as Jan Hertrich - Woleński ; born 21 September 1940 ) is a Polish philosopher , specialist in the history of Lwów - Warsaw school and in analytical philosophy .
Michel Ledoux ( born 1958 ) is a French mathematician , specializing in probability theory .
Gilbert Montagné ( born 28 December 1951 in Paris ) is a French musician from the Ménilmontant neighborhood in Paris and Bourbonnais , a pianist , organist , and a singer .
John William Van Druten ( 1 June 1901 -- 19 December 1957 ) was an English playwright and theatre director , known professionally as John Van Druten .
Giovanni Kessler ( Trento , June 11 , 1956 ) is an Italian prosecutor .
Albert Boadella Oncins ( born Barcelona , Spain , 1943 ) is a Spanish actor , director and playwright and one of the founders of the well - known theatre company Els Joglars .
Emilio Lledó Íñigo ( Seville , 5 November , 1927 ) is a Spanish philosopher .
Alexandre Cabanel ( French : ( kabanɛl ) ; 28 September 1823 -- 23 January 1889 ) was a French painter born in Montpellier , Hérault .
Michel Duguet ( born 1961 ) is a French Scrabble player who won the French World Scrabble Championships five times during the 1980s .
Arild Nyquist ( 6 March 1937 -- 21 December 2004 ) was a Norwegian novelist , lyricist , writer of children 's books and musician .
Miguel García Vivancos ( April 19 , 1895 , Mazarrón , Region of Murcia -- January 23 , 1972 , Córdoba ) was a Spanish Naïve painter and anarchist .
Barbara Matera ( born 9 December 1981 ) is an Italian television announcer , actress and MEP for the centre - right The People of Freedom ( PdL ) party .
Gerry Scotti ( born August 7 , 1956 ) is an Italian television presenter , actor and former member of the Italian Parliament .
Cristòfor Taltabull ( 28 July 1888 - 1 May 1964 ) was a Catalan composer and pedagogue who was instrumental in the reconstruction of musical life in Catalonia after the Spanish Civil War .
George Călinescu ( Romanian : ( ˈd͡ʒe̯ord͡ʒe kəliˈnesku ) ; 19 June 1899 -- 12 March 1965 ) was a Romanian literary critic , historian , novelist , academician and journalist , and a writer of classicist and humanist tendencies .
Rihards Dubra ( born 28 February 1964 in Riga , Latvian SSR , Soviet Union ) is a Latvian composer .

María Abradelo ( born María Emilia Bastante Patón on October 10 , 1969 in La Jana , Castelló ) is a Spanish actress , and daughter of singer Isabel Patton .

Claude Traunecker ( born 1943 in Mulhouse ) is a French Egyptologist , professor at the University of Strasbourg and researcher at the CNRS .
Ernst Eckstein ( 6 February 1845 , Giessen , Grand Duchy of Hesse --18 November 1900 ) was a German humorist , novelist and poet .

Miguel Sáenz Sagaseta de Ilúrdoz ( Larache , Spanish Morocco , 1932 ) is a Spanish translator .

Miguel Linares Cólera ( born 30 September 1982 in Zaragoza , Aragon ) is a Spanish professional footballer who plays for Real Oviedo as a centre forward .
Paolo Boselli ( June 8 , 1838 -- March 10 , 1932 ) was an Italian politician who served as the 34th Prime Minister of Italy during World War I.

Sister Christina Ebner , O.P. , ( also Christine ) , ( 26 March 1277 -- 27 December 1356 ) was a German Dominican nun , writer and mystic .

Klausbernd Vollmar ( born 22 November 1946 ) is a German scientific psychologist ( Diplompsychologe ) specializing in the language of symbols in dreams , art and advertisements .
Emilio Herrera Linares ( February 13 , 1879 , Granada , Spain -- September 13 1967 , Geneve , Switzerland ) ) was a Spanish military engineer and physicist .
Raymond Adolphe Séré de Rivières ( 20 May 1815 -- 16 February 1895 ) was a French military engineer and general whose ideas revolutionized the design of fortifications in France .
Friedrich Adolf Krummacher ( July 13 , 1767 -- April 14 , 1845 ) was a German Reformed theologian and a writer of devotional poetry and prose .
Gautier d'Arras ( died c. 1185 , Arras ) was a Flemish or French trouvère .
Anna Åkerhielm or Åkerhjelm , née Anna Agriconia , ( 1642 - -11 February 1698 ) , was a Swedish writer and traveller .
Alix Joffroy ( 16 December 1844 in Stainville -- 24 November 1908 ) was a French neurologist and psychiatrist remembered for describing Joffroy 's sign .
Sibylle Blanc ( born January 3 , 1974 in Aubonne , Vaud ) is a French - speaking Swiss actress and director who is actively involved in theatrical , film , television and radio productions in her native Switzerland as well as in nearby France .
Azra Erhat ( 6 June 1915 -- 6 September 1982 ) was a Turkish author , archaeologist , academician and translator .
Maria Gabriela Stefania Korwin - Piotrowska ( 1857 - -1921 ) , known as Gabriela Zapolska , was a Polish novelist , playwright , naturalist writer , feuilletonist , theatre critic and stage actress .

Luc - Olivier Merson ( 21 May 1846 -- 13 November 1920 ) was a French academic painter and illustrator also known for his postage stamp and currency designs .
Kaarlo Juho Ståhlberg ( January 28 , 1865 -- September 22 , 1952 ) was a Finnish jurist and academic , who played a central role in the drafting of the Constitution of Finland in 1919 .
Lieutenant - General Edmund Maine ( 20 January 1633 -- 25 April 1711 ) was an English soldier and politician .
Pierre Chenal ( December 5 , 1904 -- December 23 , 1990 ) was a French director and screenwriter who flourished in the 1930s , and was best known for film noir thrillers such as the 1937 film L’Alibi , where he worked with Erich von Stroheim and Louis Jouvet .
John Praed ( c 1657 -- 10 October 1717 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1708 and 1713 .
Auguste Marie Émile Laure ( June 3 , 1881 -- 1957 ) was a French général d'armée ( Army general ) .
Otto Devrient ( born 3 October 1838 in Berlin ; † 23 June 1894 in Stettin ) was a German actor and playwright .
Wentworth Webster ( 16 June 1828 -- 2 April 1907 ) was an Anglican clergyman , scholar , and collector of folk tales of the Basque Country .
Georges Glaeser ( 1918 - -2002 ) was a French mathematician who was director of the IREM of Strasbourg .

Fausto Pirandello ( 1899 - -1975 ) was an Italian painter belonging to the modern movement of the Scuola romana ( Roman School ) .

Henry Richard Farquharson ( 1857 -- 19 April 1895 ) was an English landowner and Conservative politician .
Louis - Antoine Ranvier ( 2 October 1835 -- 22 March 1922 ) was a French physician , pathologist , anatomist and histologist , who discovered nodes of Ranvier , regularly spaced discontinuities of the myelin sheath , occurring at varying intervals along the length of a nerve fiber .

In mathematics , a Dedekind cut , named after Richard Dedekind , is a partition of the rational numbers into two non - empty sets A and B , such that all elements of A are less than all elements of B , and A contains no greatest element .
