The Citroën Dyane is an economy car / supermini produced by the French automaker Citroën from 1967 to 1983 .
Minnie D. Craig ( née Davenport , 1883 - 1966 ) was an American legislator , notable as the first female speaker of a state House of Representatives in the United States .
Nancy Abramson was the first female president of the Cantors Assembly , an international professional organization of cantors associated with Conservative Judaism ; she took up that office in 2013 .
Naim Süleymanoğlu ( born Naim Suleimanov ( Bulgarian : Наим Сюлейманов ) on January 23 , 1967 ) is a Turkish World and Olympic Champion in weightlifting .
The English Premier Ice Hockey League ( EPIHL ) is a developmental ice hockey league of 10 teams , all of which are based in England .
Catherine Howard ( c.1523 -- 13 February 1542 ) was Queen of England from 1540 until 1541 , as the fifth wife of Henry VIII . Catherine married Henry VIII on 28 July 1540 , at Oatlands Palace , in Surrey , almost immediately after the annulment of his marriage to Anne of Cleves was arranged .
Sara Hall has been married to U.S. Olympic marathoner Ryan Hall since 2005 .
Anna Karen lives in Essex , and was married to actor / comedian Terry Duggan until he died in 2008 .
Baroness Orsolya Dersffy de Szerdahely ( Dersfy ; 1583 -- 15 March 1619 ) was the first wife of the later Palatine Nikolaus , Count Esterházy .
Bertila of Spoleto ( c. 860 -- December 915 ) was the wife of Berengar I of Italy , and by marriage Queen consort of Italy and Holy Roman Empress .
Huang Yaoshi is married to Feng Heng and has six students .
At the end of 1997 , Dicky Cheung met his current wife Jess Zhang(Zhang Qian ) , an actress in Mainland China .
On 1 February 1997 , Sandy Pflueger married British Olympian and coach of the American Eventing team , Captain Mark Phillips , whose first wife was Princess Anne , the daughter of Queen Elizabeth II . Mrs. Phillips coached the US eventing team in dressage , alongside her husband .
Karl Kautsky lived in Berlin - Friedenau for many years ; his wife , Luise Kautsky , became a close friend of Rosa Luxemburg , who also lived in Friedenau .
Bertha Puga Martínez ( 13 March 1909 - -9 August 2007 ) was the wife of the 20th President of Colombia , Alberto Lleras Camargo , and served as First Lady of Colombia from 1958 to 1962 .
Currently Caven is living with French writer Jean - Jacques Schuhl , whose book Ingrid Caven won the prestigious Prix Goncourt in 2000 .
Mildred Trouillot - Aristide ( born 1963 ) is an American lawyer who married Jean - Bertrand Aristide , the former President of Haïti , in 1996 .
Lilia Estrin Dallin ( 1898 - -1981 ) ( aka Lola Estrin , Paulsen , Lilya Ginzberg ) was a prominent member of Trotsky 's Paris organization in the 1930s , the wife of the Menshevik David Dallin , and incorrectly suspected of being an NKVD agent .
Dona Maria Pia of Savoy ( 14 February 1847 -- 5 July 1911 ) was a Portuguese Queen consort , spouse of King Luís I of Portugal .
Shannon Bennett is married to actress Madeleine West and the couple have six children .
According to five government investigations , Lee Harvey Oswald stored the 6.5 mm caliber Carcano rifle that he used to assassinate U.S. President John F. Kennedy in Ruth Paine 's garage , unbeknownst to her and her husband , Michael Paine .
Ealhswith or Ealswitha ( died 5 December 902 ) was the wife of King Alfred the Great .
Giuseppina Morlacchi ( October 8 , 1846 -- July 25 , 1886 ) was an Italian American ballerina and dancer who introduced the can - can to the American stage , and married scout and actor Texas Jack Omohundro .
Juana del Pino y Vera Mujica ( December 21 , 1786 - December 14 , 1841 ) was the daughter of the viceroy of the Río de la Plata Joaquín del Pino and wife of Bernardino Rivadavia , first President of Argentina , and therefore the first woman to become First Lady of Argentina .
Alexey Suetin was married to Woman Grandmaster Kira Zvorykina and together they had a son Aleksandr , born 1951 .
Noble Lady Shun ( 1748 -- 1788 ) was a concubine of the Qianlong Emperor of the Qing Dynasty .
In addition to winning excellent reviews , Orfeh met her soon - to - be husband , Andy Karl .
Aryenis was also the Queen consort of Astyages , King of Media .
Nora Barnacle ( March 1884 -- April 10 , 1951 ) was the muse and wife of Irish author James Joyce .
Françoise de Langlade ( 1921 - 1983 ) was a magazine editor with Conde Nast Publications and the wife of fashion designer Oscar de la Renta .
Stephen Poliakoff lives in London and is married to fellow scriptwriter Sandy Welch , with whom he has two children .
In 1637 , Aurangzeb married the Safavid princess , Dilras Banu Begum , also known as Rabia - ud - Daurani .
Tauquir Ahmed Married Bipasha Hayat , another fellow actor , on 23 July 1999 .
Gülçiçek Hatun ( Ottoman Turkish : گلچیچک خاتون‎ ; Greek : Γκιουλτσιτσέκ Χατούν , Gülçiçek meaning Rose blossom ) was the first wife of Ottoman Sultan Murad I and Valide Hatun to their son Bayezid I.
Hsua is a genus of extinct vascular plants , known from the Devonian .
The Eublepharidae are a family of geckos consisting of 30 described species in six genera .
Sphodromantis royi , common name Roy 's mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Burkina Faso , Mali , Mauretania , Niger , and Senegal .
Xenodiscus is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus and one of the earliest ceratites , found in the Upper Permian of northern India and Timor .
Moxostoma cervinum ( blacktip jumprock or black jumprock ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Moxostoma .
Neillieae is a tribe of flowering plants in Rose family .
Neotrypaea californiensis ( formerly Callianassa californiensis ) , the Bay ghost shrimp , is a species of ghost shrimp that lives on the Pacific coast of North America .
Mirabilistrombus listeri , common name the Lister 's conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Eleutherodactylus barlagnei is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Guadeloupe and known from the Basse - Terre Island .
Drosera aberrans is a perennial tuberous species in the genus Drosera that is native to New South Wales , South Australia , and Victoria .
Chaca burmensis is a species of angler catfish endemic to Myanmar , where it is found in the Sittang River and possibly the Ayeyarwady drainage .
The Cape Sable seaside sparrow ( Ammodramus maritimus mirabilis ) is a subspecies of seaside sparrow endemic to southern Florida .
Eriogonum codium is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common names basalt desert buckwheat and Umtanum Desert wild buckwheat .
Kairuku grebneffi is an extinct species of giant penguin .
Argyrodendron peralatum is a species of large trees , of the plant family Malvaceae .
Anagelasta is a genus of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , containing the following species : subgenus Anagelasta Anagelasta apicalis Pic , 1925 Anagelasta grisea Breuning , 1936 Anagelasta lineifrons Gressitt , 1951 subgenus Mesagelasta Anagelasta nigromaculata Breuning , 1938 Anagelasta transversevittata Breuning , 1964 Anagelasta trimaculata Breuning , 1938
Piliocalyx is a group of shrubs and small trees in the Myrtaceae family , first described as a genus in 1865 .
Salix jessoensis is a species of willow native to Japan .
Rostanga setidens is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch .
Ursavini is an extinct tribe of mammals of the family Ursidae ( bears ) endemic to North America , Europe , Africa , and Asia during Miocene through Pliocene , living from ~23 - -2.5 Ma , existing for approximately 20.5 million years .
Panicum abscissum is a species of grass known by the common name cutthroat grass .
Cyperus polystachyos , also known as Pycreus polystachyos is a herbaceous species in the family Cyperaceae , widespread in tropical and subtropical areas around the world , sometimes extending its range into temperate regions .
Carpathica is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Oxychilidae .
Epicrocis metallopa , formerly known as Cetermna metallopa , is a species of snout moth in the genus Epicrocis .
Lingulida is an order of brachiopods .
Gastrocopta pentodon , common name the comb snaggletooth , is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the vertigo snails .
Daanosaurus was a genus of dinosaur .
Sceliphron is a genus of Hymenoptera of the Sphecidae family of wasps , commonly referred to as mud daubers .
Erigeron petrophilus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names rockloving erigeron or cliff fleabane .
Boechera breweri is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Brewer 's rockcress .
Myersiohyla aromatica is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Venezuela .
Kuhlia mugil , the barred flagtail or the five - bar flagtail , is a species of flagtail belonging to the family Kuhliidae .
Alcidion unicolor is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae .
Cryptocoryne wendtii is a species of herb which is a popular aquarium plant which is native to Sri Lanka .
Eagle Lake trout , Oncorhynchus mykiss aquilarum , is a subspecies of rainbow trout endemic to Eagle Lake , in Lassen County , California .
The New Caledonian nightjar ( Eurostopodus exul ) is a poorly known species of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
Liopterus atriceps is a species of water beetle in the genus Liopterus .
Feroponera is a monotypic Afrotropical genus of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae containing the single species Feroponera ferox .
The white bromeliad ( Aechmea candida ) is a species of bromeliad in the genus Aechmea .
Quinchamalium chilense is a species of flowering plant in the family Schoepfiaceae native to Chile .
Macaroeris nidicolens is a species of jumping spider that occurs from Europe to Central Asia .
Echinosepala is a proposed genus of orchids comprising the subgenera Silenia and Satyria of the genus Myoxanthus .
Acantholycosa mordkovitchi is a species of wolf spider only known from the Terektinsky Mountain Range in the Russian part of the Altai Mountains .
Micropterix emiliensis is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Viette in 1950 , and is endemic to Italy .
Ameghinoa is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described in 1897 .
Limenitis is a genus of brush - footed butterflies , commonly called the admirals .
Ringicella carinatum is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the subfamily Bulimulinae , in the family Odontostomidae .
Wesserpeton was first named by Steven C. Sweetman and James D. Gardner in 2013 and the type species is Wesserpeton evansae .
Nephrolepis exaltata , the sword fern , is a species of fern in the family Lomariopsidaceae ( sometimes treated in the families Davalliaceae or Oleandraceae , or in its own family , Nephrolepidaceae ) , native to tropical regions throughout the world .
Cupressus arizonica , the Arizona cypress , is a North American species of trees in the cypress family .
Eurybia conspicua , commonly known as the western showy aster , is a North American species of plants in the composite family .
Astelia fragrans , commonly known as bush lily , bush flax or kakaha , is the most common astelia species found in New Zealand .
Gutierrezia microcephala is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names sticky snakeweed , threadleaf snakeweed , threadleaf broomweed , and smallhead snakeweed .
Podophyllum is an herbaceous perennial plant in the family Berberidaceae , described as a genus by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Lescaillea is a genus of Cuban flowering plants in the marigold tribe within the sunflower family .
Potentilla biennis is a species of cinquefoil known by the common names biennial cinquefoil and Greene 's cinquefoil .
Rubroboletus rhodoxanthus is a generally rare species found in southern Europe .
Erigeron formosissimus is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name Beautiful fleabane .
Brachyrhinodon is an extinct genus of sphenodontian from the Triassic of Scotland .
Distylodon is a genus of epiphytes from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Haliplus sibiricus is a species of water beetle from Haliplidae family that can be found in Finland , Norway , Sweden , Latvia , and the northern part of Russia .
Lampshade spiders , family Hypochilidae , are among the most primitive of araneomorph spiders .
Tyrannosauroidea ( meaning ' tyrant lizard forms ' ) is a superfamily ( or clade ) of coelurosaurian theropod dinosaurs that includes the family Tyrannosauridae as well as more basal relatives .
Trigonospermum is a genus of Mesoamerican plants in the daisy family .
Photorhabdus is a genus of bioluminescent , gram - negative bacilli which lives symbiotically within entomopathogenic nematodes , hence the name photo ( which means light - producing ) and rhabdus ( rod - shape ) .
Amara fusca , sometimes known as the wormwood moonshiner , is a species of ground beetles in the family Carabidae .
Klebsiella is a genus of nonmotile , Gram - negative , oxidase - negative , rod - shaped bacteria with a prominent polysaccharide - based capsule .
Anchomenus cyaneus is a species of ground beetle in the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Austria , France , Germany , Italy , Portugal , Spain and Switzerland .
Phallobrycon adenacanthus is a species of characin endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the Rio Xingu basin .
Artedius harringtoni , also known as the Scalyhead sculpin or Plumose sculpin , is a demersal species of sculpin in the family Cottidae .
Quercus sadleriana is a species of oak known by the common names Sadler 's oak and deer oak .
Armadillidium klugii is a lesser - known , rare Balkan , Dalmatia - based species of woodlouse , most distinguished by its colouration which resembles the red markings of the Mediterranean black widow Latrodectus tredecimguttatus .
Plectronidium australiense is a species of anamorphic fungus .
Gyracanthus is an extinct genus of acanthodian .
Cattleya dormaniana ( Dorman 's Cattleya ) is a bifoliate Cattleya species of orchid .
Nicandra is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the nightshade family containing the single species Nicandra physalodes .
Aiphanes is a genus of spiny palms which is native to tropical regions of South and Central America and the Caribbean .
Cittarium pica , common name the West Indian top shell or magpie shell , is a species of large edible sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Bathydorididae is a taxonomic family of dorid nudibranch , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks .
Harpadon squamosus is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the coasts around India .
Donrussellia is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in Europe during the early Eocene .
Scrophularia atrata is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the figwort family known by the common names black - flowered figwort and darkflowered figwort .
Ponapea is a genus of palms which is native to certain islands in the western Pacific .
Ropalidia marginata is an Old World species of paper wasp .
Chitonotus pugetensis , the Roughback sculpin , is a species of sculpin occurring in the eastern Pacific Ocean from British Columbia , Canada ( and possibly north to southern Alaska ) to southern Baja California , Mexico .
Habronattus fallax is a species of spiders from a Salticidae family .
Muilla coronata is a species of flowering plant known by the common name crowned muilla .
Liolope copulans is a species of a trematode , or fluke worm , in the family Liolopidae .
Promoniliformis ovocristatus is a species of parasitic worm , from the family Moniliformidae .
Ceriodaphnia dubia is a species of water flea in the class Branchiopoda , living in freshwater lakes , ponds , and marshes in most of the world .
Brachystele tamayoana is a species of orchid native to the States of Guanajuato and Baja California Sur in Mexico .
Barbus haasi , or the `` Catalonian barbel '' ( barbo colirrojo or barbo de cola roja in Spanish ) , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Cassis tessellata , common name : the West African helmet , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cassidae , the helmet snails and bonnet snails .
Populus angustifolia is a species of poplar tree known by the common names narrowleaf cottonwood and willow - leaved poplar .
Nymphargus siren ( common name : Rio Coca Cochran frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family , formerly placed in Cochranella .
Papilio epenetus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Ecuador .
Malus hupehensis , common names Chinese crab apple , Hupeh crab or tea crabapple , is a species of flowering plant in the apple genus Malus of the family Rosaceae .
Nuttallanthus canadensis ( syn . Linaria canadensis ( L. ) Dumort . , Antirrhinum canadense L. ; blue toadflax , Canada toadflax , old - field toadflax ) is a species of Nuttallanthus in the Plantaginaceae family , native to eastern North America from Ontario east to Nova Scotia and south to Texas and Florida .
Columella edentula , common name the `` toothless column snail '' , is a species of very small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Vertiginidae .
Pinellia is a genus of plants in the family Araceae native to East Asia ( China , Korea , Japan ) .
In taxonomy , the Tetrabaenaceae are a family of algae , specifically of the Chlamydomonadales .
Hylaeanthe is a genus of plants native to Central and South America .
Herpestes lemanensis is an extinct species of mongoose , of the genus Herpestes , from the Oligocene of Europe .

Reteocrinus is an extinct genus of sea lily that lived in the Middle to Late Ordovician .
Vitis chunganensis is a species of climbing vine in the grape family native to China ( Anhui , Fujian , Guangdong , Guangxi , Hunan , Jiangxi , and Zhejiang provinces ) .
Penstemon thurberi is a species of penstemon known by the common names Thurber 's beardtongue and Thurber 's penstemon .
Pilea trianthemoides , the artillery plant , is a species of shrubs or subshrubs in the Urticaceae family , native to Florida and the Caribbean islands , where it grows in waste places and moist thickets .

Clausidium is a genus of copepods that have been found in subtopical to temperate coastal areas along the Pacific , Atlantic and Gulf coasts of North America , the Pacific and Atlantic Coasts of South America , the Atlantic and Mediterranean coasts of Europe , the Atlantic coast of Africa , and the coast of India .
Agnostidae is a family of Agnostida trilobites .
Rhamnus ilicifolia is a species of flowering plant in the buckthorn family known by the common name hollyleaf redberry .
Blochius longirostris is a species of prehistoric fish belonging to the Blochiidae family .
Onykia carriboea , the tropical clubhook squid , is a squid in the family Onychoteuthidae , the type species of the genus Onykia .
Tropidophis semicinctus , or the Yellow - banded dwarf boa , is a species of snake in the Tropidophiidae family .
Leptolepia novae - zealandiae , commonly known as lace fern is a native species of fern from New Zealand .

Humboldtiana nuevoleonis is a species of American air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Humboldtianidae .
Megapomponia is a genus of cicadas from Southeast Asia containing the world 's largest cicadas species .
Garcinia zeylanica is a terrestrial species of flowering plant in the Clusiaceae family .
Ceresa , commonly known as buffalo treehoppers , is a genus of treehoppers .
Ephedra viridis , known by the common names green Mormon tea , green ephedra , and Indian tea , is a species of Ephedra .

Sisoridae is a family of catfishes .
Orthasterias koehleri , the rainbow star or red - banded sea star , is the only species in the genus .
Dawkinsia exclamatio is a species of cyprinid fish found in Kallada River , Kerala , India where it occurs in areas with clear water with pebble and rock substrates .
Allobates chalcopis , also known as the Martinique volcano frog or ravine rocket frog , is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .

Repetobasidium is a genus of fungi in the Hymenochaetales .
Hemidactylus alkiyumii is a species of house gecko from Oman .
Pyura is a large genus of sessile ascidians that live in coastal waters at depths of up to 80 m ( 260 feet ) .
Iridomyrmex calvus is a species of ant belonging to the Iridomyrmex genus .

Tenodera superstitiosa is a species in the subfamily Mantinae of the family Mantidae .
Eucryphia jinksii ( Springbrook Leatherwood ) is a species of rare rainforest trees found in Queensland and New South Wales , Australia , of the plant family Cunoniaceae .
Praealticus striatus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Pacific ocean , in the South China Sea .
Grammatostomias is a genus of barbeled dragonfishes found in the Atlantic Ocean .
Rhabdites is an extinct orthocerid genus , a kind of straight - shelled nautiloid cephalopod .
Scrancia is a genus of moth in the family of Notodontidae from the Afrotropics .
Eriogonum brachyanthum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name shortflower buckwheat .
Nymphargus chancas ( common name : Peru Cochran frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family , formerly placed in Cochranella .
Mussa angulosa , the spiny flower coral or large flower coral , is a species of stony coral in the family Mussidae .
Picramnia , the bitterbushes , is a genus of plant considered to be in the family Picramniaceae , but sometimes placed in Simaroubaceae .

Hygromia cinctella , known commonly as the Girdled Snail , is a small European species of air - breathing land snail , native to the Mediterranean region , that belongs to the terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk family Hygromiidae .
Nesopupa dispersa is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae the whorl snails .
Betta waseri is a species of gourami endemic to Malaysia .
Tegula corteziana is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Sepia hieronis is a species of cuttlefish native to the southeastern Atlantic Ocean and southwestern Indian Ocean , specifically southern Namibia , from approximately 27 ° S to Port Alfred , South Africa , and east Africa from 17 ° S to Kenya and Mozambique .
Eugenia woodburyana ( Woodbury 's stopper ) is a species of plant in the Myrtaceae family .
Omobranchus rotundiceps , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Pacific ocean , around Queensland , Australia .
Pseudocheiridae is a family of arboreal marsupials containing 17 extant species of ringtailed possums and close relatives .
Mantura chrysanthemi is a species of Chrysomelidae family , that is common in England , Turkey , Algeria , Morocco .
Synanceia verrucosa is a fish species known as the reef stonefish or simply stonefish .
Erigeron breweri is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name Brewer 's fleabane .
Sassafras tzumu ( Chinese sassafras , Cha mu , 檫木 ) is a species of Sassafras native to China , in Anhui , Fujian , Guangdong , Guangxi , Guizhou , Hubei , Hunan , Jiangsu , Sichuan , Yunnan , and Zhejiang .
Clepsis clemensiana , Clemens ' clepsis moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Brachinus andalusiacus is a species of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that can be found in Spain and Morocco .
Pachystomias microdon , the Smalltooth dragonfish , is a species of barbeled dragonfish found in the oceans at depths of from 660 to 4,000 metres ( 2,170 to 13,120 ft ) .
Rhynchocephalia is an order of lizard - like reptiles that includes only two living species of tuatara ( Sphenodon punctatus and Sphenodon guntheri ) , which only inhabit parts of New Zealand .
Clarkia arcuata is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name glandular clarkia .
Clonostachys rosea f. rosea , also known as Gliocladium roseum , is a species of fungus in the family Bionectriaceae .
Boletus edulis ( English : cep , porcino or porcini ) is a basidiomycete fungus , and the type species of the genus Boletus .
Baraeomimus usambaricus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Baraeomimus .
Cissampelopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , native to India , China , and Southeast Asia .
Arganarhinus ( meaning `` Argana ( Morocco ) snout '' ) is an extinct genus of phytosaur known from the late Triassic period ( Middle Carnian stage ) of Argana basin in Morocco .
Littoridinops tenuipes , common name the henscomb hydrobe , is a species of very small aquatic snail , an operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Polistes pacificus is a Neotropical species of social paper wasp belonging to the subfamily Polistinae and the family Vespidae .
Phileurus truncatus , Triceratops Beetle , is a species of beetle belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Cochliopidae is a family of small freshwater snails with gills and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks .
Myrmica scabrinodis is a Euro - Siberian species of ants .
Alpheus novaezealandiae is a species of shrimp in the family Alpheidae , found in Australasia .
Drosera platypoda , the fan - leaved sundew , is a tuberous perennial species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to south - west Western Australia .
Aspidura is a genus of the Colubridae family of snakes that is endemic to island of Sri Lanka which is commonly known as Rough - sided snake , and as මැඩිල්ලා ( maedilla ) in Sinhala .
Penstemon pachyphyllus is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name thickleaf beardtongue .
Peckoltia brevis is a small species of Peckoltia belonging to the Loricariidae family of catfish .
Micromystix exigua is a species of snout moth in the genus Micromystix .
Arceuthobium siskiyouense is a species of dwarf mistletoe known as knobcone pine dwarf mistletoe .
Najas marina is a species of aquatic plant known by the common names spiny water nymph , spiny naiad and holly - leaved naiad .
Yucca desmetiana is a Mexican species of plants in the asparagus family , native to northern Mexico from Chihuahua south as far as Aguascalientes and east to San Luís Potosí and Tamaulipas .
Erigeron hyssopifolius is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family , called the Hyssop - leaf fleabane .
Senecio hydrophilus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names water ragwort and alkali - marsh ragwort .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Woodiella natalensis .
Paratornoceratinae is a subfamily of oxyconic dimeroceratids included in the order Goniatitida , a group of Paleozoic ammonoids , which have closer affinity to living coleoids than to Nautilus .
Astichopus is a monotypic genus of sea cucumbers , the only species in the genus being Astichopus multifidus .
Ablabys taenianotus , the Cockatoo waspfish , is a small fish species that belongs to the scorpionfishes family Scorpaenidae .
A 2005 genetic study suggested that Glyptonotus antarcticus may in fact represent several distinct species .
Flacourtia inermis , known commonly as lovi - lovi , or batoko plum , is a species of flowering plant native to the Philippines , but which has naturalized in tropical Asia and Africa .
Bromus madritensis ( also , B. matritensis ) is a species of brome grass known by the common name compact brome .
Trichilia catigua is a flowering plant species in the genus Trichilia .
Neoclinus toshimaensis is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in rocky reefs around Japan , in the northwest Pacific ocean .
Josephoartigasia magna is an extinct species of giant rodent .
The heart urchins or Spatangoida are an order of sea urchins .
Avicularia bicegoi is a species of large tarantulas of the genus Avicularia .
Carniella mihaili is a tangle web spider species found in Romania .
Buccinum oedematum , common name the swollen whelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Eriogonum nummulare is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common names Kearney 's buckwheat and money buckwheat .
Ebaeides monstrosa is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Apomecynini .
Anthodiscus montanus is a species of plant in the Caryocaraceae family .
Rubus glabratus is a Latin American species of brambles in the rose family .
Psilocybe araucariicola is a species of psilocybin mushroom found in Brazil , where it grows on decayed Araucaria angustifolia wood in the Floresta Nacional de São Francisco de Paula in Rio Grande do Sul .
Carabus excellens is a species of beetle endemic to Europe , where it is observed in Belarus , Moldova , Poland , Romania , central and southern Russia , and Ukraine .
Hapalopsittaca is a genus of Neotropical parrot native to the Andes of South America .
Corallorhiza bentleyi is a rare species of orchid known deciduous forests in the mountains of Virginia and West Virginia .
Trachonitis cristella is a species of snout moth in the genus Trachonitis .
Brasiliorchis picta is a species of plant in the orchid family native to Brazil , Paraguay and Argentina .
Hoplopholcus minotaurinus is a cellar spider species found in Crete .
Oenopia conglobata is a species of Ladybird ( Coccinellidae ) native to continental Europe , Asia and Africa .
Conus chiangi , common name Chiang 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Tenerife goldcrest , Regulus regulus teneriffae , ( sometimes considered a separate species , R. teneriffae ) is a very small passerine bird in the kinglet family , closely resembling the goldcrest but with a broader black band across the forehead , slightly darker underparts and a longer bill .
The Nematoceran family Axymyiidae is the sole member of the infraorder Axymyiomorpha , though it is often included within the infraorder Bibionomorpha in older classifications .
Pterocarpus soyauxii , the African padauk or African coralwood , is a species of Pterocarpus in the family Fabaceae , native to central and tropical west Africa , from Nigeria east to Congo - Kinshasa and south to Angola .
Gobiocichla is a small genus of rheophilic cichlids native to the Cross ( Manyu ) and Niger Rivers in Africa .
Secodontosaurus ( meaning `` cutting - tooth lizard '' ) , an extinct genus of `` pelycosaur '' synapsid that lived from between about 285 to 270 million years ago during the Early Permian .
Tripterocalyx crux - maltae is a species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family known by the common names Lassen sandverbena and Kellogg 's sand - verbena .
Cookeconcha contorta is a species of very small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Endodontidae .
Eviota readerae is a species of goby associated with reefs and tide pools .
Cleomella parviflora is a species of flowering plant in the cleome family known by the common name slender stinkweed .
Trichloris crinita is a species of grass known by the common name false Rhodes grass .
Antennablennius variopunctatus , the Orange - dotted blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian Ocean .
Gammasphaerolipovirus is a proposed genus of double stranded DNA viruses that infect thermophilic bacteria .
Hydrolaetare dantasi ( Feijo white - lipped frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Dentalium zelandicum is a species of tusk shell , a marine scaphopod mollusk in the familyDentaliidae .
Typhlosaurus is a genus of African lizards , one of a number of genera of limbless lizards in the skink family ( Scincidae ) .
Bittacus carpenteri is a species of hanging fly in the Order Mecoptera .
Iris verna is a species of iris in the family Iridaceae , also in the subgenus of Iris .
Gladiolus dichrous is a species of flowering plant found in mountainous regions of South Sudan , Kenya and Uganda .
Caleidocrinus is a genus of sea lily that lived during the Middle and early Upper Ordovician in what is now the Czech Republic and Wales .
Oberea affinis is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Leng & Hamilton in 1896 .
Elomeryx is an extinct genus of artiodactyl ungulate , and is among the earliest known anthracotheres .
Takifugu chinensis ( Chinese Puffer ) is a species of fish in the Tetraodontidae family .
Canalispira is a genus of very small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Cystiscidae .
Parasthenias fulvotomentosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parasthenias .
Dasylirion serratifolium is a plant species in the family Asparagaceae , native to the Mexican states of Hidalgo and Oaxaca .
Hydrangea anomala , the Japanese climbing - hydrangea , is a species of hydrangea native to the woodlands of the Himalaya , southern and central China and northern Myanmar .
Aloe capitata is a species of flowering plant in the Aloe genus .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Heuflera betulae .
Ulvella is a genus of either endophytic microalgae in Ulvophyceae class , or fungi in the Ascomycota phylum .
Punctum randolphi is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Punctidae , the dot snails .
Germanosaurus , meaning `` German Kingdom of Prussia lizard '' , is an extinct aquatic genus of nothosaurid sauropterygian known from the early Middle Triassic ( early Anisian stage ) Lower Muschelkalk of what was known as Upper Silesia , now a part of Poland .
Pseudomugil reticulatus , commonly known as the Vogelkop blue - eye , is a species of fish in the family Pseudomugilidae .
Eriphia verrucosa , sometimes called the warty crab or yellow crab , is a species of crab found in the Black Sea , Mediterranean Sea and eastern Atlantic Ocean from Brittany to Mauritania and the Azores .
Junggarsuchus is an extinct genus of sphenosuchian crocodylomorph from the Middle Jurassic of China .
Granata elegans , common name the elegant stomatella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chilodontidae .
Paraconger is a genus of eels in the family Congridae .
Taxonomist C.H. Merriam was first to recognize Kodiak bears as unique and the only subspecies of the brown bear , and he named the species `` Ursus middendorffi '' in honor of the celebrated Baltic naturalist Dr. A. Th . von Middendorff .
Cochranella granulosa ( common name : grainy Cochran frog , in Spanish ranita de cristal ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
Acadiocaris is an extinct genus of spelaeogriphacean crustacean that existed in Canada during the Upper Jurassic period .
Titanomyrma is a genus of prehistoric giant ant .
Anchoa hepsetus , commonly known as the broad - striped anchovy , is a species of fish in the family Engraulidae .
Penicillium vasconiae is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated in Madrid in Spain .
Hebeloma radicosum , commonly known as the rooting poison pie , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Hymenogastraceae .
Because of the plumage variability of Spizaetus eagles , the Javan hawk - eagle was not recognised as a full species until 1953 .
Calycadenia hooveri is a California species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Hoover 's western rosinweed .
Demodex brevis is one of the two species of face mite that afflict humans ( the other being Demodex folliculorum ) .
Harrisia martinii , commonly called the Martin applecactus , is a species of night blooming cacti native to South America .
Rhus sandwicensis , commonly known as neneleau , neleau or Hawaiian sumac , is a species of flowering plant in the cashew family , Anacardiaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Oplopomus is a genus of gobies found in coral reefs of the Indo - Pacific region .
Phemonoides ochreosticticus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Phemonoides .
Staurois is a small genus of minuscule true frogs .
Parasphaerichthys ocellatus , the eyespot gourami , is a species of gourami endemic to Myanmar .
Mesomys occultus , also known as Tufted - tailed Spiny Tree - rat or Furtive Spiny Tree Rat , is a spiny rat species from South America .
Lepturus ( common name thintail ) is a genus of plants in the grass family , native to Asia , Africa , Australia , and various islands in the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Paracanthurus hepatus is a species of Indo - Pacific surgeonfish .
Silene suksdorfii is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names Suksdorf 's silene , Suksdorf 's catchfly and Cascade alpine campion .
Streptocephalus dendyi is a species of crustacean in the family Streptocephalidae .
Triteleia hyacinthina is a species of flowering plant known by the common names white brodiaea , white tripletlily , hyacinth brodiaea , and fool 's onion .
Ectopsocus briggsi is a species of Psocoptera from Ectopsocidae family that can be found in Great Britain and Ireland .
Streptochaeta is a genus of Latin American and Caribbean plants in the grass family , the only genus in the tribe Streptochaeteae .
Liwiidae is a family of nektaspid ( stem - group chelicerate ) in the order Nektaspida .
Platismatia is genus of medium to large foliose lichens with rather crinkled lobes .
Triodus is an extinct genus of xenacanthidan shark that lived in the Permian .
Borissiakia is an extinct genus of chalicothere , a group of herbivorous , odd - toed ungulate ( perissodactyl ) mammals . That lived during the late Oligocene .
Imantodes cenchoa ( common names : blunthead tree snake , fiddle - string snake , mapepire corde violon ) is a species of rear - fanged colubrid snake distributed in Mexico , Central America , and South America .
Oxalis triangularis , commonly called false shamrock , is a species of edible perennial plant in the Oxalidaceae family .
Meconematinae is a subfamily of the katydids .
Psettina is a genus of small lefteye flounders native to the Indo - Pacific .
Shorea acuminata ( also called Dark Red Meranti , Light Red Meranti , or sometimes Red Lauan ) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Piruauna tuberosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Piruauna .
Clytoctantes is a South American genus of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Cypriniformes is an order of ray - finned fish , including the carps , minnows , loaches and relatives .
Banksia solandri , commonly known as Stirling Range banksia , is a species of large shrub in the plant genus Banksia .
Tityus apozonalli is an extinct species of scorpion in the family Buthidae known from a fossil found in North America .
Matelea alabamensis is a species of flowering plant in the dogbane family known by the common names Alabama milkvine , Alabama anglepod , and Alabama spiny - pod .
Enallagma pictum , the scarlet bluet , is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Metapenaeus ensis ( sometimes called the greasyback shrimp or sand shrimp ) is a species of prawn .
It contains only one species , Tetanostola hexagona , which is found on Madagascar .
Blenniella bilitonensis , the Lined rockskipper , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Pacific ocean .
Tachina vittata is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Colombia .
Solanum sarrachoides is a species of nightshade known as the hairy nightshade or leafy - fruited nightshade .
The Kangaroo Island dunnart ( Sminthopsis aitkeni ) is a dark sooty - grey coloured dunnart species first described in 1969 , with paler underparts of its body .
Monoplex trigonus , common name the Trigonal Hairy Triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Mentzelia tricuspis is a species of flowering plant in the family Loasaceae known by the common name spinyhair blazingstar .
Cobitis fahireae is a species of loach endemic to Turkey where it occurs in intermittent rivers .
Parula was formerly a small genus of New World warblers which breed in North and South America .
Laccosaurus is an extinct monotypic genus of temnospondyl amphibian , the type species being Laccosaurus watsoni .
Pinguicula gigantea is a tropical species of carnivorous plant in the family Lentibulariaceae .
Gymnopus biformis is a North American species of agaric fungus in the family Omphalotaceae .
Rapanea is a genus of plant in family Primulaceae .
Stemona tuberosa is a species of flowering plant in the family Stemonaceae .
Adiantum aethiopicum was one of the many species first described by Linnaeus , in this case in his Systema naturae in 1759 .
Tubuaia fosbergi is a species of air - breathing land snail or semislug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicarionidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Jugulospora rotula .

Coreopsis grandiflora is a North American species of perennial plants in the sunflower family .

Scada karschina is a species of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies in the family Nymphalidae , native to Brazil .
Zoropsis spinimana is a spider species , belonging to the family Zoropsidae .
Paenibacillus alvei ( formerly Bacillus alvei ) is a species of bacteria within the order Bacillales .
Otophora unilocularis was a species of plant in the Sapindaceae family .
Drosera modesta , the modest rainbow , is a scrambling perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
Omobranchus elongatus , the cloister blenny or chevroned blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific and Indian oceans .
Artemisia rigida is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names scabland sagebrush and stiff sagebrush .
Homaloptera manipurensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Homaloptera .
The genus Kielanodon , meaning `` Kielan 's tooth '' after Zofia Kielan - Jaworowska , was named by Hahn G. in 1987 .
Prosidactus bartolozii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Prosidactus .
Cyanea truncata is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Punaluu cyanea .
Amaranthus pumilus , the seaside amaranth or seabeach amaranth , is a species of amaranth .
Pholidocercus is an extinct monotypic genus of mammal related to and resembling the modern - day hedgehog with a single species , Pholidocercus hassiacus .
The Orange Bushbrown ( Mycalesis terminus ) is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
The taxon was first established by Banks in 1968 as the subdivision Zosterophyllophytina ; they have since also been treated as the division Zosterophyllophyta and the class Zosterophyllopsida .
Entomacrodus is a genus of combtooth blennies .
Cyathopus is a genus of Himalayan plants in the grass family .
Tramitichromis intermedius is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is found in the southern parts of the lake preferring the shallows of sheltered bays .
Hapalioloemus macheralis is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Hapalioloemus of the family Tachinidae .
Esaete rufulus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Esaete .
Eclogavena quadrimaculata , the Four Spotted Cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Mahonia trifoliolata is a species of flowering plant in the family Berberidaceae , in southwestern North America .
The Discinaceae are a family of ascomycete fungi , the best known members of which are the false morels of the genus Gyromitra .
The genus Periclimenes contains a large number of species of shrimp that live symbiotically with larger animals , most commonly sea anemones , although some corals , sea stars , sea cucumbers .
Nephelomys auriventer , also known as the golden - bellied oryzomys or Ecuadorian rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Nephelomys of family Cricetidae .
Bulbophyllum reichenbachii is a species of orchid in the genus Bulbophyllum , found in northern Burma .
Lunella torquata , common name the twisted necklace , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Erigeron rydbergii is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Rydberg 's fleabane ..
Conus burryae , common name Mrs Burry 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Synthetonychiidae are a small family of harvestman with a handful of species in a single genus .
Schoenoplectus heterochaetus is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name slender bulrush .
Malacothamnus jonesii is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names Jones ' bushmallow and slender bushmallow .
Helianthus heterophyllus is a species of sunflower known by the common names variableleaf sunflower and wetland sunflower .
Dorcopsulus is a genus of marsupial in the family Macropodidae .
Ceroxylon alpinum is a species of palm tree native to Colombia , Ecuador , and Venezuela .
Pseudochama gryphina is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Chamidae .
It contains the single species Carilephia moninna , which is found on the Philippines ( Luzon ) .
Sitona californicus is a species of weevil in the Curculionidae family that can be found in Nearctic and in US states such as Arizona and California .
Carex pensylvanica is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family commonly called Pennsylvania sedge .
Danakilia franchettii is a species of cichlid fish endemic to the saline Lake Afrera and nearby swamps in Ethiopia .
Epiphyllum ( /ˌɛpɨˈfɪləm/ ; `` upon the leaf '' in Greek ) is a genus of 19 species of epiphytic plants in the cactus family ( Cactaceae ) , native to Central America .
Acetabularia caliculus is a species of green alga found in shallow temperate and tropical seas .
Shelley 's francolin ( Scleroptila shelleyi ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Hiodontiformes is a relatively new order of fish , consisting of the two living species of the mooneye family Hiodontidae and three genera of extinct types .
Blenniella leopardus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern Indian Ocean .
Retusa truncatula is a species of very small head - shield sea snail or barrel - bubble snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Retusidae The subspecies Retusa truncatula var . mammilata : is a synonym of Retusa mammillata ( Philippi , 1836 )
Sophora macrocarpa is a species of flowering tree or shrub of the genus Sophora , belonging to the Fabaceae family .
Micrelytra fossularum is a species of true bugs belonging to the family Alydidae .
Knipowitschia ephesi is a species of goby endemic to Turkey where it occurs in stagnant or nearly stagnant fresh waters .
Krynickillus melanocephalus is a species of air - breathing land slug , a shell - less terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Agriolimacidae .
Conus xanthicus , common name the Guaymas cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Callionymus belcheri , Belcher 's dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific Ocean waters off of Australia and Papua New Guinea where it occurs at depths of from 18 to 36 metres ( 59 to 118 ft ) .
Zamia decumbens , common name sinkhole cycad , is a species of cycad known only from Belize .
Calochortus syntrophus is a rare species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Callahan 's Mariposa lily and clustered Mariposa lily .
Lespedeza thunbergii is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names Thunberg 's bushclover , Thunberg 's lespedeza , and shrub lespedeza .
Bischoffena bischoffensis is a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
The Tumbling Creek cavesnail ( Antrobia culveri ) is a species of freshwater cave snail with gills and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Amnicolidae .
Heliocosma is a genus of moths , mostly placed in the Tortricoidea superfamily .
Tegula aureotincta , common name the gilded tegula , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Enceliopsis nudicaulis is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name nakedstem sunray , or naked - stemmed daisy .
Vaccinium macrocarpon ( also called large cranberry , American cranberry and bearberry ) is a North American species of cranberry of the subgenus Oxycoccus and genus Vaccinium .
Yucca glauca ( syn . Yucca angustifolia ) is a species of perennial evergreen plant , adapted to xeric ( dry)growth conditions .
Didemnidae is a family of colonial tunicates in the order Enterogona .
Carex colchica is a species of perennial plant in the family Cyperaceae .
Chalcosoma caucasus ( Caucasus beetle ) is a species of beetle in the Scarabaeidae family .
Stenocereus griseus , also known as the Mexican organ pipe , dagger cactus , pitaya , and pitayo de mayo , is a species of cactus .
Netoxena is an extinct genus of moths within the family Eolepidopterigidae , containing one species , Netoxena nana , which is known from the Crato Formation in Brazil .
Amietia wittei ( common name : Molo frog ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Nemacladus glanduliferus is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name glandular threadplant .
Psilocybe hoogshagenii is species of psilocybin mushroom in the Strophariaceae family .
Mikadotrochus salmianus , common name the Salmiana slit shell , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae , the slit snails .
Melica mollis is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to Chile where it grows on rock clevices at the elevation of 340 metres ( 1,120 ft ) .
Menegazzia sanguinascens is a species of lichen found in South America .
Sphaerotheca dobsonii ( common names : Mangalore bullfrog , Dobson 's burrowing frog ) is a species of frog capable of burrowing .
Texas pipefish ( Syngnathus affinis ) is a species of pipefish .
Urochloa fusca ( common name : browntop signalgrass ) is a wild grass species with a native native range extending from Paraguay in South America to the southern United States ( Alabama , Arizona , Florida , Georgia , New Mexico , Texas , and Oklahoma ) , and it is now found as a weed in Australia .
Orculella scalaris is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Orculidae .
The Lesser Tawny Crescent ( Batia lunaris ) is a species of gelechioid moth .
Serratula is a genus of plants in the thistle tribe within the daisy family native to Eurasia .
Triteleia lemmoniae , common names Oak Creek triteleia , Lemmon 's star or Oak Creek tripletlily , is a plant species now classed in the family Asparagaceae , although older classifications would have regarded it part of the Liliaceae .
Mesolimulus is an extinct genus of arthropod .
Armadillidae is a family of woodlice , ( Oniscidea ; terrestrial crustaceans ) .
Fromia monilis , common name necklace starfish or tiled starfish , is a species of starfish belonging to the family Goniasteridae .

Elymus glaucus is a species of wild rye known by the common name blue wild rye .
Hoplistonychus bondari is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Hoplistonychus .
Lunella smaragda , common name the cat 's eye snail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .

In taxonomy , Phaeophila is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Phaeophilaceae .
Paramysis baeri is a species of mysid crustacean from the genus Paramysis , named in honour of the prominent biologist Karl Ernst von Baer .
The Pertusariales are an order of fungi in the class Lecanoromycetes .
Adansonia rubrostipa , commonly known as Fony Baobab is one of the nine species of baobab identified to date , and one of the six indigenous to Madagascar , within the family Malvaceae .
Euthamia graminifolia ( grass - leaved goldenrod or flat - top goldentop ) is a North American species of plants in the daisy family .
Omestes torta is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Omestes .
Cheirothrix lewisii is a species of prehistoric flying fish that is included in the order Alepisauriformes , all the members of which are extinct .
Phragmipedium boissierianum is a species of orchid occurring from southern Ecuador to Peru .
Turbo smithi , common name the miniature turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Barylambda is an extinct genus of pantodont mammal from the middle to late Paleocene , well known from several finds in North America .
Speleoperipatus is a monospecific genus of Jamaican onychophoran .
Syncaris is a genus of shrimp , containing only two species : the endangered California freshwater shrimp , Syncaris pacifica , and the extinct Pasadena freshwater shrimp , Syncaris pasadenae .
Tachina testaceifrons is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Germany .
Nocardiopsis kunsanensis is a species of moderately halophilic actinomycete bacteria .
Dischidodactylus duidensis ( common name : Mount Duida frog ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Dodonaea hispidula is a species of flowering plant in the hop - bush genus of the soapberry family .
Amblychilepas nigrita , common name the black keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Electridae is a family of bryozoans in the class Gymnolaemata .
Cosmopterix is a large genus of moth in the family Cosmopterigidae ( cosmet moths ) .
Clarias is a genus of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Clariidae , the airbreathing catfishes .
Kuehneosauridae is an extinct family of small , lizard - like lepidosauromorph diapsids known from the Triassic period of Europe and North America .
Pygoscelis tyreei , also referred to as Tyree 's penguin , is an extinct species of penguin from New Zealand .
The Pythonidae , commonly known simply as pythons , from the Greek word python ( πυθων ) , are a family of nonvenomous snakes found in Africa , Asia , and Australia .
Phallodrilus macmasterae is a species of invertebrate in the Tubificidae family .
Prolepidotus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Rhaetian stage of the Late Triassic epoch .
Rhopalaea crassa is a species of tunicate belonging to the family Diazonidae .
Oreofraga morrisiana is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae , and the only species in the genus Oreofraga .
†Nerrhenidae is an extinct taxonomic family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks .
Musa beccarii is a species of wild banana ( genus Musa ) , found in Malaysia , in Sabah ( in the northern part of the island of Borneo ) .
Pangio myersi ( Myer 's loach , Myer 's kuhli or giant kuhli ) is a species of loach in the genus Pangio native to Laos , Cambodia and Thailand .
The Pieridae are a large family of butterflies with about 76 genera containing about 1,100 species , mostly from tropical Africa and tropical Asia with some varieties in the more northern regions of North America .
Hemidiptera is a monotypic genus of bug with a single species H. haeckeli .
Gastrodia javanica or Javanese Chijian ( Japanese : 爪哇赤箭 ) is an epiparasitic species of orchid native to Singapore , the Philippines , Indonesia , Malaysia , and Thailand .
Amblyolepis is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1836 .
Symphyotrichum lateriflorum ( common name calico aster or starved aster ) is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family Asteraceae , native to eastern North America .
Oncidium hydrophilum is a species of orchid found from Brazil to Paraguay .
Sisyrinchium montanum , or American blue - eyed - grass , or strict blue - eyed grass , is a grass - like species of plants from the genus Sisyrinchium native to northern North America from Newfoundland west to easternmost Alaska , and south to Pennsylvania in the east , and to New Mexico in the Rocky Mountains .
Aulonocranus dewindti is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika and associated river systems in East Africa .
Homalopoma albidum , common name the white dwarf turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colloniidae .
The Mymarommatidae are a very small family of microscopic hymenopteran insects .
Parthenocissus quinquefolia , known as Virginia creeper , Victoria creeper , five - leaved ivy , or five - finger , is a species of flowering plant in the grape family , Vitaceae .
Pseudoalteromonas phenolica is a marine bacterium species in the genus Pseudoalteromonas .
Plectranthus argentatus ( common name silver spurflower ) is a species of flowering plant in the mint family .
Atractylodes is a genus in the sunflower family .
Oxyothespis is a genus of praying mantis in the subfamily Oxyothespinae .
Morelia spilota spilota is a subspecies of Carpet Python ( Morelia spilota ) , popularly known as the Diamond Python .
Oxyepoecus inquilinus is species of ant in the genus Oxyepoecus .
Zygiella atrica , like other Zygiella species , builds an orb web with two missing sectors , and a signalling thread in the center of those , leading to its hideout , whereas young spiders build a complete web .
Bipalium kewense is a species of large predatory land flatworm of the family Geoplanidae , sometimes referred to as a `` hammerhead slug '' due to its half - moon - shaped head .
Aloe jawiyon is a species of plant in the genus Aloe .
Lithops salicola is a species of perennial plant in the Aizoaceae family , often called living stones .
Crossopriza lyoni is a widespread species of cellar spiders that prefer to live in or around human structures .
Luposicya lupus is a species of goby native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Rumex graminifolius , common name Grassleaf sorrel , is a species of the genus Rumex and the knotweed family Polygonaceae .
Calliostoma haliarchus , common name the sea monarch top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Cylindrospermopsis is a planktonic genus of filamentous cyanobacteria known for its blooms in eutrophic waters .
Macrocheilus allardi is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily Anthiinae .
Subsequently it was raised to a full species again as Sphaerium nucleus ( Studer , 1820 ) due to its having a different form of kidney , and the shell having a broad hinge plate and dense porosity .
Neophasia is a genus of pierid butterflies found in the North America .
The treeline emerald ( Somatochlora sahlbergi ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Corduliidae .
Palmoxylon ( Petrified palmwood ) , is an extinct genus of palm named from petrified wood found around the world .
Kookaburras are terrestrial tree kingfishers of the genus Dacelo native to Australia and New Guinea , which grow to between 28 - -42 cm ( 11 - -17 in ) in length .
Pyrus × bretschneideri ( or Pyrus ×bretschneideri ) , the ya pear or pearple or Chinese white pear ( 白梨 bái lí ) , is an interspecific hybrid species of pear native to northern China , where it is widely grown for its edible fruit .
Aeollanthus saxatilis is a species of plant in the mint family , Lamiaceae .
Cryptomorpha dentifera is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Cryptomorpha .
Buddleja fallowiana is a species of flowering plant endemic to the Yunnan province of western China , where it grows in open woodland , along forest edges and watercourses .
Struthio orlovi is an extinct species of ratite bird from the Miocene of Moldavia .
Desulfotomaculum is a genus of Gram - positive , obligately anaerobic soil bacteria .
Zabrus corpulentus is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that can be found in Bulgaria and Near East .
Eurya sandwicensis ( anini ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Pentaphylacaceae , that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Quercus phillyraeoides is a species of plant in the genus Quercus .
Entoprocta , whose name means `` anus inside '' , is a phylum of mostly sessile aquatic animals , ranging from 0.1 to 7 millimetres ( 0.004 to 0.3 in ) long .
Guntherichthys is an extinct genus of palaeoniscoid .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Lembosiella polyspora .
Bonia is a genus of Chinese and Vietnamese bamboos in the grass family .
Rhyzobius ventralis , common names including Black Lady Beetle , Gumtree Scale Ladybird , is a ladybird species endemic to Tasmania and all the mainland states of Australia except the Northern Territory .
†Ferussinidae is an extinct family of operculate freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the informal group Architaenioglossa .
Saccharomyces telluris is a species of yeast also known as Kazachstania telluris .
Sarracenia jonesii is a species of pitcher plant discovered by Edgar T. Wherry which is endemic to the bogs in the mountains on the border between North Carolina and South Carolina .
It contains only one species , Spatalistiforma submerga , which was described from Baltic amber .
Vanoyia tenuicornis , the long - horned soldier , is a European species of soldier fly .
Dormitator is a genus of sleeper gobies mostly found in marine , fresh , and brackish waters on either side of the Atlantic Ocean , with one species occurring along the Pacific coast of the Americas .
Iberosuchus ( meaning `` Iberian crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of sebecosuchian mesoeucrocodylian from the Eocene of western Europe .
Leptogorgia exigua is a coral species first described by Addison Emery Verrill in 1870 .
Mycena leptocephala , commonly known as the nitrous bonnet , is a species of fungus in the Mycenaceae family .
Salvia aegyptiaca ( Egyptian sage ) is a herbaceous plant species belonging to the Lamiaceae family .
Pholidostachys is a genus of palms found in Central America and northwestern South America ( northwestern Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador , Peru ) .
Dissorophidae is an extinct family of medium - sized , temnospondyl amphibians that flourished during the Late Pennsylvanian and early Permian periods in what is now North America and Europe .
Metallura is a genus of hummingbird , containing nine species distributed along the Andes :
Batocera wallacei , common name Wallace 's long - horn beetle , is a species of flat - faced longhorns beetle belonging to the Cerambycidae family , Lamiinae subfamily .
Pseudoglenea densepuncticollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudoglenea .
Piperia is a genus of the orchid family Orchidaceae .
Dictyophorus spumans , the koppie foam grasshopper or rooibaadjie , is a species of grasshopper in the family Pyrgomorphidae indigenous to Africa .
Lefua is a genus of stone loaches native to Eurasia .
Limonium binervosum , commonly known as rock sea - lavender , is an aggregate species in the family Plumbaginaceae .
Ammosaurus ( /ˌæmoʊˈsɔːrəs/ ; `` sand lizard '' ) is a genus of sauropodomorph dinosaur from the Early and Middle Jurassic Period of North America .
Dendrobium hookerianum is a species of orchid , native to Asia , in the genus Dendrobium .
Galium hardhamae ( often misspelled `` Galium hardhamiae '' ) ( note added May 2014 : `` hardhamiae '' is the correct spelling per Article 60C1 of the ICN ) is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name Hardham 's bedstraw .
Rubus durus is a Cuban species of brambles in the rose family .
Labeobarbus batesii is a species of cyprinid fish from Africa that occurs in Cameroon , Chad and Gabon .
Nelson Bay virus ( NBV ) is a novel double - stranded RNA orthoreovirus species first isolated from a flying fox ( Pteropus poliocephalus ) near Nelson Bay in New South Wales , Australia .
Zygoballus optatus is a species of jumping spider which occurs in Panama .
Coelognathus helena monticollaris is a non - venomous constrictor subspecies of colubrid snake native to south Central Asia .
Hydnocarpus octandra is a species of plant in the Achariaceae family , but originally placed in the Flacourtiaceae family by Arthur Cronquist .
Namatozodia is an extinct genus of prehistoric sarcopterygian or lobe - finned fish .
Kronichthys subteres is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Ribeira de Iguape River basin .
Androctonus maroccanus is a species of scorpion , belonging to the family Buthidae .
Apacheria chiricahuensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Crossosomataceae .
Excoecaria dallachyana , the Scrub Poison Tree or Brush Poison Tree is a species of plant in the Spurge family .
Polyscias oahuensis is a species of tree in the ivy family known by the common name ' ohe mauka .
`` True rats '' are members of the genus Rattus , the most important of which to humans are the black rat , Rattus rattus , and the brown rat , Rattus norvegicus .
Nesovitrea is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Oxychilidae , the glass snails .
Senecio hispidulus , the Hill Fireweed or Rough Groundsel , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Haliotis diversicolor , common name the variously coloured abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Allocryptobia musae is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Allocryptobia .
Iris tuberosa is a species of non - rhizomatous plant of the genus Iris , with the common names snake's - head , snake's - head iris , widow iris , black iris , or velvet flower - de - luce .
Roystonea oleracea , sometimes known as the Caribbean royal palm , palmiste , imperial palm or cabbage palm , is a species of palm which is native to the Lesser Antilles , Colombia , Venezuela , and Trinidad and Tobago .
Isopeda is a genus of huntsman spiders occurring in Australia , New Guinea , New Caledonia , and the Philippines .
Gibbus lyonetianus is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .
Platylobium triangulare , commonly known as Ivy Flat - pea , is a shrub species that is endemic to Australia .
Clarkia mildrediae is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name Mildred 's clarkia .
Adelium is a genus of Tenebrioninae ( darkling beetles ) .
Clostridium sporogenes is a species of Gram - positive bacteria that belongs to the genus Clostridium .
Saprosites raoulensis is a species of dung beetle endemic to the Kermadec Islands in New Zealand .
Acastava is an extinct genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida , from the upper Pragian ( A. atavus ) to Emsian period ( both other species listed ) of the Devonian .
Pinus maximinoi , commonly known as thinleaf pine , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
The Free State pygmy mouse or Orange mouse ( Mus orangiae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Eriogonum brachypodum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Parry 's buckwheat .
Penicillium cecidicola is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which produces pentacecilide A , pentacecilide B , pentacecilide C.
Trichadjinga batchianensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichadjinga .
Ptychozoon kuhli , commonly known as Kuhl 's flying gecko or the common flying gecko , is a species of Asian gecko .
Onychonycteris occurs alongside Icaronycteris index , previously thought to be the most primitive known bat species .
Rhizobium is a genus of Gram - negative soil bacteria that fix nitrogen .
Sphodros abboti also known as Purseweb spider , is a species of spiders from a family of Atypidae .
Euromycter is an extinct genus of large caseid synapsid from middle Early to early Late Permian ( upper Sakmarian to lower Lopingian ) deposits of Southern France .
Andrewsarchus ( /ˌændruːˈsɑrkəs/ ) is an extinct genus of mammal that lived during the middle Eocene epoch in what is now Inner Mongolia , China .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Calceomyces lacunosus .
Phaius borneensis is a species of orchid in the genus Phaius .
Amastra forbesi was a species of gastropod in the Amastridae family .
Entomacrodus vermiculatus , the vermiculated blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny native to the Indian Ocean where it is found around the Seychelles , the Maldives and Christmas Island .
Clinocottus globiceps , commonly known as the mosshead sculpin or globe - headed sculpin , is a species of fish in the family Cottidae , native to the northeastern Pacific .
Lixomorphus is a genus of cylindrical weevils belonging to the family Curculionidae .
Aulastomatomorpha phospherops , the Luminous slickhead , is a species of slickhead found in the Indian and West Pacific Oceans .
Clavaria versatilis is a species of coral fungus in the family Clavariaceae .
Potamarcha congener is a species of dragonfly in the genus Potamarcha .
Quercus hypoleucoides , the silverleaf oak or the whiteleaf oak is a North American species of trees or shrubs in the beech family .
Scorzonera tau - saghyz is a species of Scorzonera of interest as a source of latex suitable for making natural rubber .
The Ericales are a large and diverse order of dicotyledons , including , for example , tea , persimmon , blueberry , Brazil nut , and azalea .
Cornus hongkongensis ( sometimes called Benthamidia hongkongensis , Dendrobenthamia hongkongensis , or Hong Kong dogwood ) is a species of evergreen dogwood native to China , Laos , and Vietnam .
Amphimallon pseudomajale is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily that can be found in Italy and on the island of Sicily .
Zanthoxylum rhoifolium is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family known by the common names mamica de cadela , tambataru , and prickly ash .
The genus name Zygophyseter emphasizes the elongation of the zygomatic process of the only known species Zygophyseter varolai , while the term Physeter refers to the type genus of the family Physeteridae .
Phrynomedusa appendiculata , the Santa Catarina leaf frog , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Gastrophrynoides is a small genus of microhylid frogs in south - east Asia .
Alona sketi is a species of crustacean in family Chydoridae .
Incisura lytteltonensis is a species of sea snail , a keyhole limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Scissurellidae .
Tabernaemontana alternifolia is a species of plant in the Apocynaceae ( dogbane ) family .
Physena is the sole genus of the flowering plant family Physenaceae .
Lestradea perspicax is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it occurs in shallow waters over sandy substrates in the northern portion of the lake .
Penicillium sizovae is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces agroclavine - I and epoxyagroclavine - I.
Amphiesma nicobariense , commonly known as the Nicobar Island keelback , is a species of colubrid snake found in the Nicobar Islands of India .
Arbela elegantula is a species of African damsel bug in the family Nabidae .
The hylocitrea ( Hylocitrea bonensis ) , also known as the yellow - flanked whistler or olive - flanked whistler , is a species of bird that is endemic to montane forests on the Indonesian island of Sulawesi .
Tectiphiala ferox , or palmiste bouglé , is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
Desulfonatronum thiosulfatophilum is a species of haloalkaliphilic sulfate - reducing bacteria .
Metapenaeopsis kishinouyei is a species of prawn in the genus Metapenaeopsis , the velvet shrimps .
Notoceratops ( meaning `` southern horned face '' ) is the name given to a dubious genus of dinosaur based on a toothless dentary ( now lost ) from the Late Cretaceous of Patagonia ( in Argentina ) , probably dating from the Campanian and about 77 million years old .
Cladonia fimbriata is a species of lichen belonging to the family Cladoniaceae .
The Asian Widow , also known as Blue - Tailed Yellow Skimmer , ( Palpopleura sexmaculata ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Potthastia pastoris is a non - biting midge species in the genus Potthastia .
Homalodotherium is an extinct genus of the order Notoungulata , an extinct group of hoofed mammals native to South America .
Cellana toreuma is a species of limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nacellidae .
Barred pipefish , Syngnathus auliscus , is a species of the pipefishes , widespread in the eastern pacific from the Southern California , USA , to northern Peru .
Puumala virus ( PUUV ) is a species of hantavirus .
Eucalyptus aromaphloia , commonly known as Creswick apple - box , scented bark or scent - bark , is a species of plant in the myrtle family that is endemic to the state of Victoria in south - eastern Australia .

Otoceratoidea is an extinct superfamily of ammonite cephalopods in the order Ceratitida .
Thalera fimbrialis , the Sussex emerald , is a species of moth of the family Geometridae .
Mylochromis guentheri is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is found over sandy substrates .
Potamogeton diversifolius is a species of aquatic plant known by the common names waterthread pondweed and diverse - leaved pondweed .
The Purpurinidae are an extinct family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Squalius carolitertii is a species of fresh - water fish in the family Cyprinidae .
Theridula emertoni is a species of tangle web spider commonly found in the United States and Canada .
Sorbus esserteauana , commonly known as Esserteau 's rowan , is a species of rowan .
Eulalia viridis is a species of bright - green polychaete .
Pickfordiateuthis pulchella , the grass squid , is a species of squid in the family Loliginidae .
Amphicynodon is an extinct genus of mammal of the superfamily Ursoidea , endemic to Europe and Asia during the Oligocene , living from ~33.9 - -28.4 Mya , existing for approximately 5.5 million years .
Chancelloria is a genus of early animals known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale , the Comley limestone , the Wheeler Shale , the Bright Angel Shale and elsewhere .
Norops is the proposed generic name for 150 lizard species traditionally classified in the genus Anolis ( family , Iguanidae ) .
Cirsium horridulum , called bristly thistle , horrid thistle , yellow thistle or bull thistle , is a North American species of plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .

Asiopsocidae is a family of Psocoptera belonging to the infraorder Caeciliusetae .

Leucosporidiella is a genus of fungi found in the family Leucosporidiaceae .

Pluscula cuica is a species of marine snail , gastropod mollusk in the superfamily Philinoidea within the clade Cephalaspidea .

Stylidium armeria , the thrift - leaved triggerplant , is a species of Stylidium that is native to Australia .
Atyopsis is a genus of freshwater shrimp from Southeast Asia .
Chrysodema radians is a species of Jewel Beetle of the Buprestidae family .
Camponotus compressus is a species of ant found in India and Southeast Asia .
Cyrtocymura is a genus of Latin American and Caribbean plants in the evil tribe within the daisy family .
Gerrhonotus is a genus of anguid lizards that are commonly referred to as alligator lizards , due to a vague resemblance to the alligator .
Agnorhiza is a small genus of flowering plants in the aster family described as a genus in 1998 .
Mitchell 's water monitor ( Varanus mitchelli ) is a species of monitor lizards native to Australia .
Witwatia ( from the Egyptian Arabic Wit Wat meaning `` large , flapping wings '' ) is an extinct genus of giant bat that contained two species which lived in the Al Fayyum in Egypt during the late Eocene some 35 million years ago and one species which lived in Tunisia during the early Eocene .
It contains the subfamily Pratylenchinae , as well as the subfamilies Hirschmanniellinae , Radopholinae , and Nacobbinae .
Apterostigma eowilsoni is an extinct species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae known from a single possibly Miocene fossil found on Hispaniola .
Tetrodontium brownianum , is a species of moss commonly known as Brown 's tetrodontium moss or Brown 's four - tooth moss .
The superclass Tetrapoda ( Ancient Greek τετραπόδηs tetrapodēs , `` four - footed '' ) , or the tetrapods /ˈtɛtrəpɒd/ , comprises the first four - limbed vertebrates and their descendants , including the living and extinct amphibians , reptiles , mammals , birds , and some extinct fish .
Mimulus bolanderi is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name Bolander 's monkeyflower .
Valenzuela atricornis is a species of Psocoptera from Stenopsocidae family that can be found in United Kingdom and Ireland .

Lankascincus is a genus of skink , commonly known as Lanka skinks .

Zea diploperennis , the diploperennial teosinte , is a true grass species in the genus Zea and a teosinte .

Atriplex parishii is an uncommon species of saltbush known by the common names Parish 's saltbush and Parish 's brittlescale .
Laboulbenia is a genus of fungi in the family Laboulbeniaceae .
Phaeomoniella is a fungus genus in the mitosporic ascomycota , a heterogeneous group of ascomycotic fungi whose common characteristic is the absence of a sexual state .
Pterocerina interrupta is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Pterocerina of the family Ulidiidae .
Phalaenopsis reichenbachiana is an endemic species of orchid from Mindanao island , Philippines .

Hedysarum alpinum is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name alpine sweetvetch .

Caulophyllum thalictroides , blue cohosh a species of Caulophyllum ( family Berberidaceae ) , also called squaw root or papoose root , is a flowering plant in the Berberidaceae ( barberry ) family .

Mammillaria multidigitata is a species of flowering plant in the Cactaceae family that is endemic to San Pedro Nolasco Island in Mexico , growing on steep slopes .
