Hystrivasum squamosum is an extinct species of medium - sized fossil sea snail , a predatory marine gastropod in the family Turbinellidae .
Cymodoceaceae is a family of flowering plants , sometimes known as the `` manatee - grass family '' , the family Cymodoceaceae includes only marine species .
Aeschynomene is a genus of flowering plants in the family Fabaceae , and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Dalbergia clade of the Dalbergieae .
Micranthes rufidula is a species of flowering plant known by the common name rustyhair saxifrage .
Harris 's antelope squirrel ( Ammospermophilus harrisii ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Lathyrus angulatus is a species of wild pea known by the common name angled pea .

Higginsia is a genus of sponges belonging to the phylum Porifera and the order Halichondrida .
Scirpus diffusus is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name umbrella bulrush .

Priochilus captivum is a species of neotropical spider wasp in the family Pompilidae .
Amorphoscelis brunneipennis is a species of praying mantis found in India and Sri Lanka .

Calocedrus rupestris is a species of conifer recently discovered in highly eroded rocky limestone mountains in northern Vietnam and first described in 2004 .
Naiadolina is an agaric fungal genus that produces striking , yellowish fruit bodies on sedges ( Scirpus and Dulichium ) in wetlands in eastern Canada .
Gautieria mexicana is a species of hypogeal fungus in the Gomphaceae family .
Haemogamasidae is a family of mites in the order Mesostigmata .
Oreobates quixensis ( common name : common big - headed frog ) is a frog species in the Craugastoridae family .
Nebria catenata is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the US state of Colorado .
Adonidia merrillii is a palm tree species native to the Philippines and Sabah and naturalized in the West Indies .
Stellaria longifolia is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name longleaf starwort .
Scelio is a large genus ( roughly 500 species ) , the largest within the family Scelionidae , of parasitic wasp whose known target host include the eggs of grasshoppers ( Acrididae , Orthoptera ) .
It contains the single species Cyclosodes flavicostata , which is found on Borneo .
Aphelodoris affinis is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks in the family Dorididae .
Zeuxidia is a genus of very large butterflies in the family Nymphalidae . They are `` leaf '' butterflies with a cryptic ventral pattern . The genus is Indomalayan ( Burma through Indochina and the Philippines to Sumatra , Java and Borneo .
Gravicalymene is a genus of trilobites from the order Phacopida , suborder Calymenia .
Gardenia pyriformis , commonly known as malara , native gardenia or turpentine tree , is a species of plant in the coffee family .
Moreiradromia antillensis is a species of sponge crab .
The wonderpus octopus ( Wunderpus photogenicus ) is a species of octopus in the monotypic genus Wunderpus .
Sticholonche is a genus of protozoan with a single species , S. zanclea , found in open oceans at depths of 99 - -510 metres .
Partamona peckolti is a species of stingless bee from South America .
Plataleorhynchus was a genus of ctenochasmatid pterodactyloid pterosaur from the Tithonian - Berriasian - age Upper Jurassic or Lower Cretaceous Purbeck Limestone of Dorset , England .
Kundurosaurus is an extinct genus of saurolophine hadrosaurid dinosaur known from the Latest Cretaceous ( probably Late Maastrichtian stage ) of Amur Region , Far Eastern Russia .
Fritillaria yuminensis is a plant species native to the northwestern part of Xinjiang Province in northwestern China .
Caecidae is a taxonomic family of very small and minute sea snails or micromolluscs , marine gastropod molluscs in the order Littorinimorpha .
Typhlops ahsanai , or Ahsan 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Brennania belkini is a species of fly in family the horse - fly family , Tabanidae .
Coccosteidae is a family of arthrodire placoderms from the Early to Late Devonian .
Hemicoelus nitidus is a species of beetles in the genus Hemicoelus of the family Anobiidae .
Tropidophis feicki , or the broad - banded dwarf boa , is a species of snake in the family Tropidophiidae .
Picramnia xalapensis is a plant species native to the State of Veracruz , Mexico .
Palaeoloxodon mnaidriensis or Elephas mnaidriensis is an extinct species of elephant from Malta and Sicily closely related to the modern Asian elephant .
Nicotiana sylvestris is a species of the genus Nicotiana , known by the common names woodland tobacco , flowering tobacco , and South American tobacco .
Phallostethus cuulong is a species of priapum fish .
Nebria baicalica is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Irkutsk area , Russia , more precisely , Buryat Republic .
Sphenostethus taslei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Sphenostethus .
Strongyles ( from the Greek strongulos , meaning round ) , or alternatively , strongyls , are nematode worms of the family Strongylidae , order Strongylida .
Restrepia elegans , commonly called the Elegant Restrepia , is a species of orchid occurring from Colombia to northwestern Venezuela .
The Medellín small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis medellinia ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Adenomera andreae ( common name : lowland tropical bullfrog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Quercygale is an extinct genus of Miacidae , primitive carnivores that lived during the Eocene .
Rhizomys is a genus of rodents in the family Spalacidae .
Ulva laingii is a species of seaweed in Ulvaceae family that can be found in Australia and New Zealand .
Oeceoclades quadriloba is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is native to Swaziland , southern Zimbabwe , and western Madagascar .
Naticarius stercusmuscarum , the Fly - specked Moon Snail , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Naticidae , the moon snails .
Rhamnus pirifolia is a species of tree and shrub in the buckthorn family known by the common name island redberry .
Campanula shetleri is a rare species of bellflower known by the common name Castle Crags bellflower .
Euryopis flavomaculata is a tangle - web spider species with Palearctic distribution .
Devario auropurpureus is a small species of danionin fish endemic to Lake Inle in Myanmar .
Crepidula atrasolea is a species of small sea snail , a slipper snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails or slipper limpets , cup - and - saucer snails , and hat snails .
Sphodromantis gastrica , with the common names African mantis or common green mantis , is a species of praying mantis from Africa .
Worthenia is a genus of fossil sea snails , an extinct marine gastropod genus found in the fossil record .
Nama lobbii is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names Lobb 's fiddleleaf and woolly nama .
The Iceland scallop ( Chlamys islandica ) is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
Tachina canariensis is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Canary Islands .
Tetragonoderus sericatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae .
Solidago verna is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names springflowering goldenrod and spring goldenrod .
Boswellia is a genus of trees in the order Sapindales , known for their fragrant resin which has many pharmacological uses , particularly as anti - inflammatories .
Stapelia gigantea is a species of flowering plant in the family Apocynaceae , native to south eastern Africa .
Mimicia pseudolibatrix is a species of snout moth in the genus Mimicia .
Holocarpha virgata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names yellowflower tarweed , pitgland tarweed , and narrow tarplant .
Cicindela duodecimguttata , commonly known as the twelve - spotted tiger beetle , is a species of tiger beetle that is 12 - -15 millimetres ( 0.47 - -0.59 in ) long and is dark brown to black .
Perutherium is monospecific genus of notoungulate from the Late Paleocene or Early Eocene Laguna Umayo Formation of Peru .
Conus cuvieri , common name Cuvier 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Brickellia dentata ( leafy brickellbush ) is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Lithoglyphus is a genus of freshwater snails with gills and an operculum , a gastropod mollusk in the family Lithoglyphidae .
Christmas beetle is a name commonly applied to the Australian beetle genus Anoplognathus .
Pareiorhina is a genus of armored catfishes native to South America where they are only found in Brazil .
Pelargonium cucullatum ( also called Wildemalva , Tree pelargonium or Hooded - leaf pelargonium ) is a species of plant in the Geraniaceae family , that is indigenous to the south - western Cape of South Africa .
Drosera ramellosa , sometimes referred to as the branched sundew , is a tuberous perennial species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Oxyrrhis marina is a species of dinoflagellate , a protist with flagella .
Aplysia is a genus of medium - sized to extremely large sea slugs , specifically sea hares , which are one clade of large sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks .
Musineon is a genus of flowering plants in the carrot family known generally as wild parsleys , though plants of other related genera share that name .
Munditia subquadrata , common name the squared munditia , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , in the family Liotiidae .
The genus contains a single species , Centrarctia mongolica , found in the Gobi desert and neighboring arid territories .
Ampulloclitocybe clavipes , commonly known as the club - footed clitocybe , is a species of gilled mushroom from Europe .
The Yellow - flowered Bulbophyllum or golden comb orchid ( Bulbophyllum pectenveneris ) is a species of orchid .
Dolichorhynchops is an extinct genus of polycotylid plesiosaur from the Late Cretaceous ( early Turonian to late Campanian stage ) of North America , containing three species , D. osborni , D. herschelensis and D. tropicensis .
Atrosalarias hosokawai is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific Ocean , from Japan to Papua New Guinea .
Maripa virus is a single - stranded , enveloped , negative - sense RNA hantavirus species in the Bunyaviridae family .
Boonea is a small genus of small sea snails , pyramidellid gastropod mollusks .
Marpissa pikei is a species of jumping spider that is found in the eastern USA , Texas , New Mexico , Arizona and Cuba .
Platecarpus ( `` flat wrist '' ) is an extinct genus of aquatic lizard belonging to the mosasaur family , living around 84 - -81 million years ago during the middle Santonian to early Campanian , of the Late Cretaceous period .
Asclepias tuberosa is a species of milkweed native to eastern North America .
Parascaris equorum is a species of ascarid that is the equine roundworm .
Pseudidactus roggemani is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudidactus .
Yucca gigantea ( syn . Yucca elephantipes , Yucca guatemalensis ) , is a Yucca species that is native to Belize , Costa Rica , El Salvador , Guatemala , Honduras , Nicaragua and the eastern part of Mexico ( Quintana Róo , Yucatán , Campeche , Tabasco , Chiapas , Veracruz , eastern Puebla and southern Tamaulipas ) .
Rhadinomyia orientalis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Rhadinomyia of the family Tephritidae .
Sebastes flammeus is a species of fish in the rockfish family found in the northwest pacific
Cornus officinalis is a species of dogwood known also as Japanese cornel or Japanese cornelian cherry or Cornelian cherries , not to be confused with C. mas , which is also known as the `` Cornelian cherry . ''
Cadlina luteomarginata , common name the yellow - edged cadlina , is a species of colorful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cadlinidae .
Schoenoplectus tabernaemontani ( syn . Scirpus validus ) is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common names softstem bulrush , grey club - rush , and great bulrush .
Habronestes is an ant - eating spider genus that occurs only in Australia .
Camaridium is a genus of epiphytic orchids widespread across the West Indies and through Latin America from Mexico to Bolivia .
Puntius muzaffarpurensis is a species of cyprinid fish native to India .
Australostichopus mollis , formerly Stichopus mollis , commonly known as brown sea cucumber or Australasian sea cucumber , is a species of sea cucumber that has stimulated interest for its fishery potential in the Southern Hemisphere , and for its capability to reduce waste produced by aquaculture .
Cottonia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae : the only known species is Cottonia peduncularis .
Enscepastra lathraea is a species of moth of the Coleophoridae family .
Gracilidris pombero is a species of ant in the genus Gracilidris .
Cryptantha subcapitata is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names Owl Creek miner 's candle , Wallowa cat 's eye , and Wallowa cryptantha .
Cardiocrinum cordatum is a Northeast Asian species of plants in the lily family .
Bromus hordeaceus , soft brome , is an annual or biennial species of grass in the true grass family ( Poaceae ) .
Oxypolis canbyi is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Canby 's dropwort and Canby 's cowbane .
Neocrepidodera cyanipennis is a species of flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Austria , France , Italy , Romania , Slovenia , and Switzerland .
Pelycidiidae is a family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Sorbeoconcha .
Elasmia mandela is a species of moth of the family Notodontidae .
Trachycystis placenta is a species of very small , air - breathing , land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Charopidae .
Platydesma rostrata is a rare species of flowering plant in the citrus family known by the common name pilo kea lau li'i .
Corynebacterium matruchotii is one of the 12 or more bacterial species in the genus Corynebacterium .
Umbonium conicum is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Filopaludina javanica or Idiopoma javanica is a species of large freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae .
Pelargonium grossularioides is a species of geranium known by the common names gooseberry geranium and coconut geranium .
Centaurea macrocephala , the bighead knapweed , giant knapweed , or Armenian basket flower , is a species of Centaurea found in Caucasus .
Halocoryza acapulcana is a species of brown coloured ground beetle in the subfamily Scaritinae which can be found in Ecuador and Mexico .
It is the only member of its genus , Neocyema .
Acanthoscurria theraphosoides is a species of spider from the family Theraphosidae ( tarantulas ) .
Aceraceae were recognized as a family of flowering plants also called the Maple Family .
Monarda citriodora is a species of flowering plant in the mint family , Lamiaceae , that is native much of the United States and Mexico .
Pristigenys alta , common name short bigeye , is a species of fish in the family Priacanthidae .
Scinax boulengeri ( commonly known as Boulenger 's snouted tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Theria ( /ˈθɪəriə/ ; Greek : θηρίον , wild beast ) is a subclass of mammals that give birth to live young without using a shelled egg , consisting of the eutherians ( including the placental mammals ) and the metatherians ( including the marsupials ) .
Aedes australis is a brackish water mosquito species from the genus Aedes subgenus Halaedes .
Lampadia webbiana is a species of land snail in the family Helicidae , the true snails .
Wisteria floribunda ( common name Japanese wisteria ) is a species of flowering plant in the pea family Fabaceae , native to Japan .
Paracompsosoma humerale is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paracompsosoma .
Geonoma is a genus of small to medium - sized palms native to the forest understorey of tropical Central and South America .
Sinuitidae is an extinct family of Paleozoic molluscs of uncertain position ( they were either Gastropoda or Monoplacophora ) .
Adactylotis contaminaria , the brindled three - lined moth , is a species of moth in the family Geometridae .
Galium orizabense ( bald bedstraw ) is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae , named for the town of Orizaba in Veracruz , where the first collections of the species were made .
Lagarosiphon is a genus of aquatic plants described as a genus in 1841 .
Chiruromys is a genus of Old World mouse that is restricted to New Guinea and the nearby islands of Goodenough , Fergusson , and Normanby .
The Javan warty pig or Javan pig ( Sus verrucosus ) is a species of even - toed ungulate in the family Suidae .
Heteroclinus puellarum , the Little weedfish , is a species of clinid found on the Indian Ocean coast of southern Australia where it can be found in tide pools , rocky reefs and estuaries .
Musa salaccensis , commonly called Javanese wild banana , is a Malesian tropical species of plant in the banana family native to the islands of Sumatra and Java , in Indonesia .
Azorhizobium caulinodans is a species of bacteria that forms a nitrogen - fixing symbiosis with plants of the genus Sesbania .
Insects in the subfamily Phymatinae are commonly called ambush bugs after their habit of lying in wait for prey relying on their superb camouflage .
Isochrysidales is an order of Haptophyceae .
Agave filifera ( thread agave ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae , native to Central Mexico from Querétaro to Mexico State .
Pseudovespicula dracaena , the Draco Waspfish , is a species of waspfish native to the western Indian Ocean .
The Anisopodidae are a small cosmopolitan family of gnat - like flies known as wood gnats or window - gnats , with 154 described extant species in 15 genera , and several described fossil taxa .
Goudkoffia is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Maastrichtian stage of the Late Cretaceous epoch .
Oxycera dives , the round - spotted major , is a European species of soldier fly .
Hoya is an Asclepiad genus of 200 - -300 species of tropical plants in the family Apocynaceae ( Dogbane ) .
Streptospondylus ( meaning `` reversed vertebra '' ) is a genus of tetanuran theropod dinosaur known from the Middle Jurassic period of France , 161 million years ago .
Arctognathus is an extinct genus of gorgonopsid that throve during the Late Permian in the Karoo basin of what is now South Africa .
Rorippa curvipes is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name bluntleaf yellowcress .
Adenium is a genus of flowering plants in the Apocynum family , Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1819 .
Brachypodium distachyon , commonly called purple false brome or stiff brome , is a grass species native to southern Europe , northern Africa and southwestern Asia east to India .
Adactylidium is a genus of mites known for its unusual life cycle .
It contains only one species , Ptyoptila matutinella which was described by Walker in 1864 and is found in Australia , where it has been recorded from Queensland , New South Wales , the Australian Capital Territory and Victoria .

Acleris robinsoniana , Robinson 's Acleris Moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .

The Chenggong fire belly newt ( Cynops chenggongensis ) is a species of newt of China .
Chlaenius is a large and diverse genus of ground beetle .

Cattleya crispa is a species of orchid indigenous to the Tijuca Mountains north of Rio de Janeiro , Brazil , noted for its crisped and ruffled petals and lip .
Petrocephalus bane is a species of elephantfish native to Africa where it occurs in the basins of the Nile , Bénoué and Volta rivers and the Chad Basin .
Olisthops cyanomelas , the herring cale , is a species of weed whiting endemic to Australia where it is found along the southern and south eastern coast .
Eremiaphila rohlfsi is a species of praying mantisin the family Eremiaphilidae .

Lampichthys procerus , the Blackhead lanternfish , is a species of lanternfish found circumglobally in the southern oceans .
Ephydra hians , common name the alkali fly , is a species of fly in the family Ephydridae , the brine flies .
Brimeura duvigneaudii is a species of plant that is endemic to Spain .
Crepis zacintha , common name striped hawksbeard , is a plant species native to southern Europe ( Greece , Italy , Albania , Bulgaria , etc . ) but now naturalized on roadsides and other disturbed sites in Texas , Israel , Cyprus , and the United Kingdom .
Dorycera graminum is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Dorycera of the family Ulidiidae found in Croatia , Corsica , the United Kingdom , Austria , Germany , Italy , Hungary , Poland , Portugal , Slovakia , and Spain .

Aristonectes ( meaning ' best swimmer ' ) is an extinct genus of plesiosaur from the Late Cretaceous of what is now South America and Antarctica .

Scyllarides squammosus is a species of slipper lobster known as the ' blunt slipper lobster .

Barbus kessleri ( gillbar barb ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
Cryptacanthodes giganteus , the Giant wrymouth , is a species of wrymouth found in the northeastern Pacific Ocean from the Bering Sea to northern California where it is believed to spend most of its life buried in soft areas at the bottom of the ocean at depths of from 6 to 128 metres ( 20 to 420 ft ) .

Megalorhipida deboeri is a species of moth in the genus Megalorhipida , known from Indonesia .
Hippopotamus antiquus , sometimes called the European Hippopotamus , was a species of hippopotamus that ranged across Europe , becoming extinct some time before the last ice age at the end of the Pleistocene epoch .

Soyauxia talbotii is a species of plant in the Peridiscaceae family .
Megabalanus concinnus is a species of barnacle in the family Balanidae .
The Neoepiblemidae are an extinct family of hystricognath rodents from South America .
Sanguisorba is a genus of flowering plants in the family Rosaceae native to the temperate regions of the Northern Hemisphere .
Barberenasuchus is an extinct genus of an archosauriform .
Geodia exigua is a sponge species that produces the sesquiterpene spiro compound exiguamide .
Megacheira ( `` Great Hands '' ) is an extinct class of predatory arthropods that possessed a pair of short enlarged appendages ( the source of the class ' name ) .
Semiarundinaria densiflora , the short - spiked bamboo , short - tassled bamboo , or short spikelet bamboo , is a species of bamboos .
Eucalyptus morrisbyi is a rare and endangered tree species endemic to south - eastern Tasmania .
Canalispira gomezi is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Cystiscidae .
Antiponemertes is a genus of nemertean worms that contains the following species :
Monacha cantiana , common name the `` Kentish snail '' or `` Kentish garden snail '' , is a species of medium - sized air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Melittosphex burmensis is the oldest - known species of bee .
Pardaloberea curvaticeps is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pardaloberea .
Brotogeris is a genus of small parrots endemic to Central and South America .
Doragnathus is an extinct genus of tetrapod from the Early Carboniferous of Scotland .
Echinomastus ( meaning `` spiny breast '' ) is a genus of cacti .
Channa harcourtbutleri is a species of snakehead endemic to Inle Lake and surroundings in Myanmar .
Tolidomordella discoidea is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , which is in the genus Tolidomordella .
Psychotria punctata , the dotted wild coffee , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae family .
Nielsenichthys pullus is a species of viviparous brotula found in Pacific Ocean waters around Indonesia where it occurs at depths of 5 to 20 metres ( 16 to 66 ft ) .
Downingia laeta is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Great Basin calicoflower .
Blackstonia perfoliata or yellow - wort is a species of flowering plant in the family Gentianaceae found around the Mediterranean Basin , but extending into northwestern Europe .
Antezumia is a monospecific neotropical genus of potter wasps restricted to the Amazonian basin .
Gelidium is a genus of thalloid red algae comprising 124 species .
Ipomopsis aggregata is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family ( Polemoniaceae ) , commonly known as scarlet trumpet , scarlet gilia , or skyrocket because of its scarlet red flowers with lobes curving back as if blown back by rocketing through the air .
Physaria filiformis ( syn . Lesquerella filiformis ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Missouri bladderpod and limestone glade bladderpod .
Gutierrezia texana is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Texas snakeweed .
Hozukius is a genus of rockfishes native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Agoseris retrorsa is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name spearleaf agoseris or spearleaf mountain dandelion .
Lithomyrtus is a genus of small trees and shrubs in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Bothrops hyoprorus , or the Amazonian toad - headed pitviper , is a species of venomous snake in the Viperidae family .
Pseudophragmatobia is a genus of moth in the family Arctiidae from South Africa .
Megaskepasma is a monotypic genus of plants containing the single species Megaskepasma erythrochlamys , known by the common name Brazilian red - cloak .
Neoglyphea inopinata is a species of glypheoid lobster , a group thought long extinct before Neoglyphea was discovered .
Ficus pakkensis is a species of plant in the family Moraceae which is found in Brazil and Guyana .
Feeserpeton is an extinct genus of parareptile from the Early Permian of Richard 's Spur , Oklahoma .
Falcaria vulgaris , the sickleweed or longleaf , is the sole species in the genus Falcaria .
Trimeresurus trigonocephalus , the Sri Lankan pit viper , Ceylon pit viper , Sri Lankan green pitviper or locally , pala polonga , ( Sinhalese : පළා පොළඟා ) is a venomous pit viper species endemic to Sri Lanka .
Systropha tropicalis is a species of bees in the genus Systropha , of the family Halictidae .
Trombidium southcotti is a species of mite in the genus Trombidium in the family Trombidiidae .
Hymenopappus carrizoanus , the Carrizo Sands woollywhite , is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
The Salamandroidea are a suborder of salamanders , referred to as advanced salamanders .
Cyathus is a genus of fungi in the Nidulariaceae , a family collectively known as the bird 's nest fungi .
Necromys is a genus of South American sigmodontine rodents allied to Akodon .
Draba sharsmithii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Mt.
The Pampas pipit ( Anthus chacoensis ) , also known as the Chaco pipit or Campo pipit , is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
Velvet water bugs are members of the family Hebridae .
Shanxia is a genus of ankylosaurid dinosaur that lived during the upper Cretaceous Period .
Cerberiopsis is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1873 .
Osmunda spectabilis is a species of fern once thought to be the same as Osmunda regalis , but recent genetic studies have shown it to be a separate species .
Borojevia brasiliensis is a species of sponge in the genus Borojevia from Brazil from which the species ' name is derived .
Eremopoa is a genus of Eurasian and Egyptian plants in the grass family .
The Lonchaeidae are a family of acalyptrate flies commonly known as lance flies .
Helianthemum nummularium ( known as common rock - rose ) is a species of rock - rose ( Cistaceae ) , native to most of Europe .
Peltogyne purpurea , commonly known as nazareno , or purpleheart , is a species of Peltogyne tree native to the Pacific coast of Costa Rica and Panama , and also the Atlantic coast of Colombia .
Anopheles walkeri is a species of mosquito found predominantly throughout the Mississippi River Valley , with its habitat ranging as far north as southern Quebec , Canada .
Sphodromantis quinquecallosa is a species of praying mantis found in Africa .
Tectaria triloba is a species of fern in the Tectariaceae family .
Sahyadria denisonii ( Denison barb , red - line torpedo barb , or roseline shark ) is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the fast - flowing hill streams and rivers of the Western Ghats in India .
Platydoras costatus , the Raphael catfish , is a species of thorny catfish of the genus Platydoras widespread throughout northern South America down to Argentina .
Nothotsuga contains only one species , Nothotsuga longibracteata , commonly known as the Bristlecone Hemlock , which is found in southeastern China , in southern Fujian , northern Guangdong , northeast Guangxi , northeast Guizhou and southwest Hunan .
Lomatium is a genus of about 75 species of perennial herbs native to western North America .
Calonectria reteaudii is a species of fungi in the family Nectriaceae .
Lathrecista asiatica , the Asiatic blood tail , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Phyla lanceolata is a species of flowering plant in the verbena family known by the common name lanceleaf fogfruit or frogfruit .
Pseudopilema hoppingi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudopilema .
Jasminum tortuosum is a species of jasmine native to South Africa .
Etlingera maingayi ( also known as Malay rose ) is a species of herbaceous perennial plant of the Zingiberaceae family .
Crotalus viridis ( Common names : prairie rattlesnake , western rattlesnake , Great Plains rattlesnake , and others ) is a venomous pit viper species native to the western United States , southwestern Canada , and northern Mexico .
Vasilevskaya 's onion ( Allium vasilevskajae ) is a species of onion that is endemic to Syunik Province in Armenia .
Branchinella apophysata is a species of crustacean in the family Thamnocephalidae .
Allium parvum is an American species of wild onion known by the common name small onion .
Balthasarella melandryoides is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Balthasarella .
Oeceoclades maculata , sometimes known as the monk orchid or African spotted orchid , is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is native to tropical Africa and now naturalized in South and Central America , the Caribbean , and Florida in North America .
Euphilotes ancilla , the Rocky Mountain dotted blue , is a species of butterfly of the Lycaenidae family .
Lygodium palmatum is the only species of its genus native to North America .
The Gryphaeidae , common name the foam oysters or honeycomb oysters , are a family of marine bivalve mollusks , and are a kind of true oyster .
The main species of Clemensodon is Clemensodon megaloba , however , this species is also known as a part of Kimbetohia campi .
Astrantia major , common name great masterwort , is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae , native to central and eastern Europe .
Cynomacrurus piriei , the Dogtooth Grenadier , is a species of rattail that occurs in the southern oceans , mostly south of the Antarctic Convergence .
Nothophryne broadleyi ( common name : Broadley 's mountain frog , mongrel frog ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family found on Mount Mulanje ( Malawi ) and Mount Ribaue ( Mozambique ) .
Saitis annae is a species of jumping spider in the Salticidae family .
Deiracephalus is an extinct genus of trilobites .
Epilobium oregonense is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name Oregon willowherb .
Microsuchus is an extinct genus of mesoeucrocodylian .
Blandfordia is a genus of flowering plants , placed in the family Blandfordiaceae of the order Asparagales of the monocots .
Minuartia rubella is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by several common names , including beautiful sandwort , Arctic sandwort , and boreal stitchwort .
Hexacona armata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Hexacona .
Linaria ricardoi is a very rare Portuguese endemic plant species .
Leymus angustus is a species of grass known by the common name Altai wildrye .
Eryngium constancei is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Loch Lomond button celery , or Loch Lomond coyote thistle .
Allium chiwui is a plant species endemic to the Chinese Province of Hebei .
Sepia subplana is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean .
Salix boothii is a species of willow known by the common name Booth 's willow .
Bovitrigla acanthomoplate is a species of searobin native to the western Pacific Ocean near the Philippines where it occurs at depths of from 333 to 500 metres ( 1,093 to 1,640 ft ) .
Halenia weddelliana ( Cacho de Venado , Deer 's Antlers ) is a species of plant in the Gentianaceae family .
Epicrates monensis , known commonly as the Mona boa , is a species of snake in the Boidae family .
Drosophila erecta is a West African species of fruit fly , and was one of 12 fruit fly genomes sequenced for a large comparative study .
Amolops loloensis is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is endemic to southern Sichuan , China .
Lytoceras eudesianum is an ammonite species belonging to the family Lytoceratidae .
Adelpha californica , commonly known as the California Sister , is a species of butterfly in the family Nymphalidae .
Popillia bipunctata , the Yellow Shining Leaf Chafer , is a species of scarab beetles .
Myrmecia pavida is a bull ant species which lives and is native in Australia .
Psychidarbela kalshoveni is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Psychidarbela .
Mimonephelotus flavomarmoratus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimonephelotus .
Eidothea hardeniana , commonly named Nightcap Oak , is a species of trees up to 40 m ( 130 ft ) tall , of the plant family Proteaceae , which botanist Robert Kooyman recognised as a new species only recently in 2000 .
Actinoprosopa maris is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Actinoprosopa of the family Tachinidae .
Nornalupia megacephala is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Nornalupia .
Leaf beetles of the genus Neochlamisus are sometimes known as the warty leaf beetles .
Quercus gambelii flourishes in full sun on hillsides with thin , rocky , alkaline soil where competition from other plant species is limited .
Castorimorpha is the suborder of rodents containing the beavers , the pocket gophers , and the kangaroo rats and mice .
Pholisma sonorae , commonly known as sandfood , is a rare and unusual species of flowering plant endemic to the Sonoran Deserts to the west of Yuma , Arizona in the California Yuha and Colorado Desert , and south in the Yuma Desert , where it is known from only a few locations .
Kneria ruaha is a freshwater species of fish in the Kneriidae family endemic to Tanzania .
Anophthalmolabis is a genus of earwigs , the sole member of the subfamily Anophthalmolabiinae .
Chrysopsis lanuginosa , called the Lynn Haven goldenaster , is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Aedes cinereus is a mosquito species in the genus Aedes .
The Cyatholipidae are a spider family with 58 described species in 23 genera .
Allium brevistylum is a plant species native to the western United States .
Hazardia squarrosa is a North American species of shrub in the daisy family known by the common name sawtooth goldenbush .
Boettgeria obesiuscula is a species of small , very elongate , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails , all of which have a clausilium .
The Ovambo tree skink ( Trachylepis binotata ) is a species of skink from Namibia and Angola also known as Bocage 's Mabuya .
Bursa corrugata , common name the gaudy frog shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bursidae , the frog shells .
Miniopterus ( bent - winged bat , long winged bat ) is the only genus of bats in the family Miniopteridae .
Capitaspis is an extinct genus of cyathaspidine cyathaspidid heterostracan jawless vertebrate known from the Late Silurian Somerset Island Formation ( Pridolian epoch ) of the Northwest Territories , Canada .
Monomorium dentatum is an ant species which has been discovered on August 20 , 2003 by M. R. Sharaf in Egypt and described by Sharaf , M. R. in 2007 .
Cyanea mannii is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Mann 's cyanea .
Yunnanodon ( `` Yunnan tooth '' , from China 's Yunnan province where it was discovered , and the Greek don(ti ) ( δόντι ) meaning `` tooth '' ) was a genus of non - mammalian therapsid that lived in China during the Sinemurian stage of the Early Jurassic period .
Quercus sinuata , the bastard oak , bastard white oak , or Durand oak , is North American species of oak .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Anariste poliothea .
Lentinus sajor - caju ( formerly known as Pleurotus sajor - caju ) is a species of saprophytic mushroom .
The line forest - skimmer , or pale - faced forest - skimmer , ( Cratilla lineata ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Philbertia tokyoensis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turridae .
Picrosia is a genus of South American plants in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family .
Megacephala basalis is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Macleay in 1866 , and is endemic to Australia .
Viola odorata is a species of the genus Viola native to Europe and Asia , but has also been introduced to North America and Australia .
Luzuriagaceae is the botanical name of a family of flowering plants that was recognized in the 1998 APG system and the 2003 APG II system .
Hypopetalia pestilens , the white - dotted redspot , is a monotypic species of dragonfly in the family Austropetaliidae .
Ficus opposita is one of several fig species commonly known as Sandpaper figs . It is native to the Northern Territory and Queensland in Australia . Other common names include Sweet Sandpaper Fig , Sweet Fig and the ambiguous `` figwood '' and `` watery fig '' .
Rouleina is a genus of slickheads .
It contains only one species , Eupithystis infuscata which is found on Borneo and Sumatra .
Cystovirus is a genus of viruses , in the family Cystoviridae .
The purple - striped jelly ( Chrysaora colorata , formerly Pelagia colorata ) is a species of jellyfish that exists primarily off the coast of California in Monterey Bay .
Tevnia jerichonana is a species of giant tube worm in the family Siboglinidae , living in a unique deep - sea environment .
The single described species Poessa argenteofrenata is endemic to Madagascar .
Astragalus casei is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Case 's milkvetch .
Columbinae is a subfamily of birds from the family Columbidae .
Krefftichthys anderssoni is a species of lanternfish found circumglobally in the southern oceans .
Nactus kunan is an extant species of slender - toe gecko described in 2012 , and indigenous to the Admiralty Islands of Papua New Guinea .
Aspergillus nidulans ( also called Emericella nidulans when referring to its sexual form , or teleomorph ) is one of many species of filamentous fungi in the phylum Ascomycota .
Diania is an extinct genus of animal found in the Lower Cambrian Maotianshan shale of China , represented by a single species D. cactiformis .
Marasmius elegans , commonly known as the velvet parachute , is a species of fungus in the Marasmiaceae family of mushrooms .
Brasilitherium ( `` Brazilian beast '' ) is a genus of cynodont that lived during the Late Triassic in what is now Brazil .
Lamium maculatum ( also known as spotted dead - nettle , spotted henbit and purple dragon ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native throughout Europe and temperate Asia ( Lebanon , Syria , Turkey , western China ) .
Echinacea pallida , commonly called pale purple coneflower , is a species of herbaceous perennial plant in the family Asteraceae .
Dacrymyces palmatus ( Orange Jelly ) is a species of fungi in the family Dacrymycetaceae , and is edible .
The subfamily Catomerinae represents Southern Hemisphere Catophragmids .
Phragmoteuthida is an order of coleoid cephalopods characterized by a fan - like teuthoid pro - ostracum attached to a belemnoid - like phragmocone .
Caedocyon ( `` fit for cutting dog '' ) is an extinct genus of bone crushing omnivorous mammal similar to a dog of the family Canidae ) which inhabited western North America during the Oligocene living from 30.8 - -20.6 Ma and existed for approximately 10.2 million years .
Rauna is an extinct genus of prawn , containing the single species Rauna angusta , described from the Solnhofen limestones of southern Germany .
Hualianceratops is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaur that lived about 160 million years ago in the Late Jurassic epoch in what is now western China .
Astragalus tricarinatus is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common name triplerib milkvetch , or triple - ribbed milkvetch .
Phelsuma grandis Gray , 1870 , is a diurnal arboreal species of day gecko ( Phelsuma spp . )
Artemidiconus selenae is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conorbidae .
Oncidium deltoideum is a species of orchid found from southern Ecuador to northern Peru .
Acacia demissa is species of Acacia native to an area of Western Australia inland of Shark Bay .
Stipecampus cristatus , the Ring - backed pipefish , is a species of pipefish found in the waters of the Indian Ocean off the southern coast of Australia .
Hastingsia bracteosa is a rare species of flowering plant in the agave subfamily of the asparagus family known by the common name large - flowered rushlily .
Pyromaia cuspidata , also known as the dartnose pear crab , is a species of crab in the family Inachoididae .
Piezogenista callytra is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Piezogenista .
Austroboletus occidentalis , commonly known as the ridge - stemmed bolete , is a species of bolete fungus found in Australia .
Dehalobacter is a genus in the phylum Firmicutes ( Bacteria ) .
Zostera marina is a species of seagrass known by the common names common eelgrass and seawrack .
Halichoeres scapularis , commonly called the Zigzag wrasse , is a fish species in the wrasse family native from the Indo - West Pacific .
Afromicrodon is an African genus of hoverflies .
Teratobaikalia macrostoma is a species of a freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Amnicolidae .
The only species is Cephalosphaera usambarensis , which is native to the moist evergreen forests of Kenya and Tanzania .
Haplochromis rufocaudalis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria where it is known with certainty from Sengerema , the Speke Gulf and Mwanza Gulf though it may occur in other locations .
The spider species Tegenaria domestica , commonly known as the barn funnel weaver in North America and the domestic house spider in Europe , is a member of the funnel - web family Agelenidae and a close relative of the hobo spider .
Epimedium wushanense , the Wushan fairy wings , is a flowering plant species in the genus Epimedium .
Berosus chevrolati is a species of hydrophilid beetle from Cuba .
Odontolabis delesserti is a quite rare species of beetles belonging to the Lucanidae family .
Dichelostemma congestum is a species of flowering plant known by the common name ookow or fork - toothed ookow .
Histeridae is a family of beetles commonly known as Clown beetles or Hister beetles .
It was described by Holloway in 1981 , and the type species is Daytonia werthneri , which was originally described under the genus Dalmanites by Foerste in 1885 .
Ischyroplectron is a monotypic genus of weta containing the species Ischyroplectron isolatum .
Odontamblyopus lacepedii is a species of eel goby found in muddy - bottomed coastal waters in China , Korea and Japan .
Howard Marsh ( 1888 - 1969 ) was a leading Broadway tenor of the 1920s .
Teresa Cornelys ( sometimes spelt Theresa ; born Anna Maria Teresa Imer , Venice , 1723 -- died Fleet Prison , London , 19 August 1797 ) was an operatic soprano and impresario who hosted fashionable gatherings at Carlisle House in Soho Square .
Carlo Galeffi ( June 4 , 1884 -- September 22 , 1961 ) was a leading Italian baritone , particularly associated with the operatic works of Giuseppe Verdi and the various verismo composers .
Dolora Zajick ( pronounced ZAH jick ) ( born 24 March 1952 ) is an American mezzo - soprano opera singer who specializes in the Verdian repertoire .
Gaetano Bardini ( born October 8 , 1929 in Riparbella ) is an Italian tenor .
Loretta Di Franco is an American operatic soprano who is chiefly known for her more than 900 performances at the Metropolitan Opera from 1961 - 1995 .
Julia Lezhneva ( Russian : Юлия Михайловна Лежнева ) ( born December 5 , 1989 ) is a Russian soprano opera singer and recitalist , specialising in soprano and coloratura mezzo - soprano material of the 18th and early 19th century .
Martin Lattke ( born 29 May 1981 ) is a German tenor , performing as a soloist and former member of the ensemble amarcord .
Yvonne Gall ( 6 March 1885 -- 21 August 1972 ) was a famous French operatic soprano .
William Dooley ( born September 9 , 1932 , Modesto , California ) is an American operatic bass - baritone who has sung with many of the world 's greatest opera companies .
Hildegard Behrens ( 9 February 1937 -- 18 August 2009 ) was a German soprano with a wide repertoire including Wagner , Weber , Mozart , Richard Strauss , and Alban Berg roles .
Emma Calvé , born Rosa Emma Calvet ( 15 August 1858 -- 6 January 1942 ) , was a French operatic soprano .
Johann Michael Wächter ( 2 March 1794 -- 26 May 1853 ) was an Austrian bass - baritone most famous for appearing in the operas of Richard Wagner .
Elizabeth Mannion is an American operatic mezzo - soprano who has performed at opera houses throughout the world .
Vladimir Galouzine ( Russian : Владимир Галузин , Vladimir Galuzin , pronounced ( vlɐˈdʲimʲɪr ɡɐˈluzʲɪn ) ) is a Russian tenor .
Olga Averino ( November 15 , 1895 -- January 17 , 1989 ) was a Russian - born soprano and voice teacher .
Arda Mandikian ( 1 September 1924 -- 8 November 2009 ) was a Greek Armenian soprano opera singer .
Arlene Saunders ( born in Cleveland , on October 5 , 1935 ) is an American spinto soprano opera singer .
Louise Mott is a British mezzo - soprano .
Julius Huehn ( January 12 , 1904 -- June 8 , 1971 ) , was an operatic bass - baritone .
Myra Merritt is an American operatic soprano , who was born in Washington , DC . She earned a Bachelor of Music from the Peabody Conservatory of Music , and a Master of Music from the Catholic University of America .
Ferruccio Furlanetto ( born 16 May 1949 in Sacile , Italy ) is an Italian bass .
Isa Quensel ( 21 September 1905 -- 3 November 1981 ) was a Swedish actress and operatic soprano who appeared in over 50 films , plays , operas , TV and radio shows .
Linda Lister ( born June 30 , 1969 ) is an American soprano and teacher of singing .
Giuseppe De Luca ( 25 December 1876 -- 26 August 1950 ) , was an Italian baritone who achieved his greatest triumphs at the Metropolitan Opera in New York City .
Jeremy Huw Williams ( born 3 April 1969 in Cardiff ) is a Welsh baritone opera singer who studied at Ysgol Gyfun Gymraeg Glantaf , St John 's College , Cambridge , at the National Opera Studio , and with April Cantelo .
Enric Martínez - Castignani ( Barcelona , 1970 ) is an Italo - Spanish baritone who sings opera and lieder .
Hildegard Laurich ( 15 January 1941 -- 11 February 2009 ) , was a German classical contralto singer .
Emmy Krüger ( 27 November 1886 - 13 March 1976 ) was a German operatic soprano .
Antonio Paoli ( April 14 , 1871 -- August 24 , 1946 ) was a Puerto Rican tenor .
Teresa Stich - Randall ( December 24 , 1927 -- July 17 , 2007 ) was a European - based American soprano opera singer .
Mirella Freni ( Italian : ( miˈrɛlːa ˈfreːni ) ; born Mirella Fregni on 27 February 1935 ) is an Italian opera soprano whose repertoire includes Verdi , Puccini , Mozart and Tchaikovsky .
Johann Michael Vogl ( August 10 , 1768 -- November 19 , 1840 ) , was an Austrian baritone singer and composer .
Jan - Hendrik Rootering ( born 18 March 1950 in Wedingfeld near Flensburg ) is a German - born operatic bass , son of the Dutch tenor Hendrikus Rootering from whom he had his first lessons .
David Melvin English ( October 12 , 1942 -- February 23 , 1995 ) better known by the stage name Melvin Franklin , or his nickname `` Blue '' , was an American bass singer .
Otakar Kraus ( 10 December 1909 -- 28 July 1980 ) was a Czech ( later British ) , operatic baritone and teacher .
Elena Zoubareva is a Russian American soprano specializing in opera and classical crossover .
Nina Koshetz ( Russian : Нина Павловна Кошиц ; née Poray - Koshetz ( ru:Порай-Кошиц ) ; 30 December 1891 -- 14 May 1965 ) was a Russian - Ukrainian , later American opera soprano , recital singer and actress .
Yuan Chenye , also known as Chen - Ye Yuan ( 袁晨野 ; Dalian , 1967 ) is a Chinese operatic baritone .
